title: DoorTelnet Room Graph
description: Room navigation graph with nodes (rooms), edges (exits), and region data for MUD pathfinding

regionNames.description: Map of region IDs to human-readable region names

nodes.description: Array of room nodes with metadata

spawn_total.description: Total number of monsters that can spawn

edges.description: Array of directional connections between rooms

dir.description: Movement direction command (n, s, e, w, ne, nw, se, sw, u, d, etc.)

nodes.s: The Void
nodes.l: nan

nodes.s: The Imperial Room of Creation
nodes.l: ...you are in the Imperial Room of Creation.  The walls are nothing more than barriers to other worlds from which you, the Elders, receive your great powers and abilities of creation.  You gaze out upon the lands that you have created and smile.  Already, though, the urge to create more begins to stir you into motion - there is so much yet to be done.
nodes.quest_text: mortal me ... You give up the Elder Power. ... %s gives up the Elder Power!

nodes.s: You are walking down Imperial Lane.
nodes.l:
...that you are walking down a very well kept street.  Imperial Lane is
an impressive piece of land; trees line either side of the street, and
the street itself is paved smooth using a method that can barely be
understood.  The stones on either side of the road that glow with
a bluish light that make this area well lit.  Imperial Lane continues to
the north, eventually meeting with the Imperial Castle, while to the
south lies the rest of Imperial City.

nodes.s: You are standing in the Imperial Square.
nodes.l:
...that you are in a great open area within the city.  Imperial Square houses
a guard's station which seems to be always teeming with Imperial
Guardsman.  Imperius Street runs east and west from here.  To the south,
Imperius Street becomes Northern Avenue.  North is Imperial Lane which
leads to the Imperial Castle.
nodes.quest_text: present invasion plans ... You hand the plans to the Imperial Captain. ... %s hands a scroll over to the Imperial Captain. ... ,0

nodes.s: You are walking on Imperius Street.
nodes.l:
...that you are walking about the great expanse of the Imperial Castle.
This street circles around the limits of the castle grounds; a huge wall
separates you from the castle, though the castle can be seen jutting up
from behind the wall.  The street is paved smooth, and glistens
with even the slightest bit of light.  To the east is the Imperial
Square, while Imperius Street continues to the west.

nodes.s: You are walking on Imperius Street.
nodes.l:
... that you are walking around the great Imperial Castle.  Many bushes
line the streets here, giving this area a tranquil quality about it.  The
top of the castle can barely be seen over the great wall.  The
street is made of the same glitterglow from which the rest of the town's
street is made.  Imperius Street continues to the north and south
from here.

nodes.s: You are at an intersection.
nodes.l:
...that you are at the intersection of Imperius Street and Bankers
Lane.  Although the street here is made of glitterglow, it has a golden
sheen to it towards the east, which is where Bankers Lane begins.
Imperius Street continues to the north and south, as well.

nodes.s: You are walking on Imperius Street.
nodes.l:
...that you are at the northern most area of the Imperial City.  You
feel slightly claustrophobic when in this area, as you feel closed in by
the two great walls of the city; the southern wall separating you from
the Imperial Grounds, while the northern wall separates the City from
the lands beyond.  Imperius Street continues to the west as well as
to the south.

nodes.s: You stand before the Northern Imperial Gate.
nodes.l:
...that you are standing before one of the Great Imperial Gates.  The
Northern Gate has been closed for quite some time due to the extreme
dangers of the lands to the north.  By order of the Council, guardsmen
prevent the passage of anyone to the north.  Imperius Street does
continue to the east and west, however.

nodes.s: You are walking on Imperius Street.
nodes.l:
...that you are walking on a street around the great Imperial Castle.
Imperius Lane has a wall that separates the castle's land from the
street, however, you can see the great Imperial Castle over this wall.
To the north is the most northern area of the city, while the rest of
the city continues to the south.

nodes.s: Imperius Street and Contemplation Way meet here.
nodes.l:
...that you at an intersection.  Imperius Lane, the great road around
the Imperial City, meets with Contemplation Way, where the Great Garden
can be found.  A short path to the west will lead to the Great Garden
and to the Monastery beyond, while the Lane continues to the north and
south.

nodes.s: You stroll down Bankers Lane.
nodes.l:
...that you are walking on a glowing golden road.  Bankers Lane has
streets that appear to be gold, but that you know to be something other than
this precious metal.  Created with the same glitterglow as the rest of
the city, the streets of Banker Lane glitter with its golden light in
the presence of even the slightest light.  Further east is the Imperial
Bank, while Imperius Street is to the west.

nodes.s: You stroll down Bankers Lane.
nodes.l:
...that you are walking on a glowing golden road.  Bankers Lane has
streets that appear to be made of gold, but you know that even the
Council of Olde would not waste such a precious commodity.  Glittering
and glowing with the same magical substance with which the other roads are
created, everything here seems to have a slight golden sheen to it.
Further east is the Imperial Bank, while further west lies Imperius
Street - you are right in the middle of both landmarks.

nodes.s: You stroll down Bankers Lane.
nodes.l:
...that you standing in front of the Imperial Bank.  The great doors to
the bank are over twelve feet high; the great hinges of these doors are
gilded in gold.  The rest of this great building is made entirely of
steel, though the building has been magicked to prevent any type of
magicks to affect it.  Bankers Lane continues to the east.

nodes.s: You have arrived at The Imperial Bank.
nodes.l:
...that you have entered The Imperial Bank.  A huge table is centered in
the main room of the bank.  Behind it sits an elderly gentleman who
handles the scales used for trade as if he were born to them.  Several
guards stand next to the gentleman, guarding him from all who would
attempt to take advantage of his elderly state.  Several rooms lead from
the main room - these are for private transactions and personal safes.

nodes.s: You shuffle down Contemplation Way.
nodes.l:
...that you are in serene surroundings.  Trees rise high above you from
either side of the street, blocking out most of the natural light.  The
glitterglow that is normally quite strong has been subdued, creating a
peaceful, shadowed environment.  Sounds are muted here, and feelings of
calm overcome you as you walk down one of the most peaceful streets of
the Imperial City.  Contemplation Way continues to the west; the east
leads back to Imperius Street.

nodes.s: You shuffle down Contemplation Way.
nodes.l:
...that you are in very peaceful surroundings.  Trees tower over you and
they block out most of the sunlight that would normally be here.  The
streets seemed subdued, not with evil, but with serenity.  Sounds here
are muted, and even your footsteps seem to have a hypnotic quality to
them.  To the west is the Great Garden of Thought; Contemplation Way
continues to the east.

nodes.s: You are in the Garden of Thought.
nodes.l:
...that you are walking in the Great Garden of Thought.  This great
garden is, perhaps, one of the most breathtaking sights within the
Imperial City.  Flowers of all types grow here, and several sitting
stones are set about this place.  Trees that grow to enormous heights
house various birds which sing their joyful songs.  Several meditating
brothers of the monastery are seen in various places.  There are no
paths here, rather, the entire Garden is available for your needs.

nodes.s: You are in the Garden's passage.
nodes.l:
...that the garden's passage is no less serene than the connecting
areas.  This area is well maintained by the brothers of the Imperial
Monastery.  Well trimmed hedges that have flowers complimenting their
shapes surround you.  The ground is made of hardened clay that has been
mixed with glitterglow.  You hear the shuffle of several brothers as
they pass you in their travels.  The Imperial Monastery lies at the west
end of this passage, while the Great Garden lies to the east.

nodes.s: You are in the Garden's passage.
nodes.l:
...that the garden's passage is no less serene than the connecting
areas.  This area is well maintained by the brothers of the Imperial
Monastery.  Well trimmed hedges that have flowers complementing their
shapes surround you.  The ground is made of hardened clay that has been
mixed with glitterglow.  You hear the shuffle of several brothers as
they pass you in their travels.  The Great Garden lies at the east
end of this passage, while the Monastery Entrance lies to the east.

nodes.s: You are in the Imperial Monestery.
nodes.l:
....the beauty of the Imperial Monastery.  The walls are made of the
purest ivory, and have been washed and polished to a perfect sheen.
Several murals hang on these walls, mostly depicting monks and priests
in various forms of meditation.  One large mural in particular catches your eye; it depicts a battle scene of several monks in combat with many
creatures of darkness.  In the corner of this waiting room, a monk
instructs several other people on the best ways to combat these
creatures.  There is a chamber to the south that you may enter, or you
may exit the monastery to the east.

nodes.s: You are in the Imperial Monastery.
nodes.l:
...the beauty of the Imperial Monastery.  The walls here are made of the
same ivory as the rest of the monastery, but have been treated so as to
give off a soothing blue sheen.  Several sitting mats are on the floor
of this room, and many scholars care for the shelves of scrolls that
line the eastern wall.  Many of the mats are occupied by monks pouring
over the secrets of these texts.  Several more of these mats are taken
up by monks who are choosing to use the serenity of this place to
meditate.  There are chambers north and south from here.

nodes.s: You are in the Imperial Monastery.
nodes.l:
...the inner chamber of the Monastery of Contemplation.  It is here, you
see, that many of the brothers practice the arts that they have spent so
long studying.  Several injured animals are being tended to by the
youngest of the monks, while the lay brothers practice their healing
magicks on people that are unfortunate enough to require healing
services.  There is only one exit from here, which leads to a northern
chamber.

nodes.s: You are on Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...the majesty of the Imperial City Streets.  You are on  the northernmost
part of Northern Avenue.  You can hear the sounds of deep gruff voices
as the guards go over their orders in the Imperial Square to the north.
Beyond the Imperial Square is the grand sight of the Imperial Castle,
which used to be home to the Council of Guardians.  Southward,
Northern Avenue continues and eventually meets the Town Square.

nodes.s: You are on Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...the impressiveness of Northern Avenue.  The glitterglow of this
street is stronger than many of the others, almost inviting you to walk
upon its surface.  Northern Avenue is one of the most traveled roads of
Imperial City. Like the rest of the city, however, it is immaculate;
it is difficult to see any signs of travel upon this street.  Northern
Avenue continues both north and south from here.

it is difficult to see any signs of travel upon this street.  Northern
Avenue continues both north and south from here.

nodes.s: You are on Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...the impressiveness of Northern Avenue.  The glitterglow of this
street is stronger than many of the others, almost inviting you to walk
upon its surface.  Northern Avenue is one of the most traveled roads of
Imperial City. Like the rest of the city, however, it is immaculate;
it is difficult to see any signs of travel upon this street.  Northern
Avenue continues both north and south from here.

nodes.s: You are on Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...the impressiveness of Northern Avenue.  The glitterglow of this
street is stronger than many of the others, almost inviting you to walk
upon its surface.  Northern Avenue is one of the most traveled roads of
Imperial City. Like the rest of the city, however, it is immaculate;
it is difficult to see any signs of travel upon this street.  Northern
Avenue continues both north and south from here.

nodes.s: You are at a busy intersection.
nodes.l:
...a fairly old road intersecting with Northern Avenue.  Hunters Way is
devoid of the glitterglow that the rest of the city has about it;
rather, Hunters Way is lit by tall lamps that are maintained by the
Taxidermist.  The road here is made of hardened dirt, though it is
smoothed and unmarked.  It is easy to see that the road has been
magicked to insure its smooth appearance.  Signs along Hunters Way show
that the Taxidermist Shop lies to the northeast.  Northern Avenue
continues north and south as well.

nodes.s: You are walking down Hunters Way.
nodes.l:
...that you are walking along a lantern-lit dirt road.  The road,
though made of dirt, is very smooth and unmarred.  It is easy to see
that, despite all attempts to make this area look natural, Hunters
Way is no less a part of Imperial City than any other part.  Hunters Way
continues to the northeast, and connects with Northern Avenue to the
southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking down Hunters Way.
nodes.l:
...the lantern lit beauty of Hunters Way.  The dirt road, though
perfectly smooth, has a quality to it that the glitterglow based roads
of the city lack.  The scent of this area reminds you that there are
great lands beyond the walls of Imperial City that can be explored and
settled.  Hunters Way runs northeast and southwest from here.

nodes.s: You are walking down Hunters Way.
nodes.l:
...the lantern lit beauty of Hunters Way.  The dirt road, though
perfectly smooth, has a quality to it that the glitterglow based roads
of the city lack.  The scent of this area reminds you that there are
great lands beyond the walls of Imperial City that can be explored and
settled.  Hunters Way runs east and southwest from here.

nodes.s: You are walking down Hunters Way.
nodes.l:
...that you are near the Taxidermy Shop.  A small house is seen in the
distance to the east; even from here you can see the great sign
proclaiming the trade of the person who lives here.  Trees have been
placed along the side of the road here, and the figures of many wildlife
animals have been placed with the trees, and among them, to give this
area an outdoor quality to it.  The road continues east to the Taxidermy
house, and also returns to the city towards the west.

nodes.s: You are walking down Hunters Way.
nodes.l:
...that you stand before the Taxidermy Shop.  Two great deer have been
mounted on either side of the door leading to this house.  The door,
itself, has a great bear skin hanging on it.  The house appears to be
made completely of wood.  With all this, it is difficult to remember
that you are actually in the Great Imperial City; it seems more like you
are at a hut in the woods.  Hunters Way leads from this house to the
east.

nodes.s: You have entered the Taxiderm's Shop.
nodes.l:
...the works of the taxiderm.  Hides of many different animals line the
walls and floor of this quaint little house.  Humanoid bodies (can they
really be human?) stand in various positions of hunt sporting skins and
leathers of many animals.  The taxidermist himself is a gruff dwarf, who
gives the appearance of being a man who is apt to waste little.  The
door to his leads out to Hunters Way to the west.
nodes.quest_text: present scale ... You hand the precious scales to the shopkeep. ... %s hands something to the shopkeep. ... .$

nodes.s: You are walking down Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...a few of the main roads of the Imperial City.  North and east of here
is the dirt-lined Hunters Way, while south and west of here is Short
Street.  Through the trees and houses of Imperial City, you can barely
make out the Imperial Square to the south.  Northern Avenue here,
though, only goes north and south.

nodes.s: Northern Avenue meets Short Street here.
nodes.l:
...the intersection of Short Street and Northern Avenue.  Many of the
main roads of Imperial City look much alike - glittering with its
trademark glow.  These two roads are no exception.  Short Street runs
west of here, while Northern Avenue leads both north and south from
here.

nodes.s: You are walking down Short Street.
nodes.l:
...a house lined street.  Short Street is one of the few main roads of
Imperial City that has residential worth.  The houses here are fairly
large, and follow the grandeur that Imperial City impresses upon those
that live here.  Short Street continues to the west, and meets with
Northern Avenue to the east.

nodes.s: You are walking down Short Street.
nodes.l:
...one of the few residential areas of Imperial City.  Short Street has
the privilege of being lined with houses.  These houses are large and
spacious; they fit right into the spacious areas of Imperial City.
Short Street leads into Torith Street to the west, while eastwards
eventually leads into Northern Avenue.

nodes.s: Torith Street and Short Street meet here.
nodes.l:
...one of the many intersections of Imperial City.  Short Street, which
is used to connect the Northern Quarter and the Western Quarter, meets
with Torith Street here.  To the north, you can see the great gates of
one of the Great Arenas of Imperial City.  You see that Torith Street
goes south from here as well.  Short Street lies to the east, and
eventually meets with Northern Avenue.

nodes.s: You are walking down Torith Street.
nodes.l:
...one of the many glitterglow lined streets of Imperial City.  Torith
Street continues to the north, and eventually leads into one of the
great arenas of Imperial City.  Imperial City leads into Short Street
to the south.

nodes.s: You stand before Torith Arena.
nodes.l:
...the great brass gates of Torith Arena.  The sounds of combat resound
deep beyond the brass gates.  Great warnings have been posted around the
gates in every major language - the creatures within are deadly and show
no quarter.  Torith Street leads from the arena to the south.

nodes.s: You are in Torith Arena.
nodes.l:
...that you have entered Torith Arena.  Torches line this building; it
is not lit by the same glitterglow as the rest of the city.  The shadows
cast give the arena an eerie sense to it.  The arena master stands
beside a great brass gong; one of the ancients, he is responsible for
the summoning of the creatures into this great arena.  Great brass gates
lead south out of the arena.

nodes.s: You walk along South Torith Street.
nodes.l:
...the southern part of Torith Avenue.  Aptly named South Torith, this
street leads to the south.  Northwards, this street meets with Short
Street.

nodes.s: You walk along South Torith Street.
nodes.l:
...the glowing streets of Imperial City.  South Torith Street glitters
in the light, like much of Imperial City.  Far north, beyond the
intersection of Short Street, lies the Torith Arena.  Southwards, South
Torith turns west onto Western Road.

nodes.s: This is the corner of South Torith and Westgate.
nodes.l:
...the majesty of Westgate Road.  Far to the west can be seen one of the
great Imperial Gates that lead to the wilderness outside of the walled
city.  Westgate Road runs west from here, while South Torith Street runs
north from here.

nodes.s: You are on Westgate Road.
nodes.l:
...a well kept road.  Westgate Road runs westward towards the Western
Imperial Gate.  Eastward, the road turns north to South Torith.  You see
that to the west, another street meets with Westgate Road.

nodes.s: Westgate Road and Talib Street meet here.
nodes.l:
...one of the many intersections of this city.  Talib Street, formally
known as Back Alley, runs south from Westgate Road here.  Renamed in
honor of one of the Councilors of Olde, Talib Street has a quiet and serene
quality about it.

nodes.s: You are walking along Westgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the well swept roads of Imperial City.  Westgate Road, like the other
roads of this great city, have been treated with glitterglow so that the
very streets gleam in even the dimmest of lights.  Westward, the road
runs toward one of the great gates.  Eastward, this road meets with
Talib Street.

nodes.s: You are walking along Westgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the well swept roads of Imperial City.  Westgate Road, like the other
roads of this great city, have been treated with glitterglow so that the
very streets gleam in even the dimmest of lights.  Westward, the road
meets with Magus Way, while the road continues eastward.

nodes.s: Westgate and Magus Way meet here.
nodes.l:
...the intersection of Magus Way and Westgate Road.  Westgate road runs
westward towards the western gate; it also continues eastward as well.
Magus Way runs south, and you can see the great Wizard's Spire to which
Magus Way leads.

nodes.s: This is Talib Street.
nodes.l:
...the long stretch of Talib Street.  This street is quiet and barely
occupied.  Only a few houses line this street, and most of these have
been relegated to archive status.  The Council of Olde, when they lived
among the people, lived upon this street.  Great plaques indicate the
names of the Council of Olde in the olden tongue, unreadable to you.
Talib Street continues to the south, and becomes Westgate Road to the
north.

nodes.s: This is Talib Street.
nodes.l:
...the long stretch of Talib Street.  This street is serene and silent;
only the sounds of wildlife disrupt the quiet here.  The plaques that
stand in front of the few houses here tell the story of how the Council
of Olde lived among the people; you know this from lore, not from being able
to read the plaques which are in the olden tongue.  Talib Street
continues both to the north and south.

nodes.s: This is Talib Street.
nodes.l:
...the House of Talib.  Given over to the archivist, the great House of
Talib stands to the west.  Guardsmen prevent any entrance to the great
house to preserve the memory of one of the great Council of Olde.  If
you could read the tongue of olde, you would be able to read the plaque
that stands before you regaling you of his deeds.  Talib Street
continues both north and south.

nodes.s: This is Talib Street.
nodes.l:
...the long stretch of Talib Street.  This street is serene and silent;
only the sounds of wildlife disrupt the quiet here.  The plaques that
stand in front of the few houses here tell the story of how the Council
of Olde lived among the people; you know this from lore, not from being able
to read the plaques which are in the olden tongue.  Talib Street
continues both to the north and south.

nodes.s: This is Talib Street.
nodes.l:
...the long stretch of Talib Street.  This street is quiet and barely
occupied.  Only a few houses line this street, and most of these have
been relegated to archive status.  The Council of Olde, when they lived
among the people, lived upon this street.  Great plaques indicate the
names of the Council of Olde in the olden tongue, unreadable to you.
Talib Street continues to the south, and becomes Westgate Road to the
north.

nodes.s: You are walking down Magus Way.
nodes.l:
...the great glowing streets of Magus Way.  The magic emanating from the Wizards Spire seeps deep into the road here, causing it to glow with a force not seen elsewhere in the city.  You can see the spire off in the
distance to the east.  Magus Way continues to the south, where the great
path to the spire can seen in the distance; to the north, Magus Way
becomes Westgate Road.

nodes.s: You are walking down Magus Way.
nodes.l:
...the great glowing streets of Magus Way.  The magic emanating from the Wizards Spire seeps deep into the road here, causing it to glow with a force not seen elsewhere in the city.  You can see the spire off in the
distance to the east.  Magus Way continues to the south.  You can see
the great path to the spire to the south leading east.  Magus Way
continues northwards as well.

nodes.s: You stand before the Wizard's Spire.
nodes.l:
...the Great Path of the Spire.  A great, glowing, golden road leads
east from here to the Wizards Spire, a place of great power.  It is here
that many of the workers of Force learn the secrets of that sphere.  The
great glowing street of Magus Way continues both northward and
southward.

nodes.s: You are walking down Magus Way.
nodes.l:
...the great glowing streets of Magus Way.  The magic emanating from the
Wizards Spire seeps deep into the road here, causing it to glitter like
a thousand lightning bugs in the distance.  The spire of the wizards is
off to the east, with a path leading eastwards starting a bit north from
here.  Magus Way continues to the south as well.

nodes.s: You are walking down Magus Way.
nodes.l:
...the great glowing streets of Magus Way.  The magic emanating from the
Wizards Spire seeps deep into the road here, causing a glitter that is
captivating.  The spire of the wizards can be seen in the distance, in a
northeastern direction.  There is no direct path to the spire here,
you would have to go north to find the path that leads to the tower.  Magus
Way becomes Western Avenue to the south.

nodes.s: You stroll down Westgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the Great Western Gate in the distance.  Westgate Road leads from the
Western Imperial Gate to the rest of the city.  Westgate road runs west
until it reaches the great gates of the city.  To the east, Westgate
meets with Magus Way.

nodes.s: You stroll down Westgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the Great Western Gate in the distance.  Westgate Road gets its name
from the fact that it starts at the Western Imperial Gate - this can be
seen in the distance to the west.  Westgate Road also continues
eastwards to the city.

nodes.s: You stand before the Western Imperial Gate.
nodes.l:
...the Great Western Imperial Gate.  Guards are stationed before this
gate to prevent both exit and egress.  Westgate Road leads into the city
eastward.

nodes.s: This is where Western Avenue meets Talib Street.
nodes.l:
...the long stretch of Talib Street which leads eastward.  Talib Street,
which was once called Back Alley, had its name changed to honor the
great Council of Olde.  Western Avenue runs east towards the Imperial
Square, and also runs to the west.

nodes.s: You walk down Western Avenue.
nodes.l:
...one of the many glowing roads of Imperial City.  Western Avenue meets
with Talib Street if you go eastwards; Western Avenue stretches to the
west as well.

nodes.s: You walk down Western Avenue.
nodes.l:
...one of the many glowing roads of Imperial City.  Western Avenue meets
the great glowing streets of Magus Way westward of here; Western Avenue
stretches to the east as well.

nodes.s: Western Avenue and Magus Way meet here.
nodes.l:
...the intersection of Magus Way and Western Avenue.  A great contrast
is seen between these two streets - Western Avenue, made from the
same glitterglow as the rest of the city, and Magus Way, which has
absorbed much of the magic from the Wizards Spire, making it glow with a strength unseen in the rest of the city.  Magus Avenue stretches
northward from here, while Western Avenue stretches both east and west
from here.

nodes.s: You are walking down Western Avenue.
nodes.l:
...the expanse of Western Avenue.  Western Avenue here is much like many of the other streets of this great city.  Made of glitterglow, so that
all may see in even the darkest of nights, Western Avenue leads many a
traveler eastward to great Imperial Square.  Western Avenue meets Magus
way to the east, and turns into Warriors Way to the west.

nodes.s: Western Avenue and Warriors Way meet here.
nodes.l:
...the corner of Western Avenue and Warriors Way.  There is nothing
special about this area, aside from the glitterglow road that the rest
of the city sports.  Western Avenue runs east from here, while Warriors
Way runs south from here.

nodes.s: You stride down Warriors Way.
nodes.l:
...the great engraved streets of Warriors Way.  The street, which is
made of the same glitterglow that is so abundant in this city.  In
addition to its glow, this street has many carvings set into it.
These engravings show many battle scenes of many different eras.
Warriors Way runs both north and south here.

nodes.s: You stride down Warriors Way.
nodes.l:
...the great engraved streets of Warriors Way.  The street is
made of the same glitterglow that is so abundant in this city.  In
addition to its glow, this street has many carvings set into it.
These engravings show many battle scenes of many different eras.
Warriors Way runs both north and south here.

nodes.s: You stride down Warriors Way.
nodes.l:
...the great engraved streets of Warriors Way.  The street is
made of the same glitterglow that is so abundant in this city.  In
addition to its glow, this street has many carvings set into it.
These engravings show many battle scenes of many different eras.
Warriors Way runs both north and south here.

nodes.s: Warriors Way and Tenten Place meet here.
nodes.l:
...one of the many intersections of this great city.  Here, the great
engraved streets of Warriors Way meet with Tenten Place.  Eastwards
along Tenten Place you see the great fortress building which houses
the Warriors Guild.  Warriors Way runs north and south.

nodes.s: You carefully walk down Tenten Place.
nodes.l:
...the impressive Tenten Place.  Along the edges of this street are
guardsmen, and guardsmen in training.  It is the duty of the warriors guiild apprentices
to guard this street, more to show their
discipline, rather than out of need.  Tenten Place leads to the Warriors
Guild to the east, and runs into Warriors Way to the west.

nodes.s: You stand before the Warriors Guild.
nodes.l:
...the great fortress of warriors.  A huge building with a portcullis
and inner wall, the Warriors Guild is one of the best protected areas of
Imperial City, second only to the Imperial Castle.  Many young people
can be seen training here at any time, day or night.  The chamberlain
gives you a steely look as you approach the gates to the guild.  Tenten
Place continues to the east and west.

nodes.s: You stand before Tenten Arena.
nodes.l:
...the great steel gates of Tenten Arena.  Housed right near the
Warriors Guild, it is here that many of the warriors spend their time.
You may enter the arena, which lies south of here, or you may continue
along Tenten Avenue eastwards or westwards.

nodes.s: You have reached the end of Tenten Place.
nodes.l:
...the great memorial.  A wall has been erected at the end of Tenten
Avenue.  It has been engraved with the names of some of the greatest
heroes of Corinthia; many of these heroes have come from Imperial City itself.
Tenten Avenue continues to the west from here.

nodes.s: You are in the Guild of Warriors.
nodes.l:
...many warriors in training.  The Guild of Warriors is where many of
the combative arms and skills are taught.  Suits of armor and weapons of
all types can be seen on the walls of this place.  Great tapestries
detailing various combats of old are hanging on the wall.

nodes.s: You are in the Guild of Warriors.
nodes.l:
...many warriors in training.  The Guild of Warriors is where many of
the combative arms and skills are taught.  Many great wall hangings
detail some of the great wars that have taken place in the Lands.  Great
statues of old heroes stand in this room.

nodes.s: You are in the Guild of Warriors.
nodes.l:
...many warriors in training.  The Guild of Warriors is where many of
the combative arms and skills are taught.  Great constructs are seen in
this room moving around haphazardly; warriors in this room are learning
to dodge these constructs.  This room is augmented by a showcase of
masterfully made weapons.

nodes.s: You are in the Guild of Warriors.
nodes.l:
...many warriors in training.  The Guild of Warriors is where many of
the combative arms and skills are taught.  An instructor of arms stands
in the middle of several young warriors; he is instructing them on the
many weapons that exist in the Land and their differences.  Many
warriors in this room spar with one another in a ring.

nodes.s: You are in the Guild of Warriors.
nodes.l:
...the great entrance room of the Guild of Warriors.  Many weapons hang
from the ceiling while suits of armor stand in the corners of this room.
Pedestals are found in this room, they hold busts of great heroes of the
land.  A great tapestry also hangs from the ceiling with the visages of
some of the Council of Olde.

nodes.s: You are in the Guild of Warriors.
nodes.l:
...many warriors in training.  The Guild of Warriors is where many of
the combative arms and skills are taught.  A dwarven lieutenant inspects
many warriors in different forms of armor here; he corrects them in
their use and wear of it.

nodes.s: You are in Tenten Arena.
nodes.l:
...the great arena of Tenten.  An armsmaster stands beside a great brass
gong; it is he that oversees the combat against the enemies that he
summons.  He looks cold and hard at you as he assesses your skill.  He
is ruthless in his ways as he prepares to send to you your next
opponents.

nodes.s: You stride down Warriors Way.
nodes.l:
...the great engraved streets of Warriors Way.  The street is
made of the same glitterglow that is so abundant in this city.  In
addition to its glow, this street has many carvings set into it.
These engravings show many battle scenes of many different eras.
Warriors Way runs both north and south here.

nodes.s: You stride down Warriors Way.
nodes.l:
...the great engraved streets of Warriors Way.  The street is
made of the same glitterglow that is so abundant in this city.  In
addition to its glow, this street has many carvings set into it.
These engravings show many battle scenes of many different eras.
Warriors Way runs both north and south here.

nodes.s: You stride down Warriors Way.
nodes.l:
...the great engraved streets of Warriors Way.  The street is
made of the same glitterglow that is so abundant in this city.  In
addition to its glow, this street has many carvings set into it.
These engravings show many battle scenes of many different eras.
Warriors Way runs both north and south here.

nodes.s: Warriors Way and Warren Street meet here.
nodes.l:
...the corner of Warriors Way and Warren Street.  Warren Street is a
large expanse of woods.  There are huge manors that line Warren Street,
but they are unapproachable because of the many guards that protect
these houses.  Warriors Way leads north from here, and Warren Street
continues east.

nodes.s: You are walking down Warren Street.
nodes.l:
...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this street, they are far apart, though, and it is difficult to discern
where the lands of one manor start, and where one ends.  Warren Street
continues east and west.

nodes.s: You are walking down Warren Street.
nodes.l:
...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this street; they are far apart.  It is difficult to discern
where the lands of one manor start, and where one ends.  Warren Street
continues east and west.

nodes.s: You are walking down Warren Street.
nodes.l:
...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this street; they are far apart, and it is difficult to discern
where the lands of one manor start, and where one ends.  Warren Street

...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this street; they are far apart, and it is difficult to discern
where the lands of one manor start, and where one ends.  Warren Street

...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this street; they are far apart, and it is difficult to discern
where the lands of one manor start, and where one ends.  Warren Street

nodes.l:
...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this street; they are far apart, and it is difficult to discern

nodes.l:
...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this street; they are far apart, and it is difficult to discern
where the lands of one manor start, and where one ends.  Warren Street

nodes.s: You are walking down Warren Street.
nodes.l:
...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this stree;, they are far apart, and it is difficult to discern
where the lands of one manor start, and where one ends.  Warren Street
continues east and west.

nodes.s: You are walking down Warren Street.
nodes.l:
...the great expanse of Warren Street.  There are a few manors that line
this street; they are far apart, and it is difficult to discern
where the lands of one manor start, and where one ends.  Warren Street

nodes.s: You are walking down Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...one of the main roads of Imperial City.  North of here, Short
Street meets with Northern Avenue.  South, in the distance, Northern
Avenue meets Eastern Road.  The glitterglow of this street is the same
that is found in most of this city.

nodes.s: You are walking down Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...one of the main roads of Imperial City.  North, in the distance,
Short Street meets with Northern Avenue.  Southward you can see that
Northern Avenue meets Eastern Road.  The glitterglow of this street is
the same that is found in most of this city.

nodes.s: You are at Northern Avenue and Eastgate Road.
nodes.l:
...one of the many intersections of Imperial City.  Northern Avenue runs
north and south from here, while Eastern Road runs east from here.

nodes.s: You strut down Eastgate Road.
nodes.l:
...Eastgate Road in all of its glory.  This long stretch of road shows
the beauty of Imperial City, and the Lands of Corinthia at large.  Trees
and foliage abound along this road, while small huts and houses can be
seen peeking through this miniature forest.  Eastgate Road continues far
to the east.  To the west, this road meets with Northern Avenue.

nodes.s: You strut down Eastgate Road.
nodes.l:
...Eastgate Road in all of its glory.  This long stretch of road shows
the beauty of Imperial City, and the Lands of Corinthia at large.
Trees and foliage abound along this road, while small huts and houses
can be seen peeking through this miniature forest.  Eastgate Road
continues to the east and west from here.

nodes.s: You strut down Eastgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the glory of Eastgate Road.  While this long stretch of road shows
the beauty that can be achieved when nature and the works of man meet,
the splendor of this road is augmented by the glitterglow that lines
this, and every other, street.  The steady placid glow of Eastgate Road
allows you to see the stretch of road that is both east and west of you.

nodes.s: Pleasant Place and Eastgate Road meet here.
nodes.l:
...the Fountain of Beauty.  Centered in this intersection where Eastgate
Road and Pleasant Way meet is a large crystal structure of two angels
bearing a water jug to several destitute people below them.  This huge
fountain glistens in the glitterglow of the streets.  Flowers abound
here, and you cannot help but pause a moment to admire the beauty of
the fountain.

nodes.s: You strut down Eastgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the glory of Eastgate Road.  While this long stretch of road shows
the beauty that can be achieved when nature and the works of man meet,
the splendor of this road is augmented by the glitterglow that lines
this, and every other, street.  The steady placid glow of Eastgate Road
allows you to see the stretch of road that is both east and west of you.

nodes.l:
...the glory of Eastgate Road.  While this long stretch of road shows
the beauty that can be achieved when nature and the works of man meet,
the splendor of this road is augmented by the glitterglow that lines
this, and every other, street.  The steady placid glow of Eastgate Road

nodes.l:
...the glory of Eastgate Road.  While this long stretch of road shows
the beauty that can be achieved when nature and the works of man meet,
the splendor of this road is augmented by the glitterglow that lines
this, and every other, street.  The steady placid glow of Eastgate Road
allows you to see the stretch of road that is both east and west of you.

nodes.s: You strut down Eastgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the glory of Eastgate Road.  While this long stretch of road shows
the beauty that can be achieved when nature and the works of man meet,
the splendor of this road is augmented by the glitterglow that lines
this, and every other, street.  The steady placid glow of Eastgate Road
allows you to see the stretch of road that is both east and west of you.

nodes.s: You strut down Eastgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the glory of Eastgate Road.  While this long stretch of road shows
the beauty that can be achieved when nature and the works of man meet,
the splendor of this road is augmented by the glitterglow that lines
this, and every other, street.  The steady placid glow of Eastgate Road
allows you to see the stretch of road that is both east and west of you.

nodes.s: You strut down Eastgate Road.
nodes.l:
...the glory of Eastgate Road.  While this long stretch of road shows
the beauty that can be achieved when nature and the works of man meet,
the splendor of this road is augmented by the glitterglow that lines
this, and every other, street.  The steady placid glow of Eastgate Road
allows you to see the stretch of road that is both east and west of you.

nodes.s: You stand before the Eastern Imperial Gate.
nodes.l:
...one of the majestic Imperial Gates.  The Imperial Guards that stand
both inside and outside this gate serve as warnings of the dangers
that lie outside of Imperial City, as well as the dangers that could
come from within.  Entrance from the east is forbidden by the guards
outside, while the guards within prevent your exit from this gate.

nodes.s: You are walking down Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...one of the main roads of Imperial City.  North of here, Northern
Avenue meets with Eastgate Road.  Northern Avenue continues far south of here, until it meets the Imperial Square.

nodes.s: You are walking down Northern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...one of the main roads of Imperial City.  Northern Avenue stretches
both north and south from here.

nodes.s: You are just outside the Imperial Square.
nodes.l:
...one of the main roads of Imperial City.  From this part of Northern
Avenue, you can clearly see the Imperial Square south of here; the
statue of Gaetor stands tall and majestically in the center of the
square.  Northern Avenue continues to the north from here.

nodes.s: You stroll down Pleasant Way.
nodes.l:
...a beautiful stretch of worked land.  The road here is not made of the
same glitterglow, but holds a magick of its own.  The light from the
great fountain north of here beams down Pleasant Way to light it far
further than you think it should.  The foliage here is well cared for
and trimmed to perfection.  Pleasant Way meets northernly Eastgate Road and continues southward.

nodes.s: You stroll down Pleasant Way.
nodes.l:
...a beautiful stretch of worked land.  The road here is not made of the
same glitterglow, but holds a magick of its own.  The light from the
great fountain north of here beams down Pleasant Way to light it far
further than you think it should.  The foliage here is well cared for
and trimmed to perfection.  Pleasant Way continues both north and south
from here.

nodes.s: You stroll down Pleasant Way.
nodes.l:
...a beautiful stretch of worked land.  The road here is not made of the
same glitterglow, but holds a magick of its own.  The light from the
great fountain north of here beams down Pleasant Way to light it far
further than you think it should.  The foliage here is well cared for
and trimmed to perfection.  Pleasant Way stretches north from here, and
meets with Wisdom Court to the south.

nodes.s: Pleasant Way meets Wisdom Court here.
nodes.l:
...a large park-like intersection.  This area is complete with benches
and tables on which you may play games of chance.  Wisdom Court runs
east of this area, while Pleasant Way stretches north of here.  Pleasant
Place wends south of this intersection, as well.

nodes.s: You stroll down Wisdom Court.
nodes.l:
...a decorated stretch of road.  The foliage here was allowed to grow
well above your heads, and then trimmed to resemble large arches.  This
being done for several centuries, along with the aid of some basic
magicks, permits the foliage to grow in this pattern.  The majesty of
this area is further augmented by the glitterglow roads, as well as by the
light that peeks in from above during the day and well-lit nights.
Wisdom Court stretches to the east, while to the west, Wisdom Court
meets with Pleasant Way and Pleasant Place.

nodes.s: You stroll down Wisdom Court.
nodes.l:
...a decorated stretch of road.  The foliage here was allowed to grow
well above your heads, and then trimmed to resemble large arches.  This
being done for several centuries, along with the aid of some basic
magicks, permits the foliage to grow in this pattern.  The majesty of
this area is further augmented by the glitterglow roads, as well as by the
light that peeks in from above during the day and well-lit nights.
Wisdom Court stretches to the east and west from here.

nodes.s: You stand before a hut.
nodes.l:
...a simple looking hut.  Although simple looking, this hut has the universal Healers Sign placed upon its door; the hut belongs to the local wise women.  The
area around the hut is well kept, and a pleasant smell drifts from the
huts direction.  You may approach this hut which lies to the south, or
continue along Wisdom Court which runs east and west from here.

nodes.s: You stroll down Wisdom Court.
nodes.l:
...a decorated stretch of road.  The foliage here was allowed to grow
well above your heads, and then trimmed to resemble large arches.  This
being done for several centuries, along with the aid of some basic
magicks, permits the foliage to grow in this pattern.  The majesty of
this area is further augmented by the glitterglow roads, as well as the
light that peeks in from above during the day and well-lit nights.
Wisdom Court stretches to the east and west from here.

nodes.s: You are standing before the Temple of Myiras.
nodes.l:
...the great temple of Myiras.  A great statue of Myiras, goddess of
life, healing and sacrifice, has been placed on either side of the great
brass doors of this grand building.  Guards stand ready at either side
of these great doors to welcome visitors, or to bar the way of those
who are not welcome.  Wisdom Court stretches west of here.

nodes.s: You are in the Temple of Myiras.
nodes.l: ...the great waiting chamber of the temple of Myiras.  A priestessstands in this room; she is prepared to perform several services of thechurch as needed.  The antechamber lies to the west, but several guardsprevent all except the priests to enter this area.  The exit back to Wisdom Court lies to the south.  A trap door leads to the great Catacombs of Death, for those that wish to pay services to those dearones that have departed.

nodes.s: You have entered the antechamber.
nodes.l:
...the great antechamber of the temple of Myiras.  This area has been
reserved for priests, and it is here that many of the priests pour over
the holy doctrines which give them the powers of their faith.  Many are
the secrets of Life that the priests can glean from this place.  Priests
in meditation are also found here.  While prepared specifically for the
priests of Myiras, you notice the frocks of several priesthoods within
this room.  To the north is the Inner Sanctum; the waiting room lies to
the east.

nodes.s: You have entered the Inner Sanctum.
nodes.l:
...the great Inner Sanctum of Myiras.  This area has been specially
prepared by the priests for the priests.  Holy symbols adorn the walls
of this place, and there are several personal-sized alters at which priests
pray.  It is in this room that many of the priests of Myiras gain the
wisdom to cast the spells of the Sphere of their Goddess.  While the
knowledge is gained in the antechamber, it is in this room that the
great power is gained.  The only exit from this powerful place is to the
south, which leads to the antechamber.

nodes.s: You are walking down Pleasant Place.
nodes.l:
...a desolate spot of Pleasant Place.  This area is adorned only by the
small trees and flower beds that have been planted here.  To the north,
Wisdom Court makes its connection to the east, while southward, a small
stretch of land connects this road to the Imperial Square.

nodes.s: You are at an intersection.
nodes.l:
...one of the many intersections of Imperial City.  A small stretch of
land to the west connects this road to the Imperial Square and you can see
the great statue of the square clearly.  The road that you are on
continues both north and south from here.

nodes.s: You are just outside the Imperial Square.
nodes.l:
...a well kept stretch of road.  This road leads from Imperial Square to
Pleasant Place.  Imperial Square sitting west of you, and Pleasant Place
sitting east of you.

nodes.s: You have entered the Wise Woman's Hut.
nodes.l:
...a small one-room hut.  A fireplace keeps this room warm, and a
large cauldron continuously boils water.  The Wise Women looks up
from the herbs and plants that she was curing and looks at you with
large knowing eyes.  You see that she has a small aperture on the east
wall that leads to her garden.  She smiles at you as she continues what
she is doing.

nodes.s: You are in the Wise Woman's garden.
nodes.l:
...a small well-kept garden.  This garden has many different spices and
plants growing side by side, apparently without the interference you
would expect several differing plants to create when growing together.
A powerful earthy smell comes from the garden.  It is easy to see that
the wise woman has several skills, only one of which is the ability to
keep a garden alive.  A small aperture in her hut, which lies to the
west, permits re-entry.

nodes.s: You are walking down Pleasant Place.
nodes.l:
...the long stretch of Pleasant Place.  This road, which has been
decorated by some of the rarest flowers and trees, is reminiscent of the beauty
that can be found within the Realms of Corinthia.  Several sculptures of
various creatures (all accompanied by sculptures of heroes that could
cause their doom) remind you of the dangers within the Realms as well.
Pleasant Place stretches north and south from here.

nodes.s: You are walking down Pleasant Place.
nodes.l:
...the long stretch of Pleasant Place.  This road, which has been
decorated by some of the rarest flowers and trees, is reminiscent of the beauty
that can be found within the Realms of Corinthia.  Several sculptures of
various creatures (all accompanied by sculptures of heroes that could
cause their doom) remind you of the dangers within the Realms as well.
Pleasant Place stretches north and south from here.

nodes.l:

nodes.s: You are walking down Pleasant Place.
nodes.l:
...the long stretch of Pleasant Place.  This road, which has been
decorated by some of the rarest flowers and trees, is reminiscent of the beauty
that can be found within the Realms of Corinthia.  Several sculptures of
various creatures (all accompanied by sculptures of heroes that could
cause their doom) remind you of the dangers within the Realms as well.
Pleasant Place stretches north and south from here.  Southward, though,
Pleasant Place reaches into Smith Way.

nodes.s: Pleasant Place and Smith Way meet here.
nodes.l:
...iron bordered streets.  The streets of Smith Way have been maintained
by the dwarven smiths of the Imperial City for as long as anyone can
remember.  The iron borders, placed so long ago, are maintained and shined by the apprentice smiths of the dwarven smith whose shop is far east of here.  Pleasant Place intersects with Smith Way here, and stretches north from here.  Smith Way continues both east and west from this intersecting street.

nodes.s: You stride down Smith Way.
nodes.l:
...iron bordered streets.  The streets of Smith Way have been maintained
by the dwarven smiths of the Imperial City for as long as anyone can
remember.  The iron borders, placed so long ago, are
maintained and shined by the apprentice smiths of the
dwarven smith whose shop is far east of here.  Smith Way stretches to
the east and west.

nodes.s: You stride down Smith Way.
nodes.l:
...iron bordered streets.  The streets of Smith Way have been maintained
by the dwarven smiths of the Imperial City for as long as anyone can
remember.  The iron borders, placed so long ago, are
maintained and shined by the apprentice smiths of the
dwarven smith whose shop is far east of here.  Smith Way stretches to
the east and west.

nodes.s: You stand outside the Blacksmith's Shop.
nodes.l:
...the great structure of the dwarven smithy.  The doors of this house
have been reinforced with great iron bands, and a complex lock adorns
this door as well.  The Smithy, itself, is held within this structure,
and lies deep within this house.  Smoke escapes from the chimney; there
is always someone in the smithy, it seems.  Smith Way continues to the
west from this great structure which is at the eastern end of the road.

nodes.s: You are inside the Blacksmith's Shop.
nodes.l:
...the many wares of the blacksmiths here.  Many works of iron, steel,
and other metals adorn the walls, floor, and ceiling of this large room.
Several dwarves hurry busily about, some of them watch you as you gaze
at several of their works.

nodes.s: You have entered the Smithy.
nodes.l:
...the great smiths workshop.  Hammers strike anvils noisily here, as
several dwarves labor at many different pieces of work simultaneously.
The fire is stoked by several apprentices under the watchful eye of a
master smith.

nodes.s: You are in the Blacksmith's Shop.
nodes.l:
...the many wares of the blacksmiths here.  Many works of iron, steel,
and other metals adorn the walls, floor, and ceiling of this large room.
Several dwarves hurry busily about, some of them watch you as you gaze

nodes.l:
...the great smiths workshop.  Hammers strike anvils noisily here, as
several dwarves work on many different pieces of work simultaneously.
The fire is stoked by several apprentices under the watchful eye of a
master smith.

nodes.l:
...iron bordered streets.  The streets of Smith Way have been maintained
by the dwarven smiths of the Imperial City for as long as anyone can
remember.  The iron borders, placed so long ago, are maintained and shined by the apprentice smiths of the dwarven smith whose shop is far east of here.  Smith Way stretches to the east and west.

nodes.l:
...iron bordered streets.  The streets of Smith Way have been maintained
by the dwarven smiths of the Imperial City for as long as anyone can

nodes.l:
...iron bordered streets.  The streets of Smith Way have been maintained
by the dwarven smiths of the Imperial City for as long as anyone can
remember.  The iron borders, placed so long ago, are maintained and shined by the apprentice smiths of the dwarven smith whose shop is far east of here.  Smith Way stretches to the east and west.

nodes.s: You walk down Southern Avenue.
nodes.l:
...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue reaches from the Imperial
Square, which lies directly north of here, to the Southern Gate, which
lies far south of here.  The glitterglow of Southern Avenue is worn,
though no less effective.  The southern quarter of the Imperial City is
barren of houses and huts, and holds only the fauna of the local
land.

nodes.s: You walk down Southern Avenue.
nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: You walk down Southern Avenue.
nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: You walk down Southern Avenue.
nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: You walk down Southern Avenue.
nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: You are at a very busy intersection.
nodes.l:
...one of the great intersections of Imperial City.  This particular
intersection is one of most traveled areas of Imperial City due to its
location.  The iron bound streets of Smith Way wend east of here, wide
Warren Street is west, while Southern Avenue continues both north and
south from here.

nodes.s: You walk down Southern Avenue.
nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: You walk down Southern Avenue.
nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: Southern Avenue and Stable Pass meet here.
nodes.l:
...one of many intersections of Imperial City.  The street to the west
seems to have a layer of soot on it, though it appears to be well
traveled despite the soot.  A large smoke damaged building lies to the
west of here, as well.  Southern Avenue stretches both north and south
from here.

nodes.s: You are on Stable Pass.
nodes.l:
...a soot covered road.  Stable Pass has been the recent victim of a
fire which burned down the great stables of Imperial City.  You can see
the building that once housed the finest horses of the land to the west.
Stable Pass meets with Southern Avenue to the east.

nodes.s: You stand in front of a burnt, boarded building.
nodes.l:
...a soot covered, fire damaged building.  This building used to house
the Imperial Stable, but is now no more than a damaged building which has
been boarded up.  Several people pass this building and shake their
heads in disgust, anger, or shame.  The great Imperial Council has
decided against rebuilding the stable at this time, much to the
disappointment of its citizens.  In time, they promise, the great
stables will be restored.

nodes.s: You have reached the end of Stable Pass.
nodes.l:
...a soot covered road.  Stable Pass has been the recent victim of a
fire which burned down the great stables of Imperial City.  You can see
the building that once housed the finest horses of the land to the east.
Stable Pass continues only to the east from here.

nodes.s: The stables are closed.
nodes.l: nan

nodes.s: You are in a newly formed arena.
nodes.l: ...a newly created arena.  This large room has been converted by to anarena by the Warrior's guild under the careful eye of the guildmaster.A large polished gong glitters in the torchlight, its magical abilitiesevident to even the initiates.  One ring of this gong will summon acombantant to test your skills against.  By decree of the ImperialCouncil, only citizens of the realm may enter here.

nodes.s: The stables are closed.

nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: Destron Road meets with Southern Avenue here.
nodes.l:
...one of the many, many intersections of the Imperial City.  Destron
Road reaches east of here, and you can see several shops line this
street.  Southern Avenue reaches to the north and south of this
intersection.

nodes.s: You are on the main pass to Imperial City.
nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: You are on the main pass to Imperial City.
nodes.l: ...a well traveled road.  Southern Avenue is the only of the "directional road" that stretches from its corresponding gate to the Imperial Square.  As such, it is the most traveled road of Imperial City.  Southern Avenue stretches north and south of here.

nodes.s: You are at the Southern Imperial Gates.
nodes.l:
...the Southern Imperial Gates.  The most used of the gates, these gates
are continuously open and monitored by the Imperial Guard Corp.  Signs warn of the many hazards that can be found within South City Forest, and advise the untrained and ill-prepared to remain at home.  Southern Avenue leads north from here.  South City Forest lies outside the gate to the south.

nodes.s: You are walking down Destron Road.
nodes.l:
...an extremely busy street.  Destron Road has several shops connected
to it, and it is easy to see that these shops are frequented often.
While Destron Road continues far in the eastern direction, it meets with
Southern Avenue to the west.

nodes.s: You stand before the Bowyer's Shop.
nodes.l:
...a large wooden house.  This house has a sign that hangs above the
door indicating that it is the home of the local bowyer.  The bowyer is
skilled in making bows and arrows of all types.  The entrance to his
house and shop is to the north; Destron Road reaches both east and west
of here.

nodes.s: You are walking down Destron Road.
nodes.l:
...an extremely busy street.  Destron Road has several shops connected
to it, and it is easy to see that these shops are frequented often.
Destron Avenue reaches to the east and west.

nodes.s: You are outside the Weaponsmithy.
nodes.l:
...a well made stone structure.  This structure has a sign that hangs on
chains well above the door.  The symbol of this sign reveals this place
to be a weaponsmithy, a person who specializes in the creation of
weapons.  The entrance to the weaponsmithy lies to the south, while
Destron Avenue continues to the east and west.

nodes.s: You are on Destron Road.
nodes.l:
...an extremely busy street.  Destron Road has several shops connected
to it, and it is easy to see that these shops are frequented often.
Destron Avenue reaches to the east and west.

nodes.s: You stand outside the Woodcarver's Hut.
nodes.l:
...a great wooden house.  Several staffs are bolted into the ground
here; this house is owned by the great woodcarver.  The entrance to his
house and shop is to the north.  Destron Road reaches east and west,
though you can see that the road comes to a quick end westward.

nodes.s: You have reached the end of Destron Road.
nodes.l:
...the end of Destron Road.  A heavy cover of trees are found at the end
of this road; they have been preserved so that the carver, bowyer, and
weaponsmith all have a supply of raw materials to work from.  Great
magicks help replenish the woods of this area so that the woods grow
almost as fast as they are used.  Destron Road stretches west of here.

nodes.s: You are in the fletching room.
nodes.l:
...the bowyer's fletching room.  In this room, the bowyer and his
workers make the arrows that are sold.  They sit at many tables
whittling away at the shafts, while several of them run back and forth
with arrow heads which are being fitted to the shaft.

nodes.s: You have entered the Bowyer's Shop.
nodes.l:
...the bowyer's shop.  Bows are seen leaning against the far wall, and
several bundles of arrows are in barrels sitting to either side of the
bows.  Quarrels are kept in a separate area near the bows; several parts
can also be seen in display - unstrung bows, bow strings, unfletched
arrows - all of these are, apparently, for sale.  Eastward of here there
lies an indoor archery field, while westward lies his fletching room.

nodes.s: You are in a large, indoor archery field.
nodes.l:
...a large, indoor archery field.  Several people are seen here
practicing their skill at bowmanship under the watchful eye of a
bowmaster.  Arrow laden targets can be seen in the distance, flags which
indicate hits and misses can seen in the background as well.

nodes.s: You have entered the Woodcarver's home.
nodes.l:
...the woodcarver's home.  The main room of the woodcarver has been
remade into a makeshift shop and you see several staffs lying
on the floor or leaning on the wall.  The carver's son is sitting at the
carving table creating more staffs for the carver.

nodes.s: You have entered the Weaponsmithy's shop.
nodes.l:
...the weaponsmithy.  The weaponsmith has several cases in which to show
his weapons.  The back of this structure houses a mini-forge and
temperer.  The lord of this house stands ready to sell any of his wares
to you.

nodes.s: You stand outside the Imperial Training Hall.
nodes.l:
...the splendor of the Imperial Square.  Centered in the square is a
great statue of Gaetor, Grand Councilor of The Rose.  Several large
structures are here in the Imperial Square; they are in the corners of
the square proper.  The Imperial Training Hall is west of you.

nodes.s: You are in the Imperial Square.
nodes.l:
...the splendor of the Imperial Square.  Centered in the square is a
great statue of Gaetor, Grand Councilor of The Rose.  Several large
structures are here in the Imperial Square; they are in the corners of
the square proper.  Northern Avenue is north of you.

nodes.s: You stand outside the Coat of Arms Tavern.
nodes.l:
...the splendor of the Imperial Square.  Centered in the square is a
great statue of Gaetor, Grand Councilor of The Rose.  Several large
structures are here in the Imperial Square; they are in the corners of
the square proper.  The Coat of Arms Tavern is east of you.

nodes.s: You stand outside the Imperial Training Hall.
nodes.l:
...the splendor of the Imperial Square.  Centered in the square is a
great statue of Gaetor, Grand Councilor of The Rose.  Several large
structures are here in the Imperial Square; they are in the corners of
the square proper.  The Imperial Training Hall is north of you.

nodes.s: You are in the Imperial Square.
nodes.l:
...the splendor of the Imperial Square.  Centered in the square is a
great statue of Gaetor, Grand Councilor of The Rose.  Several large
structures are here in the Imperial Square; they are in the corners of
the square proper.

nodes.s: You are at the Imperial Statue.
nodes.l:
...the great statue of Gaetor, Grand Councilor of The Rose.  This statue
stands a full thirty feet tall, and is made of polished brass.  The
statue is made in such a way so that each of the cardinal points has a
full facing of the Grand Councilor.  Gaetor stands with arms outstretched, welcoming all those that walk the streets of the Imperial
City.

nodes.s: You are in the Imperial Square.
nodes.l:
...the splendor of the Imperial Square.  Centered in the square is a

traveled often, but well kept.  The glitterglow of this road is strong

nodes.s: You are at the Imperial Statue.
nodes.l:
...the great statue of Gaetor, Grand Councilor of The Rose.  This statue
stands a full thirty feet tall, and is made of polished brass.  The
statue is made in such a way so that each of the cardinal points has a
full facing of the Grand Councilor.  Gaetor stands with arms
outstretched, welcoming all those that walk the streets of the Imperial
City.

nodes.s: You are at the Imperial Statue.
nodes.l:
...a great statue.  This statue is over thirty feet tall, and made
entirely of polished brass.  The statue shows the front of Gaetor, The
Grand Councilor of The Rose; it is made in such a way that the statue
shows the visage of Gaetor with hands outstretched in the four cardinal
directions.  This causes the statue to have a column-type look to it,
but this does not distract from its impressiveness.  Around you is the
Imperial Square, the heart of this city.  Several large structures are
seen in the corners of the square, and the square is teeming with
villagers at all times.
nodes.quest_text: embrace statue ... You embrace the statue warmly. ... %s is hugging the statue of Gaetor. ... $

nodes.s: You are deep within the Wizard's Spire.
nodes.l:
...a large study hall.  The walls of this room are filled with shelves
of books from ceiling to floor.  Many people sit at desks pouring over
many musty tomes attempting to glean knowledge from these tomes.  An
elderly gentleman slowly levitates books to and fro; he is obviously
the caretaker of this area.

nodes.s: You have entered the Wizard's Spire.
nodes.l:
...the inner chamber of the great Wizards Spire.  This area has a very
powerful feel to it, and great spiraling staircases lead both north and
south from this place.  Although there are no other people here, you
cannot shake the uncanny feeling that you are being watched.

nodes.s: You are deep within the Wizard's Spire.
nodes.l:
...a large laboratory.  Beakers, vials, and tomes are found all over the
many tables of this room.  Several old mages instruct others on the use
of their magicks, and it is easy to see that the instructions are,
indeed, the labors of the Workers of Force.  With enough practice and
knowledge you too can become a worker of the Sphere of Force.

nodes.s: You are within the Imperial Training Center.
nodes.l: ...the Imperial City Adventurer's Guild.  Several people mill about examining their goods and weapons that they have purchased from the guild's quartermaster.  You notice several guildsman giving combat instructions to those standing outside Tasque Arena, which is to the north.  A large sign hangs from the trumpet of the large Herald's statue which indicates that the famous Quest Corridors lie below.  Stairs lead up to a second tier; the way is blocked by several Imperial Guards.  Above you, on the higher tier, the guildmaster looks on.

nodes.s: You step into the Coat of Arms Tavern.
nodes.l:
...a large tavern.  Many round tables are spread throughout this room,
and the bar has several seats by it.  Patrons wander to and fro in the
tavern, and you see several serving girls wending their way through the
patrons.  There are many conversations going on in this room.  The scent
of cooking escapes from the kitchen, and the pungent smell of ale cuts
through the air.

nodes.s: You are shopping in the Imperial Stores.
nodes.l:
Welcome to Imperial Sundries and Equipment.  The store has recently
finished costly renovations and patrons stream about the store in 
delight of its new facelift.  Along one wall you see several lanterns and
lamps of varying sizes and shapes hanging from hooks and under them,
in much quantity, you see many torches lying in small piles against the
wall.  Attached to the western wall are many shelves.  The shelves 
contain a variety of preserved and non-preserved food and water rations.
The highlight of the shop, the ambrosia wafer, sits inside a showcase
under the shelving.

nodes.s: You quietly enter the Imperial Study Hall.
nodes.l:
...the Imperial Study Hall.  You shuffle quietly into the Imperial 
Study Hall holding down your possessions so as not to make noise.
Rows upon rows of books line the walls and columns upon columns of book
cases stand (bolted to the ground so you cannot accidently push them
over like dominos) line the expanse of the study hall.  In one corner
of the library are several large oak tables occupied by students
who look about various tomes scribbling notes furiously. A spiral 
staircase leads upwards but is cordoned off with a very firm:
"Elder's Only".
nodes.quest_text: study ... You pour over an ancient tome of Old Carinthia. ... %s quietly studies an ancient tome. ... 0$

nodes.s: You stand outside the Imperial Castle.
nodes.l:
...the Imperial Castle.  This grand structure lies directly north of
you, but is inaccessible to you.  A great expanse of emptiness surrounds
the castle. The expanse appears to be several hundred feet in width.  It
would take great power, indeed, to cross this great divide.

nodes.s: You are just outside Imperial City.
nodes.l:
...that you are standing just outside the great gates of Imperial City.  A
large clearing has been made here so that those waiting to enter have a
place to rest their weary selves.  Guards posted outside attempt to keep
order amongst the crowd.  There are two dirt paths leading southwards
into South City Forest, one heading slightly east, the other slightly
west.

nodes.s: You are on a forest path.
nodes.l:
...a wide forest path.  This path is well traveled by travelers and
explorers alike.  Trees and bushes line the path to either side of you,
though there is no growth on the path itself.  This path leads towards
Imperial City in the northeastern direction, while it leads deeper
into the forest in the southwestern direction.

nodes.s: You are on a forest path.
nodes.l:
...a wide forest path.  This path appears to be welltraveled.  Trees
and bushes line this path to either side of you.  This path continues
to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You are on a forest path.
nodes.l:
...a clearing in the forest.  This small clearing looks like it is often
used as a campsite for the weary.  A small firepit is seen near a small
structure designed to assist campers to keep dry during some of the
nightly rains.  There are paths leading from this clearing in the
northeast, southeast, and westerly directions.

nodes.s: You are in the forest.
nodes.l:
...a small path in the forest.  This path appears to have had some
passage in the past, but the moss on the ground shows it path is
traveled lightly as of late.  This path may be followed northwesterly
or southeasterly.

nodes.s: You are in the forest.

nodes.s: You are in the forest.
nodes.l:
...that you stand outside a small, natural cave.  A small hill rises out
of the ground, separating and bending many of the trees that are here.
Roots stick out of the ground, and a tree has fallen across the entrance
of this cave, forcing you to climb over it to enter .  You may enter
the cave to the east, or follow the path to the west.

nodes.s: You are in a cave.
nodes.l:
...a small, dank cave.  Grime, slime, and moss cover the inside of this
cave.  Small mushrooms grow on the floor of this cave, and water drips
from the cave ceiling.  An old man sits silently upon a wooden stool in the middle of the room; his mood is one of frustration, loneliness and sorrow.  In front of the old man is a large bubbling cauldron which hangs from a sturdy iron framework.  Small bubbles lift from the surface of the cauldron as the fire below roars upon it.  The old man looks up at you questioningly as you make your way through the room.  The only exit from this cave is to the west.
nodes.quest_text: give brew ... You give the old man the hag's brew. ... %s administers brew to the old man. ... %$

nodes.l: ...a dirt path leading to a cave.  This section of the forest seems to have been stripped of trees long ago.  Weeds still overrun this area, though.  A small path that leads west to a cave can still be made out.  A small dark path leads eastward from here.

While the tracks in the dirt show that this cave is visited upon occasion, the filth of this cave shows that it is not lived in, nor used for any other purpose.  There is an exit from this cave to the east.

nodes.l: ...a small platform.  This platform leads to a small path which leads eastwards from here.  A large cave entrance is set into the hill which is to the west; the dank odor comes from it.

nodes.s: You are in a large, smelly cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  This cave is roughly circular, and has several small cul-de-sacs which lead from it.  Two small firepits are centered in this room.  One of these firepits is obviously used for a cooking fire; the many bones of several animals lie strewn about it.  Furs, trash, and other various items lie in several places of this cave.

This gravel-like substance helps your footing, though it wears on the feet quickly.  This loosely cobbled path continues south, while the path becomes more natural to the north.

nodes.s: You are in a forest clearing.
nodes.l: ...a loosely cobbled path.  This area is part of what has infamously been called "satyr pass".  Several stakes with various rotting body parts have been stuck into the ground along the path as a warning to those that would travel the area that the satyrs have claimed as their own.  A natural path leads southwest of here, while the loosely cobbled path continues east.

nodes.s: You are in the forest.
nodes.l: ...a winding path in the forest.  This path has been created by the many years of travel in the forest, and winds around trees and other natural obstacles that have been here long before any path.  Birds flitter in the trees overhead, and small rodents duck and hide at your passing.  You may continue northwest or southeast from here.

nodes.s: You are in a patch of wild growth.
nodes.l: ...a wildly overgrown area.  The area here is overgrown with trees, bushes, weeds, and roots.  There is a notable lack of animal life in this area; it is as if they have all been chased off, or killed.  You can escape this overgrowth by traveling to the north or to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are on a clear path.
nodes.l: ...a well made path.  This path has been cleared of trees, bushes and weeds.  The path, made of hardened clay, is very well maintained.  The path apparently ends in a sudden upcrop of forest wildgrowth to the northwest.  The path continues to the southeast.

nodes.s: You are on a clear path.
nodes.l: ...a well made path.  This path has been cleared of trees, bushes and weeds.  The path, made of hardened clay, is very well maintained.  This path continues to the northwest and to the east.

nodes.s: You are on a path.
nodes.l: ...a well made path.  This path has been forged in hardened clay.  You are quite surprised to note that this clay has been mixed with glitterglow.  While dim, the glow from this path is sufficient for you to travel on without danger of tripping over any obstacles.  The dimness, however, prevents this path from being seen from any appreciable distance.  This path continues northwards.  The path continues west as well, though the clay has not been mixed with glitterglow in that direction.

nodes.l: ...a small circular clearing.  This clearing is made of the same clay/glitterglow mixture as the path you just came from.  A small wooden wall has been erected to the north; it has a door set in it which is presently closed.  A path leads from here to the south.

nodes.l: ...a small clearing of Satyr Pass.  You can make out several huts hidden among the trees of the forest; these huts lie off the road, and are inaccessible to you.  Like the rest of Satyr Pass, this area has been lined with stakes with body parts attached.  Satyr Pass continues to the west and southeast.  Another forest path begins to the northeast.
