Huge bugs of various types flitter in and out of the outcroppings, and many rodents are heard scurrying along the ground.  You can barely make out what is left of the paths which lead to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are overlooking a mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a small plateau.  While standing on this plateau, you can see the majesty of the mountains to the north.  While untraversable, there is a path that leads through the mountains.  The hint of lush plant life hidden among the mountains can be seen from here, though you cannot judge the distance nor the size of that oasis-like area.  While the mountain pass leads northwards from here, another path leads from here southwardly.

This path continues to the southeast.  Weeds begin to cover this path completely to the northwest.

nodes.s: You are in a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...a large clearing in the woods.  This clearing still has evidence of the many large trees that grew here long ago.  A makeshift firepit can be seen, though there are no tents or other structures around.  Small animal bones are scattered along the ground here.  There is a small path which leads westward from here, while a much larger path leads southeasterly from here.  A small, overgrown path leads north from here.

nodes.s: You are on a wide path.
nodes.l: ...a large path in the woods.  This large path appears to be natural. No evidence of tree-chopping, bush-burning, or ground razing appears here.  Small patches of moss grow in many areas of this path which leads northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are standing at a crossroad.
nodes.l: ...a dark area of the forest.  The area in which you are traveling has many tall trees which block out much of the sunlight here.  The trees are huge and robust, with many branches on them.  The shadows seem to move as you walk in this area, and the air carries the faint sound of laughter which may or may not be imagined.  Paths lead from this area to the northwest, southwest, and to the southeast.

nodes.l: ...a stony clearing.  This clearing is covered in rocks and various stones.  You find it difficult to focus on anything except for the huge depression in the ground to the south.  It looks like a very large structure may have simply been uprooted from its foundation.  A very large wooded path leads from here to the north.

nodes.s: You are in the forest.
nodes.l: ...forest.  Trees grow all about you, with bushes and weeds jutting up from the ground where they are able.  Roots from the trees grow above the ground in some places, and moss covers several rocks are strewn haphazardly on the forest floor.  A large path is seen to the east, though you could work your way westward if you choose.

nodes.s: You are near a pond.
nodes.l: ...a small pond.  This small clearing of the forest has a pond of freshwater that is almost centered on this natural clearing.  Fish can be seen swimming in this pond without apparent direction or care.  A sense of peace and serenity overcome you as you stop to admire the beauty of this area.  You sigh as you contemplate whether you are going to leave this beauty by going northwest, south, or westward.

nodes.s: You are on an overgrown path.
nodes.l: ...a small overgrown path.  The path here, while fairly easy to travel, has the beginnings of overgrowth as weeds attempt to overcome the work that has been put into making a working path.  Tree roots are beginning to jut out of the ground as well, forcing you to keep an eye on your footing.  This path continues to the northwest and to the east.

nodes.l: ...a wildly overgrown area.  The area here is overgrown with trees, bushes, weeds, and roots.  There is a notable lack of animal life in this area, though; as if they have all been chased off or killed.  You may travel either to the northeast or to the southwest.

nodes.l: ...a dark cave.  This cave has vines that grow up from the ground and seem to cover every inch of the walls and ceiling of this cave.  A small firepit is in the center of this cave, and a small bed made of broken twigs and leaves is against the far wall.  A curtain of vines covers the entrance of this cave which is to the north; it is also the only exit.

This beaten path is riddled with various tracks, and continues to the northwest and to the east.

nodes.s: You are standing outside a village.
nodes.l: ...a large cave entrance. A large hill stands before you in the northern direction.  A large cave mouth in the hill faces you.  You see a large wooden structure designed to prevent entry into the cave mouth. It has obviously been set from the inside, and reveals the presence of intelligent denizens.  Two spikes have been placed on the outside of the cave mouth to either side of it.  Atop the spikes is some type of crude banner with a marking that you realize to be goblinoid in nature.  Beneath the banner are several skulls of various types of peoples tied to the spike.  A path leads from this place to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are deep in the forest.
nodes.l: ...the beauty of South City Forest.  The area here is barely touched by the travelers of the land.  As a result, many of the flower bearing bushes are intact, and the trees have been allowed to reach an impressive height.  Birds flitter high above you, while land based animals dart to and fro.  You can find paths from here leading northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You are standing before a desolate structure.
nodes.l: ...the beauty of South City Forest.  Through the many flower bearing bushes and amidst the trees you see a small wooden structure that may have once been a hut.  This hut has long since been deserted and the wood has been allowed to rot.  Peering in, you see nothing but cobwebs and dust; not even the animals enter this dilapidated building.  You find paths leading northeast, southeast, and northwest.

nodes.s: You stand before a small stream.
nodes.l: ...a bubbling brook.  The trees seem to part majestically to permit a free flowing stream to pass.  Fish can be seen being carried by the current of this stream, and rocks force the water to splash high into the air while the strong current creates a foam about the rocks.  Out of the corner of your eye, you see a figure near the brook which quickly darts into the forest as you turn your head to look.  The path continues to the northeast and to the west.  A small wooden bridge arches over the stream to a viney path northwest of here.

Small stones are strewn about the path, making your footing very difficult.  You may continue to the north, or escape this path by going southeast.

nodes.l: ...thorny bushes all around.  This area of the forest has a path, but the path has been overrun by rose-bearing bushes and vines with large, sharp thorns.  Small stones are strewn about the path, making your footing very difficult.  To the north is a cave entrance that has been curtained by a wall of crosshatched vines.  The path continues to the south.

nodes.s: You are in a large, dark, vine-covered cave.
nodes.l: ...a large vine-covered cave.  This cave, you notice, has vines that crop up from the ground and seem to cover every inch of the walls and ceiling.  The ground has been covered with a thick layer of cut moss.  Three small fires burn continuously in the center of this cave; over two of them are large cauldrons.  One has boiling water, while the other has some type of soup.  A large cul-de-sac against the far wall contains a huge pile of skins, twigs, and leaves made into a bed of some nature.  Though the heat in this cave is refreshing and comfortable, the smell of sweat and rotting animal drifts through the air.  The mouth of this cave is covered with a curtain made of cross-hatched vines and lies to the south.

nodes.s: You are on a dark path.
nodes.l: ...a shadowy path.  The trees here grow tall and free, and their branches filter out much of the light that would normally fall on the path.  You hear the sounds of birds flying high overhead, but try as you may, you cannot catch a glimpse of them.  A layer of underbrush covers the ground of this path which leads to the east and west.

nodes.s: You are at a fork in the path.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  This clearing is natural, and has been created by the small paths that lead from it.  The trees here allow only a little of the light from above to filter through.  The paths from here lead to the northwest, southwest, and to the east.

nodes.s: You are in the forest.
nodes.l: ...a rocky forest path.  This path appears to be more rocky than most of the other paths that you have traveled in South City Forest.  While trees and bushes are evident here, they are not as closely packed as most of the forest.  They still prevent much light from reaching you, but you find your passage here easier than in the deeper parts of the forest.  This path continues to the northwest and to the northeast.

nodes.s: You stand before a small hill.
nodes.l: ...the beginnings of North Spiral Mountain.  While a pass does lead through the spires of this majestic mountain range, the legends of the many travelers that have entered these mountains and have never returned comes to mind, forcing you to pause as you consider your next traveling decisions.  Your palms itch as you recall the legend of Mord, the mightiest of minotaurs, and the treasures that he must possess.  (It is said that he bears a halberd that can only be wielded by the mightiest of heroes, able to cleave even the best prepared adventurer in half in a single stroke).  Your heart beats quickly as you consider taking on the challenges of Mord and the other denizens of the mount.  The pass to North Spiral Mountain. leads westward, while the forest lies to your east.

nodes.s: You stand before a small hill.
nodes.l: ...the beginnings of South Spiral Mountains.  You recall the great legends of Mirax, the great dragon of South Spiral Mountain, and thank the goddess that the pass has long since been closed by an quake-produced rockslide.  Though you may foolishly long to attempt the treasures of Mirax, the only path from here back to the forest, eastward.

nodes.s: You are on a beaten path.
nodes.l: ...a path beaten into the ground of the forests.  Many trees have been fallen, with broken branches all around.  Bushes look like they have been yanked up carelessly, and even the weeds look like they have been trampled into the ground.  This beaten path is riddled with various tracks, and continues to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small makeshift tower.  A small circular clearing has been created here, and centered in it is a wooden tower that stands approximately twelve feet in height.  The tower, while empty, looks like it could have been recently occupied.  A beaten path leads to the northeast and west of here, while a small cobbled path leads southeast of here.

nodes.s: You are on a forest path.
nodes.l: ...a small cobbled path.  The path here has several cobble stones laid upon it. It is apparent that this has been done without the benefit of a master cobbler, as many of the stones are presently missing, uprooted, or mislaid.  Rather than make your footing easier, the cobbling of this path actually makes it more difficult for you to travel.  The cobbled path leads southeast, while it becomes a more natural path to the northwest.

nodes.s: You stand outside a walled encampment.
nodes.l: ...a great wooden reinforcement.  West of here you can see a small hill.  Between you and the hill, however, is a large wooden wall which has a closed, iron-banded door set  in it.  The iron-banded door, however, has long since been thrown off its hinges, and no longer bars your passage to the great hill beyond.  Several vultures stare menacingly at you as they feast on the few body parts that have been left to remain here.  While you may approach the hill to the east, the path leads west from here.

nodes.s: You are in a large clearing of the forest.
nodes.l: ...a large clearing of the forest.  This area is clear of any trees and vegetation, allowing the bright sky to be seen.  It is almost eerie at how tightly packed the forest is around this clearing, and it defies you to explain how this clearing came to be.  You can barely continue into the dense forest southwest or north from here.  A dark, shadowy pass leads from here in the northeast direction.

nodes.s: You are in dense forest.
nodes.l: ...nothing but trees and bush.  This dense part of South City Forest is obviously not traveled often enough for there to be any real path.  You hear the sounds of many creatures scurrying about, though, and you are forced to wonder just how many of these sounds are caused by humanoid creatures.  You believe you can make your way either southwest or northeast from here.

nodes.s: You are in a clearing.
nodes.l: ...an uprooted area of the forest.  Many of the trees here have been forcibly uprooted, though you can only guess at the cause of this condition.  This clearing has a layer of loose soil caused by the uprooting of these trees.  There are paths that lead to dense forest to the northeast and northwest, while a razed path leads south from here.

nodes.s: You are in a destroyed part of the forest.
nodes.l: ...a razed path in the forest.  The trees here have been bent, or outright uprooted by some force that can only be imagined.  The bush and weeds in this area have been literally pressed into the ground, and several marks that look like tree dragging tracks cut into the path here.  This part of the forest is devoid of the birds and other animals that seem so prolific to the forest.  The razed path continues north and south from here.

nodes.l: ...a razed path in the forest.  The trees here have been bent, or outright uprooted by some force that can only be imagined.  The bush and weeds in this area have been literally pressed into the ground, and several marks that look like tree dragging tracks cut into the path here.  This part of the forest is devoid of the birds and other animals that seem so prolific to the rest of the forest.  The razed path continues east and west.

nodes.s: You stand outside a huge cavern.
nodes.l: ...a huge opening in a hill.  This cave mouth is at least five men high, and is wide enough to easily fit a two-horse carriage through it.  The area here is devoid of trees, brush, and anything else that could conceivably fit into the category of  forest life.  There are indistinguishable tracks in the loose dirt here which lead both in and out of the cave.  The cave, which is to the north, has a very foreboding feel to it, while a path has been forcibly created to the east of here.

nodes.s: You are in a huge dark cavern.
nodes.l: ...a huge cavern.  This cavern has many marks in the walls that can only be described as scratches created by some huge creature.  A pile of bones almost a man high stands at the northern end of this cavern.  The bones have been cleaned of any trace of flesh or muscle that may have once existed on them.  While the stench of death and sulfur is evident within this cave, it is almost immaculate.  The only exit from this cave is to the south.

nodes.s: You are in dense forest.
nodes.l: ...nothing but trees and bush.  This dense part of South City Forest is obviously not traveled often enough for there to be any real path.  You hear the sounds of many creatures scurrying about, though, and you are forced to wonder just how many of these sounds are caused by humanoid creatures.  You believe you can make your way either east or west from here.

nodes.s: You stand before a large pond.
nodes.l: ...a natural hotbed.  A small pond is found here, and it bubbles from the heat that is created far beneath it.  The vegetation here is lush and thick, as the pond gives off some type of nutrients that assist in the growth of the vegetation here.  One of the densest part of South City Forest, you can only make your way northwestward from here.

nodes.s: You are in dense forest.
nodes.l: ...a small hut in the distance.  The forest seems to become less dense here, though it is still very difficult to pass this area.  You can see, off to the northeast, a small wooden hut.  Thatch and straw make up the roof of this hut, and a small well stands outside of it.  You realize that his must be the dwelling of the Old Man who is oft spoke of in the Wizard's Spire, and you realize that he only permits those who are worthy of his attention to approach his dwelling.  You can make your way back into the dense forest in the western direction.

nodes.s: You stand outside a small hut.
nodes.l: ...the hermit's hut.  This small clearing that has the hermit's hut and well has a sense of serenity and controlled power to it.  The door to the hermit's hut stands open, inviting all that have made it thus far to enter and meet with the old man.  The forest lies to the southwest of here.

nodes.s: You are in a dark cave.
nodes.l: ...a small room.  The hermit's hut, small and quaint, appears to have only the bare necessities to it.  A table and two chairs are placed by the fireplace for warmth, and a skin rug lies on the floor for comfort.  The hermit, despite rumors, appears to be gentlemanly and well kept.  His eyes hold a look of serene wisdom and controlled powder as he sits quietly in one of the chairs.  A black curtain hangs on the north wall, separating this room from the room beyond.

nodes.s: You are in the rear of the hut.
nodes.l: ...a magickal workshop.  Beakers, fires, and tomes line the rear of the hut which is impossibly huge.  Several of the hermit's apprentices (whom not many know about) wander to and fro as they tend to their experiments and learning.  The only exit from this room is through the black curtain to the south.

nodes.s: You are in the rear of the cave.
nodes.l: ...a hidden part of the dragon's cave.  This area has several bones strewn about.  Many pieces of armor and other equipment also line the floor, but all of these have been destroyed, either burnt or broken.  Useless, they lie here for some unknown purpose.
nodes.quest_text: enter ... Visons of dragons flow quickly through your mind! ... %s shudders slightly. ... 2

nodes.s: You have entered a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  This cave looks much like any other cave that you have seen; it is large, dark, and dirty.  The northern face of this cave, however, has been chipped away and worked at until a small passageway was created through it.  The darkness prevents you from seeing too far into the passageway, though.  You can tell that the passageway is not all too large.  The passageway to the north and the cave entrance to the south are the only exits from this room.

nodes.s: You are in a small worked passage.
nodes.l: ...a rudely formed passageway.  This passageway has literally been cut from the stone of the hill that you are within.  The workmanship of this passageway is crude, but sturdy.  A thin layer of dust is in the air, tickling your nose and distorting your vision slightly.  This passageway continues to the north and south.

nodes.l: ...a rudely formed passageway.  This passageway has literally been cut from the stone of the hill that you are within.  The workmanship of this passageway is crude, but sturdy.  A thin layer of dust is in the air, tickling your nose and distorting your vision slightly.  This passageway continues to the north and south.

nodes.s: You are in an intersection.
nodes.l: ...an intersection of passageways.  Two passageways intersect here forming a "T".  Like the rest of the passageway, the area here is worked crudely.  It is obvious that these passageways were created for functionality rather than for aesthetics.  Exits from this area are to the north, south, and east.

nodes.s: You are in a small cave.
nodes.l: ...a small natural cave.  Though the passageway to the southwest is obviously worked by some type of creature, this underground cave has been naturally formed.  The ceiling to this cave is fairly high, though the rest of the dimensions are almost diminutive.  In addition to the worked passageway to the southwest, there are natural exits from this cave to the northeast and to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a small cave.
nodes.l: ...a small natural cave.  This small dark cave has no outstanding qualities to it.  It is roughly shaped, and has a thin layer of dust on the floor.  The dust has several track marks which reveal the fact that this cave has seen some traffic in the recent past.  Exits from this cave exist to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a smelly cave.
nodes.l: ...a small natural cave.  This small cave has the stench of wet dogs hanging in it; it assails your senses.  Though the layer of dust normally associated with these caves is absent, there are piles of dirty rags, bones, and feces scattered throughout this cave.  The only exit from this cave is to the northwest.

nodes.s: You are in a small passageway.
nodes.l: ...a natural passageway.  The scent of wet, dirty dogs assails your senses as you pass though this passageway while a thick layer of dust in the air forces you to cough constantly.  Exits from this passageway are to the east and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a small passageway.
nodes.l: ...a natural passageway.  The scent of wet, dirty dogs assails your senses as you pass though this passageway while a thick layer of dust in the air forces you to cough constantly.  Exits from this passageway are to the east and west.

nodes.s: You are in a messy cavern.
nodes.l: ...a small, messy cavern.  The scent of wet dogs is even more evident in this cave than in many of the other caves that you have visited in this place.  A layer of dust hangs in the air, and it is difficult to hold back the coughs and chokes that the dust attempts to solicit.  Small bones, broken and chewed, lie scattered on the floor of this cavern.  There are several exits from this cavern; they are to the northwest, northeast, south, and west.

nodes.s: You are in a mineway.
nodes.l: ...a small mineshaft.  The air here is dank and foul.  Several wooden arches support the ceiling and walls of this area, though they look as though they could give out at any time.  Lanterns, unlit and unfilled, hang from the many ceiling arches that have been created.  Though the mineway continues to the southeast, there is an exit to the north.

nodes.s: You are in a mineway.

nodes.s: You are in a mineway.
nodes.l: ...a small mineshaft.  The air here is dank and foul.  Several wooden arches support the ceiling and walls of this area, though they look as though they could give out at any time.  Lanterns, unlit and unfilled, hang from the many ceiling arches that have been created.  Many holes seem to have been picked out of the walls and floor of this place.  You think you catch the glint of some type of crystal from the rocks on the ceiling, but think it best to leave it uninvestigated.  The mineway continues to the north and west.

nodes.s: You are in a large cavern.
nodes.l: ...a large cavern with picked walls.  Small chunks of quartz are seen embedded in the wall, though most of it has been long since removed.  You notice that there is a small skeleton on the floor near the far wall; it looks goblinoid in nature.  Rusted tools lie near this skeleton.  You are forced to wonder about the cause of its death.  The only exit from this cavern is to the south.

nodes.l: ...a dark, dusty cavern.  The cavern shows signs of a cave-in having occurred here, a small skeletal hand sticks out from among the rocks piled against the far wall.  The cavern may be exited to the north.

nodes.s: You are atop a shaftway.
nodes.l: ...a stone well.  The walls of this cavern appears to be made almost entirely of quartz.  You light is reflected and glitters with all the colors of the rainbow as the quartz captures and reflects your light.  There is a small well-like hole that has been cut into the floor, though it far too dark to make out what could possibly lie in such a place.  With no way to progress down into the causeway, the only exit from this cavern is to the southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a natural passageway.
nodes.l: ...a natural passageway.  This passageway twists and turns erratically.  Dust in the air makes it difficult to see at times, and the air seems to tickle your throat.  A faint, indiscernible odor hangs in the air.  You may continue to the north or southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a large smelly cavern.
nodes.l: ...a fairly large cavern.  This cavern, though large, has a cramped feeling to it.  Rags, bones, and other filth litter the floor of this cavern.  The scent of wet and dirty dogs is prevalent here.  The smell, combined with the layer of dust, force you to gag as you breath.  There is a single exit from this cavern to the south.

nodes.l: ...a crudely shaped room.  This room, like the passageway, was created by workers who were either rushed, unskilled, or both.  Roughly square in shape, this room has a thin layer of dust on the floor and walls.  Exits from this room can be found to the north and south.

nodes.s: You are in a large cavern.
nodes.l: ...a natural cavern.  Your torches flicker when entering this cavern, as there are small holes in the ceiling that force air into the cavern.  The layer of dust in the air that you have become so accustomed to has been filtered out by the air being brought into the cavern.  While a small stench still hangs in the air, it is no where near as strong as it has been in other areas of this complex.  In the northwestern corner of this roughly shaped cavern, you notice a large golden-red archway which has been carved into the wall.  Many glyphs are scribed into the archway.  You cannot quite discern the meaning of these glyphs, though they appear to be goblinoid in nature.  Aside from the glyphed archway, which has a small curtain of an iron-type substance to block passage through it, there are exits which lead east and west.

nodes.s: You are in a rocky passageway.
nodes.l: ...a rocky passageway.  This passageway has many rocks embedded into the floor, which make travel more difficult than in other areas of this complex.  You cannot help but notice the large golden-red archway that has been carved into the southeastern wall.  The many glyphs scribed into it defy all attempts at translation.  The only other exit from this passageway is to the northwest.

nodes.l: ...a rocky passageway.  This passageway has many rocks embedded into the floor, which make travel more difficult than in other areas of this complex.  There are exits from this passageway to the northeast, northwest, and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a dank, damp cave.
nodes.l: ...a dark cavern.  The ceiling in this cavern is high above you, and your light cannot reach high enough to see the top of this huge cavern.  Puddles have been formed on the floor by the constant drippings from the ceiling.  The water appears to drain out of this cavern somehow, though, as the entire floor is not covered in water.  The faint smell of feces hangs in the air.  The only exit from this cavern is to the north.

The floors have been smoothed by the long term passage of the many goblins that have inhabited these caves over the decades.  Dust has not been permitted to settle in these passages, nor have cobwebs been permitted to form.  There is a constant passage of air through these passages, though you cannot determine the source of such a welcome gift.  There are exits from this passageway to the north and south.

nodes.s: You are in a huge cavern.
nodes.l: ... a huge worked room.  This room is almost perfectly square, and has smooth walls.  Several lit lanterns hang on hooks on the walls of this room.  A small table sits against the north wall, and there are three chairs around it.  The south wall sports several animal skins which have been set up as bedding.  Manacles hang off the western wall, just north of the entrance of this room.  A huge iron door is in the eastern wall..  It has a large lock set into it.  The only exit from this room, aside from the door, is to the west.

nodes.s: You are in a smelly cell.
nodes.l: ...a dirty, smelly cell.  This room has many manacles attached to the wall to hold prisoners.  The cell smells of sweat and bodily functions.  The door to this cell is to the west.
nodes.quest_text: free prisoners ... You unshackle the prisoners. ... %s unchackles the prisoners. ... 

nodes.s: You are in the basement of Imperial Guild.
nodes.l: ...the basement.  The basement of the Imperial Training Hall holds many weapons and pieces of equipment in locked crates.  Two guildsman guard the Hall's equipment, and don't look like they are apt to allow any theft.  This corridor is cleaned, and the floor and walls are made of glitterglow, giving a bright appearance to this room.  There is a corridor to the west that leads to the famous Quest Corridor, while stairs lead up to the Guild Hall.

nodes.s: You have entered the famous Quest Corridor.
nodes.l: ...the famous Quest Corridor.  The heralds of olde created this corridor with its many rooms attached to is to help inform the peoples of Corinthia of what was going on in the lands.  These rooms also permitted the Council of Olde to hand down the many quests that were created by the land (and sometimes by them) in order to test the mettle of those who would attempt ascension into the Council of Guardians.  The heralds, having since returned to the Isle, have magicked the rooms once again to be able to tell tales of wonder, and of woe.  Tapestries of the great heralds who EMBRACE the STATUE of Gaetor, Councilor of Olde, hang from the ceiling.

nodes.s: You have entered the Herald's room.
nodes.l: ...a Quested Room.  You can feel the potent magic of this place as you gaze upon the statue of one of the mighty heralds of the land.  A voice booms in your head:  "Many are the trials that the peoples of the Island of Corinthia have been forced to endure, but none so inhumane as this.  The goblins of South City Forest have raided many of the villages of the island, and have taken captives to use as slaves, or worse, as food.  The goblins have even been so bold as to accost the good citizens of Imperius.  This will not do.  You seek to advance your stature and your status among the people of the lands.  You seek to prove your worth to the Council.  This, then, you must do.  Find the underground lair of the goblins.  Look deep within the Goblin Caves.  Find the cells that they keep the good folk of Corinthia in.  FREE the PRISONERS as you find them.  Prove yourself, my adventurer, and may the glory of the Council go with you.  Long Live The Rose."

nodes.s: You have entered the Herald's room.
nodes.l: ...a Quested Room.  You can feel the potent magic of this place as you gaze upon the statue of one of the mighty heralds of the land.  A voice booms in your head:  "Many are the ways that the people of Corinthia have to prove themselves to the Council, if they are willing to take the risk.  Deep within South City Forest lies a family of dragon whelps that have long since been abandoned.  The Great Minax, dracolich of legend, long ago abandoned this cave, and there are still magicks within it.  The taxidermist has managed to perfect a method of creating armor that is, indeed, powerful, but requires dragon scales to create it.  Your task, then, young citizen, is to find the dragons, and defeat them.  Young as they are, this task will prove to be many a citizen's undoing.  Once defeated, you must find the spot which they use to grow, and take from that spot one of their precious scales.  PRESENT the SCALE to the taxidermy, and you will have proven your worth to him, and to the Council.  Go, my adventurer, and may the glory of the Council go with you.  Long Live The Rose."

nodes.s: You have entered the Herald's room.
nodes.l: ...a Quested Room.  You can feel the potent magic of this place as you gaze upon the statue of one of the mighty heralds of the land.  A voice booms in your head:  "Many of the folk that are helped by the Council of Guardians.  Those that wish to become Councilors must, indeed, prove their willingness to assist those in need.  You, who are so willing to prove your self-sacrifice, then, are given to this task.  Within South City Forest lies a old man who once was a priest.  He has long since been cursed twicely. Once with immortality, but at the age that he as achieved, he can hardly enjoy it.  Twice, with the inability to eat or drink anything except a brew made by the malicious forest hags.  Your task is simple, young citizen.  Find thee, then, where the hags create this brew.  Bring it to the old man.  Once you GIVE the BREW to the old man, you receive his thanks, and our blessing.  Go, my adventurer, and may the glory of the Council go with you.  Long Live The Rose."

nodes.s: You have entered the Herald's room.
nodes.l: ...a Quested Room.  You can feel the potent magic of this place as you gaze upon the statue of one of the mighty heralds of the land.  A voice booms in your head:  "Many are the dwellings that are protected by the Council of Guardians.  Those that wish to become Councilors will find that their might must often be lent to the strength of the towns and cities... even great Imperius itself.  This is one such time.  The orcs that swell within South City Forest often plan to invade this fair city; if the might of Imperius should falter, then so shall the rest of Corinthia.  Knowing that they cannot hope to succeed without careful planning, the Council often finds great adventurers to infiltrate the orcs.  You can assist in this matter.  Find the Orc Caverns within South City Forest.  Find the orc invasion plans, whereever they may be.  PRESENT the orc INVASION PLANS at the Imperial Guard Tower, and not only will you have saved Imperius for yet another day, you will have earned the respect of the Council.  Go, my adventurer, and may the glory of the Council go with you.  Long Live The Rose."

nodes.s: You have entered Tasque Arena.
nodes.l: ...that you have entered Tasque Arena.  Torches line the walls; it is not lit by the same glitterglow as the rest of the city.  The shadows cast give the arena an eerie sense to it.  The arena master stands beside a great brass gong; one of the ancients, he is responsible for the summoning of the creatures into this great arena.  Great brass gates lead south out of the arena.

nodes.s: You have entered the taxiderm's special workroom.
nodes.l: The smell of preservatives and acids assails you as you enter this huge work room.  A large oak table is centered in this room.  Far from being clean, this room has many shavings and leather strips lying all about.  A vat of blood and entrails is seen close to the table.  Two craftsman work on a large animal, reptilian in nature.  It is no surprise to see them carefully removing the scales from this creature.

nodes.s: You are in the apprentice's shop.
nodes.l: ...the apprentice's workshop.  This small room is poorly lit, save for a large luminescent candle atop a small podium in the western end of the room.  The room is cluttered with baskets of scrolls and other magical paraphenialia.  A gnomish apprentice sits hunched over a larg book, quill in hand.  He looks up at you from under his spectacles as if he already knows the answer to your questions.  The  main foyer of the aventurer's guild is to the west.

nodes.s: You have entered a dark corridor.
nodes.l: ...a dark corridor.  This corridor has no light save the light that you bring with you.  You notice that this corridor shows the signs of constant traffic.  Knowing the tenacity of the orcs of the area, you cannot help but wonder if you are truly prepared for the encounters to come.  The corridor leads east and west.

nodes.s: You are in an underground corridor.
nodes.l: ...a natural corridor.  Though naturally created, it is obvious that these corridors are well traveled.  The floor is devoid of much of the dust and soot that is normally associated with underground passages.  The only dirt that appears to be in the corridor is that which has fallen from weary travelers.  The walls bear many scratch marks upon them, their cause and reason unknown to you.  This corridor continues to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a cavern.
nodes.l: ...a small cavern.  This small cavern appears to be being used as some type of checkpoint or guard room.  There is a single table in this room, with two chairs around it; the chairs face each other.  Crudely made Shari blocks have been placed; the game apparently interrupted.  There are two small cages against the northern wall; both open.  There are exits from this cavern to the northwest, east, and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in an underground cavern.
nodes.l: ...a messy cavern.  This cavern has garbage, rags, half-eaten food, and filthy cloths thrown about the floor.  These items haven't even been pushed into corners or crevices; they practically line the floor.  Small paths in the garbage reveal that this cavern does have some traffic which goes through it.  The exits from this cavern are to the east, northwest, and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a wide cave.
nodes.l: ...a wide cavern.  This wide cavern has been cleaned and almost looks polished.  A great deal of care has gone into the care of this cavern, though the reasons for such cleanliness escapes you.  There is no dust on the floor; not even the dirt from passing boots is permitted to litter this place.  There are well formed exits to the north and west.

nodes.s: You are in a dusty passageway.
nodes.l: ...a dust filled passage.  This passage is filled with dust.  Cobwebs cover the ceiling and droops down in several locations.  The dust on the floor is heavy, though track-ridden.  Small pebbles riddle the floor, piecing the bottoms of your feet through the shoes.  The passage exits to the east and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in an abandoned cave.
nodes.l: ...a filth filled cave.  Bolts of rotting cloth and old rotting wooden chests line the walls of this cave.  Cobwebs completely cover the ceiling of this cave, and the rotting goods are covered in the same dust-covered strands.  The dust in the air seems to glitter in your light; it looks almost like snow.  While there are a few tracks in the dirt on the floor, it is difficult to determine when they were made, or by what.  The only exit from this cave it to the west.

nodes.s: You are in a small cavern.
nodes.l: ...an underground intersection.  Passages meet to form a small cavern here.  Like the passages that lead to it, the cavern is quite clean and well maintained.  There is a distinctive scent in the air that comes in from the south.  Besides the south exit, there are exits to the east and west.

nodes.s: You have entered an unkempt passageway.
nodes.l: ...an unkempt passageway.  A scent much like wet canines filters in from the southern portion of this passageway.  Dirty rags and garbage line the floor near the east and west walls of this passageway and dust hangs heavy in the air.  You may continue to the north or south from here.

nodes.s: You have entered a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a pen.  Several cages line the south wall of this cave, they are open and filthy.  Bones and remnants of chopped, molding meat lie near the cages.  Wet molding stacks of what may be hay sit in several locations of this large cavern, the strong scent of ammonia wafts from them.  A half-eaten carcass of some unidentifiable animal half-sits in one of the cages.  You hold back a gag as the scent of this room hits you; the smell of decay is far too strong for you to stomach for long.  You take in the sights as you notice that the only exit from this cave is to the north.

nodes.s: You are in a very large, well lit cavern.
nodes.l: ...a huge cavern.  This cavern is much larger than many others that you have encountered.  Several hooks line the walls of this cavern; lit lanterns hang from them.  Throughout this cavern there are torch holders standing up from the floor.  These hold lit torches.  This cavern is extremely well lit.  A huge oak door that has been reinforced with iron is in the southeastern part of this huge cavern.  Other exits lead to the north and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a well kept cavernway.
nodes.l: ...an very well kept corridor. This wide corridor has been cleaned and almost looks polished.  A great deal of care has gone into the care of this cavern, though the reasons for such cleanliness escapes you.  There is no dust on the floor; not even the dirt from passing boots is permitted to litter this place.  There are well formed exits to the south and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a dark corridore.
nodes.l: ...a dark corridor.  Broken weapons, rotting bags, and shattered chairs and other wood structures lie strewn about the this area.  There are no cobwebs, though the room smells heavily of mold and mildew.  This corridor leads to the west and southeast.

nodes.s: You have entered a cave.
nodes.l: ...a small cave.  This cave may have once been used for storage, but all the bins in this cave are empty.  Cobwebs cover the tops of these bins and barrels.  Dust and mildew cover everything in this room.  The only exit from this small, unlit cave is to the northwest.

nodes.s: You are underground.
nodes.l: ..and underground passage.  This passage is dark and dismal.  Your footsteps echo throughout the passageway; your shadows seem to dance on the wall.  Small stalactites hang from the ceiling, they are coated in a thin slime.  Small pebbles roll around as you inadvertently kick them as you stride through this passageway.  This passage leads you west and south.

nodes.s: You are in a small cavern.
nodes.l: ...a small underground cavern.  A pool of stagnant water collects around a small stalagmite.  The water has a layer of slime on it that does not look at all inviting.  Small patches of mold and fungus grow just outside the small puddle.  The air in this cavern is stale.  Exits lead you to the east and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a small twisting passage.
nodes.l: ...a small underground passageway.  This passageway looks nearly indistinguishable from many of the other passageways that you have traveled through.  This passageway leads you west and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a strangely shaped room.
nodes.l: ...a large natural cavern.  This cavern defies any attempt to prescribe a shape to it.  Many cul-de-sacs form along the huge walls of this cavern, and many of the exits that you see loop back to meet with another exit of this cavern.  Grime lines the floor of this large cavern, and the many stalactites and stalagmites of this cavern almost make it look like a huge mouth waiting to close.  The only real exit from this cavern is to the northwest.

There are exits from this corridor to the northwest and southeast.

There is a thin layer of dust on the ground.  There are exits from this passageway to the west and northeast.

nodes.s: You are in a large natural cavern.
nodes.l: ...a very large cavern.  This cavern has several small straw structures that vaguely resemble the human body.  Straw lines the floor of this cavern, and several broken arrow flights can be seen sticking out of the large straw structures.  It is noticable that someone has made an attempt to keep this cavern fairly clean, though debree still lines the floor amidst the straw.  There are exits from this cavern to the north, south, and west.

nodes.s: You have entered a well formed passageway.
nodes.l: ...a well worked passageway.  This passageway is of a working that is well beyond the capabilities of the orcs that inhabit this area.  You find it difficult to accurately determine what race may have worked these corridors, and presume that it is of a race that you have little knowledge about.  Cleaned almost to perfection, this passageway goes east and west.

nodes.s: You are in a huge cavern.
nodes.l: ...a huge cavern.  This cavern houses a large stone table which is centered in the room.  Upon the table are many unrolled scrolls which have charts and notes scribbled upon them.  A large stone door with a great iron keyhole dominates the west wall.  The only other exit from this room is to the east.

nodes.s: You are in a cramped cave.
nodes.l: ...a small cramped room.  In front of the north and south walls of this small cave there is a large pedastal which is normally used for the gargoyles to stand upon.  A small niche in the floor looks just the right size for a scroll case.  The only exit from this room is to the east.

nodes.s: You have entered the lay healer's hut.
nodes.l: ...the lay healer's hut.  One of the three lay healers permitted to operate within the boundaries of Imperial City, this lay healer derives much of her existence from the misfortunes of the combatants of Torith arena.  For a modest fee, the lay healer will heal some or all of your wounds.

For a modest fee, the lay healer will heal some or all of your wounds.

nodes.s: You have entered the lay healer's hut.

nodes.s: You are in a small pawn shop.
nodes.l: ...that you have entered a small pawn shop only steps away from the Imperial Bank.  This dingy pawn shop is run by a seedy individual known only as Ooteenie.  The room which you stand in is bare except for a large teller shaped window toward the southern end.  The teller window is built of a thick translucent glass.  Behind the glass is a metal grating which was created for no other reason than to protect the teller behind the pawn shop window.  Behind the reinforced window you see an assortment of weapons, armors, items, and mundane trinkets.  You get the feeling that although they will buy anything, you will not be getting much money for it, and you will most likely never see it again.

nodes.s: You have entered a mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a wide mountain pass.  This pass leads from South City Forest to the North Spiral Mountains.  From here you can see the many spires of the mountains that give this area its name.  Several tall peaks can be seen to either side of you.  It would be a simple matter for you to get lost and become one of the many nameless victems of the great spires.  The path continues to the east and west.

nodes.s: You have entered a rocky pass.
nodes.l: ...a small unused path.  By the grooves that are well worn into the stone of this path, you can tell that this path was once widely used.  Wide enough to comfortably fit a small wagon, this path was, perhaps, once part of some trading route.  Many pebbles and stones line the ground now, and several upcroppings of weeds shoot through the rock of the floor.  This barely used path continues to the north and south.

Many pebbles and stones line the ground now, and several upcroppings of weeds shoot through the rock of the floor.  This barely used path continues to the east and southeast.

nodes.s: You have entered a small stone building.
nodes.l: ...a well maintained building.  This stone building has managed to survive the ravages of time and stands tall and true.  The inside of this building, while dusty, seems to be fairly maintained, probably by passerbyers like yourself.  Many shelves line the walls of this building, and a small set of scales have been bolted to a small counter which is near the eastern wall.  This building may have been a way station at one point before its apparent abandonment.  You may exit this building to the west.

nodes.s: You are in a small mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a small mountain pass.  This pass is barely wide enough for a mounted rider to pass, and your footing is unsure.  The slopes to either side of you look like they could collapse at any time, though you know that this visage is misleading.  This pass continues to the east and northwest.

nodes.s: You have reached a dead end.
nodes.l: ...an ending to the pass.  You know that there is no way through the sheer rock that faces you, and you mumble to yourself as you force yourself around.  You know instictively that there are many such dead ends in the spires, and pray that you do not find every one on your travels.

nodes.s: You are on a rocky pass.
nodes.l: ...rocks... and more rocks.  This path seems to be lined with rocks from one mountain sheer to the other.  The rocks grind together with every step you take, and your nerves become frazzled as you continue on this path.  This rocky path continues to the west and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a wide clearing.
nodes.l: ...a wide clearing.  Many mountain paths meet here, and this has caused a large, nearly circular, clearing to form in the spires.  Bones riddle the floor, and you get the sense that this clearing is not always uninhabited.  You may take any of the several paths that lead from this place to the north, south, west, or northwest.

nodes.s: You are traveling in a valley.
nodes.l: ...a valley.  Mountains jut to either side of you as you walk along this valley.  Small pebbles roll as you uncaringly kick them away from you.  Travel to the north and southwest is possible here.

nodes.l: ...a natural clearing.  A small platform is formed by one of the overhangings that one of the mountain faces creates.  A makeshift tent has been created there.  This area is obviously a natural campsite which is often used by waytravellers like yourself.  You may continue your jouney to the north, south, or west.

nodes.s: You are traveling in a natural pass.
nodes.l: ...a pass in the mountains.  This natural path seems to follow one the many curves found while travelling North Spire Mountains.  While there are many pebbles on the grounds, the footing here is not difficult at all.  You may continue to the north or southeast.

nodes.s: You are at the base of a spire.
nodes.l: ...the base of one of the mountains.  The paths here diverge to travel to either side of the mountain's base.  Looking up gets you dizzy, as the spire of this mountain reaches high into the cloads.  The spire's path continues to the east, northwest, and southwest.

nodes.s: You are on a spire's path.
nodes.l: ...a small harsh path.  This path travels the base of the mountain at a height of nearly fifty feet.  The rock face both above and below you are sheer, and the footing here is dangerous.  You may continue on this path to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are on a spire's path.
nodes.l: ...a small harsh path.  This path travels the base of the mountain at a height of nearly fifty feet.  The rock face both above and below you are sheer, and the footing here is dangerous.  You may continue on this path to the  north and southeast.

nodes.s: You stand outside several cave entrances.
nodes.l: ...cave entrances.  There are several caves that lead from this part of the spire's path, though only two of these caves are truely accessible to you.  The path continues back to the south, or you may enter one of the caves; either northeast or west.

nodes.s: You are in a cave.
nodes.l: ...a dark cave.  This small cave has lichens and fungus growing prolifically within it.  Huge stalagmites line the floor of this cave.  A thin layer of ooze makes your footing very treacherous as it threatens to make you lose your footing to force into one of the many sharp conical formations that grow from the floor.  You may exit this cave to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  This large cave has several stalactites that hang from the cieling.  A small pool of rancid water is formed on the floor, though it looks like it hasn't been disturbed in quite some time.  Dust, dirt, and cobwebs fill this room making breathing difficult.  The rear of the cave lies to the southwest, while you may exit the cave to the east.

nodes.s: You are in the back of a cave.
nodes.l: ...the rear of this cave.  This part of the cave is much like the main part of the cave, though no water is found on this floor.  The dust in the air hangs heavily, and it is difficult to see.  The only exit is back to the main part of the cave to the west.

nodes.s: You are on a spire's path.
nodes.l: ...a small harsh path.  This path travels the base of the mountain at a height of nearly fifty feet.  The rock face both above and below you are sheer, and the footing here is dangerous.  You may continue on this path to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You are on a small plateu.
nodes.l: ...a beutiful view.  You find yourself on a small plateu which overlooks the majestry of North Spire Mountains.  Many mountains and their spires are seen, and the growth of their evergreens is evident from here.  Snow caps many of the mountains, while others seem to be hidden by the clouds.  You pause at this refreshing view of the mountains before you continue on to the south, west, or northeast.

nodes.l: ...a small harsh path.  This path travels the base of the mountain at a height of nearly fifty feet.  The rock face both above and below you are sheer, and the footing here is dangerous.  You may continue on this path to the north or east.

nodes.s: You stand outside a small cave entrance.
nodes.l: ...a cave entrance.  The elevated path that you have been travelling does, indeed, continue.  An aperture upon the eastern wall, however, catches your attention.  This cave entrance is fairly large, and a strong oder of decay wafts through the area.  The passage continues to the northwest and southwest.

nodes.s: You have entered a small cave.
nodes.l: ...a small cave.  The ceiling of this cave is fairly high, nearly fifteen feet from the ground, though the rest of the gave is farily small.  Bones and rotting fur line the floor of this cave which is obviously the lair of some type of creature.

nodes.s: You are in the back of a cave.
nodes.l: ...the rear of the cave.  More furs and rotting cloth is found in this room, though it is completely devoid of the bones that were in the front of the cave.

nodes.s: You have reached an intersection of paths.
nodes.l: ...several paths.  Many paths intersect here causing a small clearing.  The area that you are in is particularly well traveelled which is eveident by the absence of rocks, dust and debree.  The path to the east appears to be more travelled than the path to the south.

nodes.s: You are on a small path.
nodes.l: ...a well travelled path.  Though this path is elevated and treacherous, there are several tracks in the path.  You carefully end your way along this path which goes north and south.

nodes.s: You are on a small path.
nodes.l: ...a well travelled path.  Though this path is elevated and treacherous, there are several tracks in the path.  You carefully end your way along this path which goes north and southeast.

nodes.s: You stand outside a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a well travelled path.  Though this path is elevated and treacherous, there are several tracks in the path.  You notice a cave opening to the east, while the path continues to the northwest.

nodes.s: You are in a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  You stand within a large dark cave.  You are given the sense that you are being watched while within this cave which causes you to feel concerned and weary.  This cave has a single exit to the west.

nodes.s: You are on a well traveled path of the spire.
nodes.l: ...a smooth plan.  This path is elevated high above the mountain floor, but is wide and easy to travel.  A layer of pounded dirt lines this road, and several guards have been built along the edge of this road.  A sense of warmness overcomes you as you travel this path.  It continues to the east and west.

nodes.s: You stand outside the halfing village.
nodes.l: ...a small platform.  Beneath you lies a small winding road which leads to the Township of Spalango with its large guild hall standing tall in the middle of the villiage.  Several people, many of them halflings, doll about the villiage.  The mountain pass which leads to the villiage has been worked and reworked until it is as smooth as any worked road that you have seen.  The Township lies to the north, while this path continues to the south.

nodes.s: You are on a mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a pass in the mountains.  Barely passible, this path is thin and dangerous.  Far beneath you is the canyon floor; the wall leading to it is nearly sheer.  Looking above, you can see that the peaks of the mountains near you are shrouded in mist and clouds.  This path gets no easier as you travel to the east or northwest.

nodes.s: You stand outside a small cave mouth.
nodes.l: ...several broken statues.  Many statue bases of long lost heroes are found here, many of which have been broken or worn away with time. Statue legs lie everywhere, while a small statue head lies near the cave mouth towards the north.  This path continues to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a small damp cave.
nodes.l: ...a small damp cave.  Several smooth stalagmites grow from the floor, while several ragged stalactites sink from the cieling.  Many statues of men and women in various poses of defense are in this cave, many have the look of horror on their faces.  You may exit this cave to the south.

nodes.s: You are on a mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a small mountain pass.  This path is lined with many small pebbles seemingly attack the bottoms of your feet as you walk this pass.  Not truely treacherous despite its height above the mountain floor, this path continues to the north and southeast.

nodes.s: You are on a mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a small mountain pass.  This path is lined with many small pebbles seemingly attack the bottoms of your feet as you walk this pass.  Not truely treacherous despite its height above the mountain floor, this path continues to the south and northwest.

nodes.s: You stand atop a small ledge.
nodes.l: ...a small natural ledge.  While the site that is normally seen upon many of the plateus is beutific, the site seen here is rather plain.  Several mountain spires are seen from here, though not many features are evident along them aside from the basic vegetation that you are so used to seeing.  Paths lead from this ledge to the west, northeast, and southeast.

nodes.s: You travel steadily along a path.
nodes.l: ...a small mountain pass.  This path is lined with many small pebbles seemingly attack the bottoms of your feet as you walk this pass.  Not truely treacherous despite its height above the mountain floor, this path continues to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.l: ...a small mountain pass.  This path is lined with many small pebbles seemingly attack the bottoms of your feet as you walk this pass.  Not truely treacherous despite its height above the mountain floor, this path continues to the north and southwest.

nodes.l: ...an ending to the pass.  You know that there is no way through the sheer rock that faces you, and you mumble to yourself as you force yourself around.  You know instictively that there are many such dead ends in the spires, and pray that you do not find every one on your travels.

nodes.s: You are on a descending mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a small depression in the mountains.  This clearing has the benifit of being blocked from civilation by the many mountain spires that seem to meet here.  A small pool of water is here, though you can tell that is far too dirty and dusty to drink safely.  Passes lead from this depression to the north, east, and west.

nodes.s: You walk along a rocky path.
nodes.l: ...a rock ridden path.  This path, like many others in the North Spire Mountains is lined with pebbles and stones of various sizes.  Several sharp stones almost pierce your boots as you walk along this path which leads south and northwest.

nodes.s: You walk along a rocky path.
nodes.l: ...a rock ridden path.  This path, like many others in the North Spire Mountains is lined with pebbles and stones of various sizes.  Several sharp stones almost pierce your boots as you walk along this path which leads north and southeast.

nodes.l: ...an ending to the pass.  You know that there is no way through the sheer rock that faces you, and you mumble to yourself as you force yourself around.  You know instictively that there are many such dead ends in the spires, and pray that you do not find every one on your travels.

nodes.s: This is a dummy room.
nodes.l: ...an expanse of gray and haze.  Your presence here disturbs the natural flow of the universe, and unless you have some power over this haze, you are most likely trapped here forever.  No exits are apparent, and even the most extensive search avails you not.

nodes.s: You are on a descending mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a rock ridden path.  This path, like many others in the North Spire Mountains is lined with pebbles and stones of various sizes.  Several sharp stones almost pierce your boots as you walk along this path which leads east and southwest.

nodes.s: You are on a descending mountain pass.
nodes.l: ...a rock ridden path.  This path, like many others in the North Spire Mountains is lined with pebbles and stones of various sizes.  Several sharp stones almost pierce your boots as you walk along this path which leads south, northeast, and northwest.

nodes.s: You walk upon a smooth natural pass.
nodes.l: ...a smooth path.  This path is devoid of the rocks, stones, and pebbles that normally line many of the natural paths found among these mountains.  Though there are no tracks on this ground, the floor of this area has been smoothed with passage.  Several scratch marks can be seen on the walls of the surrounding mountain faces.  This path continues to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You stand outside a large cave entrance.
nodes.l: ...a large cave entrance.  Like the path that leads to this cave entrance, the ground here has been smoothed over by the passage of time and travel.  Only a few small pebbles and stones can be found along the floor here.  Many deep scratches are found in the wall surrounding the cave entrance though their cause is a mystery to you.  You may enter the cave to the north, or continue along the path to the southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  Many ledges at various heights are found on the walls of this cave.  The center of this cave houses a small stone pedastal, though there is nothing atop it.  No dust or cobwebs are found in this cave, though you can't shake the feeling that there is something watching you.  The only exit from this cave is to the south.

nodes.l: ...a valley.  Mountains jut to either side of you as you walk along this valley.  Small pebbles roll as you uncaringly kick them away from you.  Travel to the north and southwest is possible here.

nodes.s: You stand outside a large tower.
nodes.l: ...a large obsidian tower.  The legends about this tower, the Spire of Kragoth, abound.  Many are the adventures that have attempted to find an entrance to this tower; all withiin the past century or so have failed.  The rumors about the magical cache that must be found within are many.  No-one has been able to enter this place to confirm these rumors.  If any have been able to enter, they have not returned and are considered to be yet another victim of the North Spire Mountains.  The only exit from this place is to the northwest.

nodes.s: You are traveling in a valley.
nodes.l: ...a valley.  Mountains jut to either side of you as you walk along this valley.  Small pebbles roll as you uncaringly kick them away from you.  Travel to the northwest and southeast is possible.

nodes.s: You have entered a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing in the mountains.  This clearing, like many of the other clearings that exist among the mountains, is the result of several natural paths that have meet at a large juncture.  This clearing is fairly devoid of any special qualities.  Rocks, pebbles, and stones litter the clearing and several brushes of growth can be found here.  There are exits from this clearing to the north, northeast, and the southeast.

nodes.s: You travel one of the spire's passes.
nodes.l: ...a thin path of the mountain.  The path that you are travelling on is a natural path that winds around one of the many spires of North Spire Mountain.  Looking below you, you notice that a fall of over a hundred feet awaits you should you lose your footing.  The path has been smooth by its exposure to the elements, and winds its way to the south and northwest.

nodes.s: You have reached a dead end.
nodes.l: ...an ending to the pass.  You know that there is no way through the sheer rock that faces you, and you mumble to yourself as you force yourself around.  You know instictively that there are many such dead ends in the spires, and pray that you do not find every one on your travels.

nodes.s: You walk along the base of several mountains.
nodes.l: ...a large wide valley.  You walk on the canyon floor at the base of several of the mountains of North Spire Mountains.  Above you looms the expanse of the mountains which are shouded in clouds high above you.  Bushes and dirt line the canyon floor, and an occasional tree colors the area that you walk about.  This valley continues to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You are outside a cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave entrance.  Like the path that leads to this cave entrance, the ground here has been smoothed over by the passage of time and travel.  Only a few small pebbles and stones can be found along the floor here.  Many deep scratches are found in the wall surrounding the cave entrance though their cause is a mystery to you.  You may enter the cave to the west, or continue along the path to the north.

nodes.s: You have entered a small cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  Many ledges at various heights are found on the walls of this cave.  The center of this cave houses a small stone pedastal, though there is nothing atop it.  No dust or cobwebs are found in this cave, though you can't shake the feeling that there is something watching you.  The only exit from this cave is to the east.

nodes.s: You are in a clearing.
nodes.l: ...a clearing in the mountains.  Several natuarl paths lead out of the valley here, and a small clearing is formed.  Dry and dusty, the floor here is cracked and brittle.  Pebbles and dried balls of dirt and clay are strewn about.  While the valley may be entered to the northwest, thre are paths to the east and northwest.

nodes.s: You walk along a running stream.
nodes.l: ...a running stream.  A small stream passes through this area, and you are walking aside it.  The stream rolls rapidly past you, splashing you as it encounters the many boulders that are within it.  The spray of the stream is refreshing and soothes you as you continue on your journeys.  The stream, and its subsequent path, continues to the east, while a clearing to the mountains is to the west.

nodes.s: You are at a waterfall.
nodes.l: ...a waterfall.  The stream that you have been following takes a sudden dive down into rocks and unknown territory here.  Looking down from you vantage point you can see that the waterfall drops a few hundred feet into rocks that are sharp and very deadly.  The path that you have been following returns you north.  There are no other exits from here.

nodes.s: You ascend one of the many spires.
nodes.l: ...a path high on the mountains.  Like many of the paths within the North Spiral Mountains, this one is elevated high above the canyon floor.  This path is wide and fairly easy to transverse, though its slope makes it tiresome to travel here.  The view from so high up off the ground is breathtaking.  You may continue to the northwest or southeast.

nodes.s: You have reached a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  Several trees and brush part to reveal a small clearing that is fairly unexplored.  Grass grows on the ground here, and a the trees grow to an amazing height.  The soil here is amazingly soft and fertile.  You may leave this clearing by travelling northeast or south.

nodes.s: You walk along a thin twisting ledge.
nodes.l: ...a thin ledge.  This path is quite treacherous as it is thin and winding.  You tred carefully to avoid any missteps as you travel north or southeast.

nodes.s: You have reached a dead end.

nodes.s: You are walking along a thin pass.
nodes.l: ...a thin ledge.  This path is quite treacherous as it is thin and winding.  You tred carefully to avoid any missteps as you travel east or southwest.

nodes.s: You stand outside a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave mouth.  The mountain face to the southeast has an aperture that seems to have been cut and smoothed.  Even to the most untrained eye it is apparent that this cave was not formed naturally; the workmanship of this aperture is not immediately apparent.  You may enter this cave which lies to the southeast, or you may return westward.

nodes.s: You have entered a huge cavern.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  This cave is large and dark.  The many stalactites and stalagmites in the room make you feel like you have just entered a large toothy maw.  Shadows seem to dance upon the wall, and your lights flicker in the wind.  A large statue of a warrior defending himself with sword and shield is centered in this cave, though how it got here, or why it is here, is a mystery.  The cave exit is to the northwest.

nodes.s: You are on a natural path.
nodes.l: ...a wide dirt path.  This dirt path is formed by the connection of two of the spires of the North Spire Mountains.  In several places, there are small holes in the ground which reveal that this path, while solid, is hundreds of feet above the true valley floor of the Spires.  An amazing site, this path continues to the east and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...a large clearing.  This area, much like the path that leads to it, is formed by the junction of several mountain spires.  Also like the path that leads to it, the clearing is actually several hundred feet above the true valley floor.  You can feel drafts of air that whistles through the tiny holes of the clearing floor.  You may leave the clearing to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking in a huge valley.
nodes.l: ...a long wide canyon.  You find yourself walking in one of the large valleys of the North Spire Mountains.  Small patches of grass and shrubbery grow along the edges of the valley.  The great spires of the mountains surrounding you cast shadows into the valley making it seem like perpetual dusk.  This part of the valley runs east and west.

nodes.s: You have entered a huge clearing.
nodes.l: ...a large wide clearing.  The valley here opens into a huge clearing.  This clearing has several large trees within it, as well as a small pond.  The water in the pond is clean and bubbles with its heat.  Unlike most heated springs, this pond appears to have a particular lack of sulpher, and is still drinkable.  The dirt here has been pounded by the passing of many creatures and adventures and is almost perfectly smooth.  The clearing has paths leading from it which go north, northeast, and southeast.

nodes.s: You are walking along a well traveled path.
nodes.l: ...a well travelled path.  This dirt road has been smoothed over by the passage of time and many travellers.  Several old glyphs are marked into the ground, though their meaning is long lost.  Large rocks line this road, most likely as leaning or sitting posts.  This path continues to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You have entered a small stone building.
nodes.l: ...a well maintained building.  This stone building has managed to survive the ravages of time and stands tall and true.  The inside of this building is clean and well maintained as well.  Many shelves line the walls of this building, and they are stocked well with adventurer's gear, weapons, and armors.  It is a wonder how such a place could exist and maintained in the dangers of the Spires, but a sign posted cautions you "No questions, no lies.  Serious inquiries only."  A well-built, though fairly old, human converses with a small fairyfolk; the obvious proprietors of this shop.

nodes.s: You walk along an ascending path.
nodes.l: ...a small harsh path.  This path travels the base of the mountain at a height of nearly fifty feet.  The rock face both above and below you are sheer, and the footing here is dangerous.  You may continue on this path north and south.

nodes.s: You are outside a small cavern.
nodes.l: ...the entrance to a small cavern.  This mountain ledge leads directly to a small cavern.  The entrance of the cavern has several cobwebs that hang from the top, and vines grow around the aperture leading to the interior of this cavern.  This cavern is obviously visited infrequently.  The cavern lies to the east, or you may return to the path that lies south of here.

nodes.s: You have entered a cave.
nodes.l: ...a small cavern.  This small cavern is devoid of many of the features that are present in mountain caves.  No stalactites hang from the cieling, and no stalagmites grow from the floor.  A layer of dust and dirt is on the floor, and the smell of earth and fungus is strong here.  This cavern may be exited to the west.

nodes.s: You stand atop a high plateau.
nodes.l: ...a plateau high on in the mountains.  This plateau gives you a good view of the surrounding areas, though the air here is a bit thin.  You can see many of the peaks that make up the North Spire Mountains, though several of the peaks are shrouded by cloud cover.  North of here is Mount Spirian, one of the minor peaks of the North Spire Mountains, while paths lead down to the west and southeast.

nodes.s: You are following a descending path.
nodes.l: ...a slanted pathway in the mountains.  This pathway is difficult to foot as it is steeply angled.  You carefully tred upon the rocky path, careful not to lose your footing which would cause you to begin an uncontrollable tumble down the mountain side.  The path continues to the east and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a depression.
nodes.l: ...a depression in the valley.  You have reached the base of one of the mountains of the Norh Spires.  The area that you are at presently is a large clearing which is further depressed in the center.  This clearing looks much like a huge bowl that has been filled with dirt.  You may climb north out of this depression.

nodes.s: You are atop Mount Spirian.
nodes.l: ...a breathtaking view.  Standing atop Mount Spirian, the second tallest mountain in the North Spires, you see much of the country side below.  Many areas are hidden from your view by the clouds that drift below you.  You find yourself breathing heavily due to the height that you have attained, and your breath forms little crystals in the air.  You shiver as a wind blows past you.  Surveying the area, you see that you may continue south, northeast, or northwest.

nodes.s: You are following a thin path downwards.
nodes.l: ...a thin spiralling path.  This path leads from the top of Mt. Spirian, one of the tallest mountains in this range.  This path is perhaps one of the most treacherous of the paths that you have encountered, as it is both thin and steep.  With all the twists and turns this path takes, one misstep could spell disaster.  This dizzying pathway may be travelled north or southwest.

nodes.s: You have reached a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small wooded clearing.  This clearing has quite a bit of vegation growing within it.  Bushes and grass grow strong and unrestrained.  Several large trees tower over you.  Mountain flowers give off a beautiful scent, and a small creek runs by.  The cool mist caused by the creek refreshes and revitalizes you.  The only exit from this natural beuty is to the west.

nodes.s: You are on a small plateau.
nodes.l: ...a plateu overlooking several paths.  This small plateu offers a small view of some of the clearings in the area.  Many trees growing nearby block your view of much of the land, however.  Three paths lead from this plateu; they go south, northeast, and northwest.

nodes.s: You are carefully following the rocky path.
nodes.l: ...a cracked rocky path.  This path has been dried out and is well travelled.  Cracks have formed in the earth from the lack of moisture on this path, and fairly large rocks have formed and can be seen everywhere.  This path leads east, northeast, and southwest.

nodes.s: You are the base of several spires.
nodes.l: ...severeal mountains which reach far above you.  You find yourself at the junction of several mountain bases.  This clearing is rocky and overshadowed by the towering mountains.  Though no real breeze blows here, the warmth of the sun does not reach this spot making it very cold, indeed.  There are paths leading up from here to the east, northeast, and southwest.

nodes.s: You are following a small shadowed path.
nodes.l: ...a small difficult path.  This path appears to be perpetually hidden in shadow and darkness.  Even in the brightest of days, artifical light of some type is required to see in this area.  The mountains that loom overhead prevent much of the sun's light, and warmth, from reaching this part of the North Spires.  As a result, it is very cold.  A swirling mist is everpresent.  This path continues northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You have reached a dead end.
nodes.l: ...an ending to the pass.  You know that there is no way through the sheer rock that faces you, and you mumble to yourself as you force yourself around.  You know instictively that there are many such dead ends in the spires, and pray that you do not find every one on your travels.

nodes.s: You have reached a small overgrown cairn.
nodes.l: ...a vine-covered cairn.  Many rocks have been placed here as a marker of the death of some poor traveller or adventurer.  The name-plaque that is normally placed with such a cairn is long missing.  Vines completely cover this cairn.  The mountains are to the northeast of you.

nodes.s: You carefully tread this dangerous path.
nodes.l: ...a small difficult path.  The path that you tred upon is covered in small loose rocks which roll beneath your feet.  The footing on this path is difficult, and you are forced to pause regularly to regain your footing.  High in the mountains, you find it difficult to breathe.  This path continues to the north and southwest.
