nodes.s: You are standing in a clearing
nodes.l: ...an uprooted area.  This large clearing has been created by the uprooting of several trees and bushes.  The roots of the excavated trees stick out of the ground as evidence of the forceful removal of what once were mighty wooden trunks.  Thin stringy roots that once belonged to bushes stand destroyed.  Many claw marks can be seen in the ground.  A sense of awe and wonder eminates from the cavern that lies east of you.  A small path leads west away from here.

nodes.s: You are inside a large cavern.
nodes.l: ...a large cavern.  This large cavern has small piles of fur and scales along the edges.  Bones also line the edges of this cave.  Many claw marks are seen in the floor and walls, and a the stench of sulphur is prevalent here.  This cavern has a single exit to the west.

nodes.s: You are at the base of a spire.
nodes.l: ...a small valley.  You stand at the base of the mountain known as Mount Necros, named so because of the necropolis that has been built on the western side of the mountain.  This path spires around Mount Necros northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are on a flattened road.
nodes.l: ...a worked road.  The path here has been leveled and smoothed to make travel easier.  This path, which is at the base of Mount Necros, is wide and easy to travel.  It leads you northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are on a flattened road.
nodes.l: ...a worked road.  The path here has been leveled and smoothed to make travel easier.  This path, which is at the base of Mount Necros, is wide and easy to travel.  It leads you north, southeast, and southwest.

nodes.s: You are on a flattened road.
nodes.l: ...a worked road.  The path here has been leveled and smoothed to make travel easier.  This path, which is at the base of Mount Necros, is wide and easy to travel.  It leads you northeast and southwest.

nodes.l: ...a worked road.  The path here has been leveled and smoothed to make travel easier.  This path, which is at the base of Mount Necros, is wide and easy to travel.  It leads you south and northeast.

nodes.s: You are on a flattened road.
nodes.l: ...a worked road.  The path here has been leveled and smoothed to make travel easier.  This path, which is at the base of Mount Necros, is wide and easy to travel.  It leads you north and southeast.

nodes.s: You have entered the Spiral Cairns.
nodes.l: ...many mounds of rocks.  You have come unto the famous necropolis known as the Spiral Cairns.  This ancient burial ground is no longer used by the dwarves and is considered sacred by some.  Many of the naming plaques that are placed with the cairns are missing or faded being readability.  Dark clouds create shadows on the ground which seem to move with a life of their own.  A sense of forboding makes the hair on the back of your neck stand on end, and shivers occasionally travel up and down your spine.  A mist seems to be ever present in the Spiral Cairns.  They do not hide the paths which lead east, northwest, and southwest.

nodes.s: You have entered a small graveyard.
nodes.l: ...a small graveyard.  This area of the Cairns was used mainly by the other races, as the dwarves had already deigned their method of burial in the Cairns.  Many stakes in the ground mark the burial sites, though the names that were once carved in are faded with weather.  The dirt here is amazingly moist, yet free of any growth.  The only exit from the graveyard is back towards the cairns to the south.

nodes.s: You have entered a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing in the cairns.  As is custom in the dwarven burial custom, there is a patch of unused land in the middle of the cairns.  This area is considered to be the burial place of the Earth Father of dwarven religion, and as such it is forbidden to bury another here.  The great sense of forboding is strong here, and you can feel a great power hanging in the air.  The haze that is everpresent is thicker here, and there seems to be dark clouds perpetually above you here.  In the distance, you here the caw of a raven though you see no evidence of life anywhere nearby.  There are exits from this clearing to the south, northeast, and northwest.

nodes.s: You stand before a huge cairn.
nodes.l: ... a huge cairn.  This cairn which has been created using the largest of boulders towers over you.  The top of this cairn must be at least fifteen feet up, though its height is not easily determinable.  In the middle of the cairn face that you can see, there are rocks which have been discolored and have a tannish-brown tint to them.  The rocks of this cairn are unmovable, and the only way to leave this area is by returning to the clearing to the southeast.

nodes.s: You stand before an abandoned cairn.
nodes.l: ...an overgrown cairn.  The cairns found in the Spiral Cairns are seem to be well tended and cared for except for this one.  Strange glyphs have been placed around this cairn.  As you attempt to approach the cairn for a closer look, a strange blue barrier erects itself forbidding you passage.  It seems that the only thing for you to do is to return to the cairns to the northwest of here.

nodes.s: You are in a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...a huge clearing.  The trees here have been toppled by some unseen force, and the ground here has been literally ripped up from the foundation.  You contemplate what could have caused such damage while deciding whether you should do south, northeast, or northwest.

nodes.s: You are on deserted path.
nodes.l: ...a deserted path.  More destruction like the clearing is seen here.  Strong tall trees look like they were snapped like twigs, and the ground looks like it was cut through as if it were soft butter.  Long deep tracks have been ploughed into the ground by some undetermined force.  From here you may continue north or southeast.

nodes.s: You are walking in a rocky valley.
nodes.l: ...a rocky valley.  This depression is naturally formed.  The signs of many landfalls are evident, as there are huge boulders all about.  This valley may be travelled to the east or southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking in a rocky valley.
nodes.l: ...a rocky valley.  This depression is naturally formed.  The signs of many landfalls are evident, as there are huge boulders all about.  This valley may be travelled to the west, northeast, or southeast.

nodes.s: You have entered a small cave.
nodes.l: ...a small cave.  This cave, like many of the caves of the North Spiral Mountains, appears to be deserted.  Your experiences tell you that looks can be decieving, but you find it difficult to refut the evidence before you.  Trackless dirt on the floor, cobwebs on the ceiling, and vines that reach in from the outside all tell you that this cave is far too remote for any creatures to lair here for long.  The rear of the cave lies to the south, while the valley can be reached by travelling northwest.

nodes.s: You have entered the rear of the cave.
nodes.l: ...a small dark area.  This area, like the cave that leads to it, shows the classic signs of not being used often.  You notice nothing of any real interest.  The cave front is to the north.

nodes.l: ...a small dark area.  This area, like the cave that leads to it, shows the classic signs of not being used often.  You notice nothing of any real interest.  The cave front is to the northwest.

nodes.s: You are walking in a rocky valley.
nodes.l: ...a rocky valley.  This depression is naturally formed.  The signs of many landfalls are evident, as there are huge boulders all about.  This valley may be travelled to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking in a rocky valley.
nodes.l: ...a rocky valley.  This depression is naturally formed.  The signs of many landfalls are evident, as there are huge boulders all about.  This valley may be travelled to the east and southwest.

nodes.l: ...a rocky valley.  This depression is naturally formed.  The signs of many landfalls are evident, as there are huge boulders all about.  This valley may be travelled to the west and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  Several paths upon the valley floor meet here forming a small clearing.  The paths that lead from here all have a slight incline away from here.  In the distance, you can see the great ziggarat of Mount Fear.  This ziggarat is legendary, as it houses the lair of Mord, the Elder Minotaur.  The paths from here lead west, northwest, and southeast.

nodes.s: You walk along a desolate valley floor.
nodes.l: ...an overgrown path.  This path is dark and desolate.  Your footsteps are muffled by the overgrowth of this area.  Through the overgrowth you can feel the many rocks and pebbles that lie on the valley floor.  The thorns of the overgrowth tug at your outer garments while the path itself seems to make attempts to cause you to fall.  This path leads to the east and northwest.

nodes.s: You stand outside a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a cave entrance.  Through the growth, you can see that a large cave mouth is set into the mountain wall to the southwest.  You carefully wend your way along to investigate.  You may travel to the cave to the southwest or return to the overgrown path to the north.

nodes.s: You are inside a huge cavern.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  This cave is warmer than the surrounding area, though you cannot accurately detemine why.  The cave is dry and free of dust and cobwebs.  No real scent is here, so it is difficult to determine if this cave is the lair of some creature, and if it is, what type.  The only exit from this cave is to the northeast.

nodes.s: You are on a treacherous path.
nodes.l: ...a dangerous path.  This path is wide, but very steep.  To the west, the great spire of Mount Fear reaches high into the sky.  To the east, a smaller mount, but one of equal importance, can be seen.  The mountain to the east has been given the name Mount Dragonphyre after the family of drakes that have taken up there.  This path, however, leads to neither of these places, but travels to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You are on a treacherous path.
nodes.l: ...a crosspath.  The path at this point is very wide, and very flat.  A statue of a herald lies here with its hands outstretched in the universal sign of warning.  The statue wears a tunic which has the glyph of danger engraved upon it.  It is easy to determine the reasons for such a severe warning.  A path leads westward towards Mount Fear.  A path leads eastwards to Mount Dragonphyre.  A path leads southwestard to the rest of the North Spire Mountains.

This path leads east and west, directly to one of either mountains.

nodes.s: You are in a clearing.
nodes.l: ...a clearing.  You find yourself on one of the few clearings that has formed on Mount Dragonphyre.  This clearing is the home of the family of drakes from which this mountain derives its name.  You may leave this clearing only northwards; the rest of the mountain is unpassible.

nodes.s: You negotiate the path on Mount Fear.
nodes.l: ...a stepped path.  This great path looks like a large staircase has been carved out of the mountain side.  This huge carved staircase leads directly up Mount Fear.  Atop this large stepped staircase, overshadowing your path, is the great ziggarat.  This ziggarat holds the elder minataur and his lair, the Labyrinth of Fear.  Though smoothed and cleared, the incline makes this path nearly unnegotiable.  This path leads to the east and west.

nodes.s: You stand before a huge ziggurat.
nodes.l: ...the great Ziggarat of Fear.  This huge stepped pyramid looms above you.  Alone, it is the size of a small mountain.  Atop Mount Fear, it is a colassal work that strikes awe, and fear, into your heart.  Your heart pounds as you gaze upon the steps that lead to the great entrance.  On either side of the huge open expanse that leads within is a giant statue of a minataur standing prepared for battle.  Atop the ziggarat is another statue of a minataur wielding a halberd twice his size.  The shadow of the ziggaraut blots out all sunlight, and a howling breeze blows, causing shivers to creep up and down your spine.  Approaching the ziggaraut, you break out in a sweat as your footsteps echo throught the steps of the ziggarat like some deadly pulse.  Your mouth dries as you step forward.  The ziggarat stands ready to the east, adventurer; legends await within.

nodes.s: You have entered the gypsy encampment.
nodes.l: ...the entrance to the gypsy encampment.  Many tents have been staked into the ground, colorful flags wave in the wind from atop of them.  Many people bustle to and fro, many of them children carrying a package, or some other type of item.  Men dressed in flamboyant colors stand around chatting in a language foriegn to you; they eye you warily as you enter.  The smell of fresh cooked meet hangs in the air, and a sense of mystery fills you.  You may leave the encampment by going south, or continue north.

nodes.s: You are in the gypsy encampment.
nodes.l: ...the gypsy encampment.  You can't help but notice the many tents that are staked into the ground around you.  It is a wonder that these people have managed to remain as isolated as they are.  Children run gleefully about you as many men, apparently unarmed, glance over with a very watchful eye.  The camp exits to the south, or you may walk among the tents that lie to the north and southeast.

nodes.s: You are walking amidst many tents.
nodes.l: ...many tents staked to the ground.  You carefully tred a path that leads you amid many tents.  The path, narrow and twisty, reveals to you the fact that the gypsy camp has been here for quite some time.  Many people glance in your direction as you wend your way through the tents.  You may make your way northeast or southwest.

You may make your way southeast, or southwest.

nodes.s: There are many tents with colorful flags here.
nodes.l: ...several tents with unknown standards.  The tents around you have flags attached to the tops of them.  The flags flutter boldly in the wind and have heraldic markings that you have not seen before.  The colorful stories of gypsy princes and far away lands run through your mind as you gaze upon these tents.  The path you walk is weather beaten and travelling smooth.  Whatever the stories may say, these gypsies have been here for quite some time.  You may make your way around the tents by going north, northeast, or northwest.

nodes.s: You are standing in a small patch of woods.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing away from the tents.  A small gentleman comes out of the woods as you enter this clearing.  He is dressed in a dark green leather tunic, and wears two bracers to protect him from the damage that a misfired shot from his large bow could bring.  In addition to the long bow strapped to his back, he carries a sheathed short sword.  He carries on his shoulders a small barou, a large weasle like animal renown for its soft hide, and succulant meats.  He glances warily at you as you approach what he feels to be his territory.

nodes.s: You are walking on a small path.
nodes.l: ...a beaten path.  You leave the tents of the villiage to walk upon this small beaten dirt road.  This road has the signs of many years of passage, and is quite smooth.  Even on this path the uncanny feeling that you are being watched does not leave you.  You may continue to the north or south.

Even on this path the uncanny feeling that you are being watched does not leave you.  You may continue to the north or south.

nodes.s: You have entered a large tent.
nodes.l: ...a large general store.  This large tent holds many barrels with meats and skins.  In the center of the tent is a large steel showcase with various types skins and chain mail peices.  Two burly men stand before the case to insure that the case stays where it is.  The owner of these wares haggles softly with a child nearby.  The only exit from this tent is to the south.

nodes.s: You are walking on an overgrown path.
nodes.l: ...a path overgrown with weeds.  It is difficult to follow this path, as it is hidden beneath many weeds.  This path is obviously uncared for, and abandoned.  No tents are nearby, and you find yourself leaving the sounds of life behind you.  The hair on your next is on end, however, and you cannot seem to shake the feeling that you are being watched over.  You may continue north or southeast.

nodes.s: You stand outside a small wooden hut.
nodes.l: ...a small wooden hut.  You step out from the path to find a small clearing with a small wood hut before you.  The walls are formed of planked wood, while the cieling is made of thatch and mud.  A small closed door leads into this hut south of you, while the overgrown path is northwest of you.

nodes.s: You have entered the room of the gypsy puzzler.
nodes.l: ...the work place of the puzzler.  Puzzles of many types, jigsaw, ironworks, and slight of hand puzzles, are neatly displayed on many shelves here.  In a small chair on the far side of this room is a small figure fiinishing one of the ironwork puzzles.  He smiles gently at you as you enter his domain.  The door leading out of this hut is north of you.

nodes.s: You walk a path between many tents.
nodes.l: ...many tents staked to the ground.  You carefully tred a path that leads you amid many tents.  The path, narrow and twisty, reveals to you the fact that the gypsy camp has been here for quite some time.  Many people glance in your direction as you wend your way through the tents.  You may make your way south or northwest.

nodes.s: You find yourself in a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  This clearing has a fire pit centered in it.  It seems to be some type of central meeting place for those that live in the villiage.  Gyspy villiagers glance at you as you pass by.  There are paths from this clearing to the northeast, northwest, and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  Holes in the ground which used to hold stakes show that this clearing is the result of tents that have been moved.  Trees grow tall around this clearing, and you feel a sense of serenity here.  The path to the northwest of here barely recieves any light from the sun; many tall trees throw their shadows onto the path.  A larger clearing is seen to the northeast.

nodes.s: You stand in a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...Several men laugh heartily at several people that have been trapped by there nets while one of the men begins to set them free.  A small group is seen examining the settings of the trap while an older gentle appears to be explaining the aspects of trap setting to them.  You hear a sharp twang as another person is caught in one of these traps.  You may leave this clearing by stepping carefully southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking on a shaded path.
nodes.l: ...a path with many shadows.  Many tall trees grow about this well kept path.  The shadows that the trees throw onto the path makes this path seem very eerie, indeed.  The sensation that there are people hidden around you is unshakable, and you always think that you can see someone just out of the corner of your eye.  You may continue to the north or southeast.

nodes.l: ...a path with many shadows.  Many tall trees grow about this well kept path.  The shadows that the trees throw onto the path makes this path seem very eerie, indeed.  The sensation that there are people hidden around you is unshakable, and you always think that you can see someone just out of the corner of your eye.  You may continue to the northwest or southeast.

nodes.s: You stand before a small black tent.
nodes.l: ...a small dark tent.  Through the shadow, it is difficult to see the small dark tent that has been erected among the trees.  No clearing has been made around the tent, which makes it that much more difficult to see.  No sound can be heard coming from the tent, nor any motion seen.  A small black standard with a dark grey key flys from the top of the tent.  The path leads you back south.

nodes.s: You have reached the gypsy locksmaster.
nodes.l: ...a darkened tent.  The gypsy locksmith uses no torches or lamps of any type in his tent, and appears to be perfectly at home with the darkness that surrounds him and his home.  Peices of  a complex lock sit on a table with many small tags identifying the lock parts.  The locksmith shifts uncomfortably in your presence.

nodes.s: You are at a gypsy checkpoint.
nodes.l: ...a checkpoint.  Several men garbed in colorful clothes stand here.  Armed with long swords, thse gentlemen where courballi which has been polished until you can almost see a reflection in the leather.  They glance harshly in your direction as they watch you walk through the brush that hides this particular road from prying eyes.  While this hidden path continues to the southeast, you may return to the main village by going northwest.

nodes.s: You walk down Gypsy Road.
nodes.l: ...a well kept road.  This road has been covered with a thin clay layer which makes it almost perfectly smooth.  This road is kept brushed and free of debree.  In the clay, some marking has been fired into it, thoug the marking is completely foreign to you.  This road leads you northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You stand before a large pavilion.
nodes.l: ...a large pavilion.  The sounds of clashing steel comes from the pavilion south of you, and a large banner hangs above the pavilion.  You notice that the marks in the ground are similiar to the standard of the banner above the tent.  You recognize that the standard is that of some gypsy noble (though he would claim to be prince, of course).  You may walk the long road back to the villiage northward, or continue into the pavilion southward.

nodes.s: You have entered a large training center.
nodes.l: ...a brightly lit pavilion.  Many gypsies are seen here practicing many of their skills.  Two (two!) Gypsy Nobles haggle prices with many of the others here, while a third practices combat with several of the younger gypsies.  Four banners hang from the ceiling of this huge tent.  Three of these banners are the personal flags of the lords that are present.  The fourth standard is unknown to you.  This pavilion is filled with a sense of life that rivals the life in Imperial City.  The only exit from this pavilion is to the north.

nodes.s: You are on a small path.
nodes.l: ...a small natural path.  This small dirt road is the result of many years of travellers.  Small bushes have been grown on either side of this path to give it a more aestetic feel to it.  This path leads you north and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  Several small paths meet here to form a small clearing.  Many standing torches have been placed in this clearing to help light it at night.  Paths lead from here to the northwest, northeast, and south.

nodes.s: You are walking a lit path.
nodes.l: ...a lit path.  Many standing lanterns have been placed here, and are lit constantly, even during the day.  The path that you are walking on has several horseshoes imbedded into it.  This path leads you southeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking a lit path.
nodes.l: ...a lit path.  Many standing lanterns have been placed here, and are lit constantly, even during the day.  The path that you are walking on has several horseshoes imbedded into it.  This path leads you northeast and northwest.

nodes.s: You have entered a small smithy.
nodes.l: ...a small smithy.  A small anvil sits in front of forge.  Several clay molds are stacked carefully on the far wall.  Several children work carefully on small swords and daggers.  An older gentleman points out there mistakes and assists them with their hammer strokes.  You may exit the smithy to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking a small overgrown path.
nodes.l: ...a small path covered in weeds.  Slightly overgrown, this path is falling into disrepair.  Though still smooth because of the many years of passage, small weeds and ivy have begun growing about the path which leads north and southeast.

nodes.s: You are walking a small overgrown path.
nodes.l: ...a small path covered in weeds.  Slightly overgrown, this path is falling into disrepair.  Though still smooth because of the many years of passage, small weeds and ivy have begun growing about the path which leads south and northwest.

nodes.s: You have entered a small encampment.
nodes.l: ...a small encampment.  This area is some type of elite area, as it is set off from the rest of the encampment.  Several people interrupt their conversation to watch you carefully as you enter this encampment.  Though there are only a few of them, you get the instincual impression that many more are around.  You may leave this encampment by going southeast.

nodes.s: You find your way through the trees.
nodes.l: ...an overgrowth of trees.  Many tall trees grow among many vines and bushes.  Tall bushes prevent your passage, and the many vines and underbrush prevent any hope of blazing a trail.  You sense of direction is confused, as the trees hide the sky.  A sense of frustration overcomes you as you find yourself in an area with no path leading from it.

nodes.s: You have entered a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  You hear the sounds of laughter about you as a small elf gyspy steps out of the tree cover.  He smiles at you as he bows before quickly darting back into the woods.  You know that he is still around, and probably watching you, however.  There are no exits apparent from here, but you believe that you could probably work your way back the way you came.

nodes.s: You have entered the Elder Chamber.
nodes.l: ...the Astral Plane.  From here, you gather much of the essence and store it deep within you for later use.  Quickly, you know that it is best for you to return to the Realms of Corinthia, lest evil win the day.

nodes.s: You are walking on a well paved street.
nodes.l: ...a well paved street.  This town has road that are kept meticulous by its people.  Clean and well-maintained, this road leads you north into town, or south back to the mountains.

nodes.s: You are at an intersection.
nodes.l: ...a well paved intersection.  Small signs reveal that this is where Main Road and Training Street meet.  While travelled greatly, both of these streets are kept in excellent condition.  Main Road leads northeast from here while Training Street leads north.

nodes.s: You are walking on Training Street.
nodes.l: ...the cleansliness of Training Street.  This street, like the others within Spalango Township, is kept incredibly clean by its peoples.  Many lamp posts have been placed on the sides of the streets so that even in the darkest of nights, this street is well lit.  Small banners hang from the lamp posts.  The banners, which are all red in background, have silver and gold thread which is stitched into scenes of battle and triumph.  This street leads you north an south.

nodes.s: You stand before Spalango Hall.
nodes.l: ...a large building.  You are on Training Street, and presently stand before the large building which is known as the Spalango Township's Guild.  This guildhall is more than a place for simple training, however.  The halflings and other inhabitants of the town use the guildhall as their main hall and town square.  You may enter the guild to the north, or you may follow Training Street southward.

nodes.s: You have entered Spalango Township's Guild.
nodes.l: ...Spalango Hall.  A large sign which hangs from the cieling proclaims this building to be named Spalango Hall.  A small statue of Spalango, a diminutive yet impressive halfling, is centered in the grand hall.  Many people practice with their weapons in the training circles at the far end of the hall, and a small booth shop has also been set up within the hall.  The single exit from Spalango Hall is to the south.

nodes.s: You walk along Main Road.
nodes.l: ...an excessively clean street.  This street has been paved with white brick, and it is kept very clean by the inhavitants of this town.  The mud of your shoes seem to melt right off the stone of the pavement, and not even dust seems capable of settling on this street.  Signs attached to the many posts proclaim this to be Main Road.  From the amount of traffic along this street, it is easy to believe that this is, indeed, their main road.

nodes.l: ...a large intesection.  Though the inhabitants of this town are practical geniouses when it comes to managing clean streets, you realize that they are very unimaginative when it comes to street names.  A small signposts announces this to be the intesectin of Main Road and Side Street.  While Main Road runs north and south, Side Street runs east from here.

nodes.s: You find yourself on Side Street.
nodes.l: ...that you are travelling a clean street.  While this street is called Side Street, it recieves almost as much traffic as Main Road.  Lampposts shine with amazing brightness, and the ground seems to reflect the light.  Side Street continues to the east and west.

nodes.s: Runners Way and Side Street intersect here.
nodes.l: ...a clean intesection.  Two streets meet here to form a 'T'.  Side Streeet, which runs westward from here, and Runners Alley which runs north and south from here.

nodes.s: You stride down Runners Way.
nodes.l: ...a long strip of clean, flat road.  Runners Alley has been smoothed over and cleaned, much as most of Spalango Township has been.  Small banners hang from the many lampposts of this alley.  Pictures sown into the banners show races in its various stages.  Small horseshoe have been staked to either side of the work ground here, sybolizing a nearby blacksmith or armoror.

nodes.s: You have reached the end of Runners Way.
nodes.l: ...the end of the road.  Runners Alley ends here.  While a great expanse of land lies to the south of here, the large fence indicates that it is, indeed, private property.  The only exit from here is north, to the rest of Runners Alley.

nodes.s: You are walking along an unpaved road.
nodes.l: ...an unpaved road.  Unlike the rest of Spalango Township which is nearly septically clean, the area that you are in now boasts a dirt road, few lighting posts, and no worked areas of road at all.  The only reason that this road is smooth, you gather, is because of the travel that must be present.  Trees are all about you to further disguise this area.  You may continue east back to Runners Alley, or you may travel further west.

nodes.s: You are walking along an unpaved road.
nodes.l: ...an unpaved road.  Unlike the rest of Spalango Township which is nearly septically clean, the area that you are in now boasts a dirt road, few lighting posts, and no worked areas of road at all.  The only reason that this road is smooth, you gather, is because of the travel that must be present.  Trees are all about you to further disguise this area.  You may continue east or west here.

nodes.s: You are in a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small natural clearing.  The trees seem to bend in various directions to create this clearing.  Many bushes and vines grow in this area, though you can see a path that has been blazed south of here.  A small resting station lies to the north of here.

nodes.s: You are standing at a dead end.
nodes.l: ...a small resting station.  Several boulders have been placed in a horseshoe shape here to rest upon.  The form of the semi-circle choses so that groups of travellers can sit together and converse here.  A small clearing lies south of here.

nodes.s: You have entered Hanson's sanctuary.
nodes.l: ...a small hidden clearing.  This area is usually well hidden from prying eyes, and this is just the way that Hanson likes it.  Many swinging targets swing from trees, and you can see a fairly large halfling, as well as a small child, running around these targets avoiding them as they swing them towards one another.  The larger of the two rolls out of the range of these targets to stand before you.  He introduces himself as Hanson Older.

nodes.s: You have entered the rear of Hanson's sanctuary.
nodes.l: ...a larger clearing.  You are startled when you enter this area as a small halfling steps out of the foilage to greet you.  He eyes you warily, though he greets you warmly enough.

nodes.s: You walk upon a beaten path.
nodes.l: ...a path beat into the woods.  Many of the weeds here have been cut away, and plants have been trampled underfoot to force this path into existance.  Thin and dark, this path leads you north and south.

nodes.s: You enter Iabo's Locksmithy.
nodes.l: ...a locksmiths shop.  Several wooden doors lean against the walls of this shop, all without locks, though some have been fitted with lock holders.  Many polished chests of oak and stronger materials sit against another wall, all with shiny new locks.  Iabo sits a desk with several mechanical impliments which are used to make the locks that he is so proud of.

nodes.s: You have entered Iabo's back room.
nodes.l: ...a barren room.  Iabo's backroom looks much like an abandoned warehouse.  Crates line the walls and create a labyrinth like path through the room.  The only exit is back west to Iabo's workshop.

nodes.s: You walk along Main Road.
nodes.l: ...an excessively clean street. This street has been paved with white brick, and it is kept very clean by the inhavitants of this town.  The mud of your shoes seem to melt right off the stone of the pavement, and not even dust seems capable of settling on this street.  Signs attached to the many posts proclaim this to be Main Road.  From the amount of traffic along this street, it is easy to believe that this is, indeed, their main road.

nodes.s: You are at a crossroads.
nodes.l: ...a large intersection.  Two large roads intersect here, forming a large intersection.  A signpost has been erected in the middle of this intersection to give travellers and visitors direction.  Arena Alley runs northeast and southwest here, while Main Road runs northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You step towards the mercenaries guild.
nodes.l: ...an excessively clean street. This street has been paved with white brick, and it is kept very clean by the inhavitants of this town.  The mud of your shoes seem to melt right off the stone of the pavement, and not even dust seems capable of settling on this street.  Signs attached to the many posts proclaim this to be Main Road.  From the amount of traffic along this street, it is easy to believe that this is, indeed, their main road.

nodes.s: You stand outside an abandoned building.
nodes.l: ...a large abandoned building.  A faded sign indicates that this building was once the home of the Spalango Mercenaries Guild.  It was here that travellers would hire other adventurers to protect them through the dangerous paths of the mountains.  The mercenaries guiild has long since closed, however, with the rise of the evils that have plagued this part of Corinthia.

nodes.s: You walk down Arena Alley.
nodes.l: ...a large, well-maintained street.  This street is much like the rest of Spalango Township, that is to say that it is clean beyond belief.  Well placed lamppost light your way as you travel down Arena Alley.

nodes.s: You stand outside Uvil Arena.
nodes.l: ...a large circular wall.  This wall confines Uvil Arena from the rest of the town.  Inside this arena, one of the great arena masters summons combatants for those that would hone their skill at arms.

nodes.s: You are in Uvil Arena.
nodes.l: ...the vastness of Uvil Arena.  Near the door entrance hangs a great brass gong that is held up by two large staffs that have been treated with dragon blood to insure their longevity.  An arena master, dressed in black robes, stands by the gong, ready to summon for those that are brave enough to bring forth its mighty toll.

nodes.s: You walk on Arena Alley.
nodes.l: ...a large, well-maintained street.  This street is much like the rest of Spalango Township, that is to say that it is clean beyond belief.  Well placed lamppost light your way as you travel down Arena Alley.

nodes.l: ...a large, well-maintained street.  This street is much like the rest of Spalango Township, that is to say that it is clean beyond belief.  Well placed lamppost light your way as you travel down Arena Alley.

nodes.s: You are at a large intersection.
nodes.l: ...a large intersection.  Two large roads intersect here, forming a large intersection.  A signpost has been erected in the middle of this intersection to give travellers and visitors direction.  Healthgate Avenue runs northeast and southwest here, while Arena Alley runs northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You walk on Arena Alley.
nodes.l: ...a large, well-maintained street.  This street is much like the rest of Spalango Township, that is to say that it is clean beyond belief.  Well placed lamppost light your way as you travel down Arena Alley.

nodes.s: You stand outside Exile Arena.
nodes.l: ...the great barrier of Exile Arena.  The wall here is made of obsidian, and a great ivory gate leads to the inner area of Exile Arena.  Within, powerful creatures are summoned for those that feel that discretion may not necessarily be the better part of valor.

nodes.s: You stand within Exile Arena.
nodes.l: ...the great chamber of Exile Arena.  No arena master mans the great gong that is held up by obsidian holders, as this arena has been treated with magicks of old.  A ring of the this great gong made from the heart of a great dragonbeast summons mighty creatures to the arena.  Woe unto those that ring this gong without being prepared!

nodes.s: You walk along Healthgate Avenue.
nodes.l: ...a golden runed street.  This street has been made of the same white, ivory-like material that cover most of the other roads.  This road also has many golden glyphs insribed on the edges of the road.  These glyphs give off enough light to see by, so this road does not need the lampposts that are so plentiful in the rest of the town.

nodes.l: ...a golden runed street.  This street has been made of the same white, ivory-like material that cover most of the other roads.  This road also has many golden glyphs insribed on the edges of the road.  These glyphs give off enough light to see by, so this road does not need the lampposts that are so plentiful in the rest of the town.

nodes.s: You stand outside a temple.
nodes.l: ...a great temple.  This great stone building has been enhanced with great ivory plaques which have prayers inscribed in gold.  Like many of the temples in Corinthia, this one is dedicated to Myias, the healer.

nodes.s: You have entered a temple dedicated to Myiras.
nodes.l: ...that you have entered a huge prayer room.  Acolytes walk patiently through the mass of petitioners that are within this temple.  Layhealers walk among those that have been injured healing the wounds of those that ask of them this small favor.  Great candles burn continuously on the alter, and the censer remains ever lit with its oderous smoke being emitted.

nodes.s: You walk along Healthgate Avenue.
nodes.l: ...a golden runed street.  This street has been made of the same white, ivory-like material that cover most of the other roads.  This road also has many golden glyphs insribed on the edges of the road.  These glyphs give off enough light to see by, so this road does not need the lampposts that are so plentiful in the rest of the town.

nodes.s: You are at a large intersection.
nodes.l: ...one of the many intersections of Spalango Township.  These streets, while not very wide, are easily travelled.  They are swept, cleaned, and scrubbed on a regular basis.  The halfling capability for detail is evident by looking at these smoothed streets.  Even the dirt around the worked roads is even and cultivated.  To the north lies Littlefoot Path, Dirt Road is southwest of you, and southeast brings you to Healthgate Avenue.

nodes.s: You are walking on Littlefoot Path.
nodes.l: ...a small, thin road.  This road is worked much like the rest of Spalango Township.  An ivory colored clay has been smooted a small path in the dirt, and then polished to perfection.  To either side of the road is the natural dirt of the area, but this, too, has been raked and smoothed over.  Small bushes grow on either side of the road, and you feel very comfortable walking within this town.  Littlefoot Path extends northward from here, and meets with an intersection to the south.

nodes.s: You are walking on Littlefoot Path.
nodes.l: ...a small, thin road.  This road is worked much like the rest of Spalango Township.  An ivory colored clay has been smooted a small path in the dirt, and then polished to perfection.  To either side of the road is the natural dirt of the area, but this, too, has been raked and smoothed over.  Small bushes grow on either side of the road, and you feel very comfortable walking within this town.  Littlefoot Path extends north and south from here.

Small bushes grow on either side of the road, and you feel very comfortable walking within this town.  Littlefoot Path extends north and south from here.

nodes.s: You are at a small intersection.
nodes.l: ...a thin intersection.  This area of the township is not often visited by those other than the occupants.  This is evident by the small thin roads that are prevalent here.  While created with the same eye for detail that the halflings are known for, the roads here are considerably thinner.  While Littlefoot Path extends north and south from here, Seref Way extends east.

nodes.s: You stand before a wooden fence.
nodes.l: ...the fence leading to Spalango Park.  A large wooden fence has been erected here.  Its purpose is as much to prevent unauthorized entrance as it is to keep the animals within from escaping.  The huge park that lies beyond this fence is a wonderful place to visit.  Hunting within the park is available only to those with license.

nodes.s: You have entered a large park.
nodes.l: ...a large park.  The park here is quite well maintained.  Great pains have been gone through to insure that this park maintains its natural feel.  How the halflings of this villiage manage to put so much work into the park without ruining the natural feel of the area is a mystery.  In the distance, you can see creatures running through trees.  A ranger station is nearby for those that wish to enter the park to extend their knowledge of hunting.  You may exit the park to the south.

nodes.s: You stride down Seraf Way.
nodes.l: ...a small street.  Seref Way shows the same attention to perfection as the rest of the streets of this town, although it is quite smaller.  Seref Way continues east and west from here.

nodes.s: You stride down Seraf Way.
nodes.l: ...a small street.  Seref Way shows the same attention to perfection as the rest of the streets of this town, although it is quite smaller.  Seref Way continues east and west from here.

nodes.s: The corner of Seraf Way and Steele Street.
nodes.l: ...a street corner.  The thinness of Seref Way seems out of place here, where it meets Steele Street.  Steel Street is made much the same as the other streets, with its clay topping.  Steele Street, however, is outlined with a wide band of polished steel.  The outline is of a universal width, and is polished to reflect light.  Steel Street extends north, while Seref Way may be taken west.

nodes.s: You are walking on Steele Street.
nodes.l: ...the greatness of Steele Street.  This street is wide and open.  To either side of this street lies a three inch band of steel that has been molded into the ground to delimit the boundaries of this street.  The lights from the lampposts set here glimmer off of this band of steel that has been polished to near perfection.  Steele Street runs north and south here.

nodes.s: The corner of Steele St. and Woodward Street.
nodes.l: ...a contrast of ideas.  The banded section of Steele Street meets with the picketed area of Woodward Street.  These two boudary markers clash, but clash in such a way as to make you awed by the great skills of the halflings of this villiage.  From the most basic of works, to the most complex of works, the makers of this town were quite proficient.  Steele Street leads to the armsmaster north, while Woodward Street continues west.

nodes.l: ...the greatness of Steele Street.  This street is wide and open.  To either side of this street lies a three inch band of steel that has been molded into the ground to delimit the boundaries of this street.  The lights from the lampposts set here glimmer off of this band of steel that has been polished to near perfection.  Steele Street runs north and south here.

nodes.s: You have entered the Armsmasters Shop.
nodes.l: ...a great array of weapons.  Many barrels line the walls, and they are filled with daggers, standing swords, and many other types of weapons.  The store is clean and looks more like a house that happens to be selling weapons, rather than a store itself.  The door from the armsmaster lies to the south.

nodes.s: You follow Woodward Street.
nodes.l: ...a street boundaried by a picket fence.  To either side of this street, a tall picket fence has been erected.  The fence has been finished with a sharp rust color, and has been shillacked with a smooth, shiny substance.  The fences glow with the lights of the streets, and come close to reflecting your visages.  Woodsward Street meets Steele Street east of here, and continues to the west.

nodes.s: You follow Woodward Street.
nodes.l: ...a street boundaried by a picket fence.  To either side of this street, a tall picket fence has been erected.  The fence has been finished with a sharp rust color, and has been shillacked with a smooth, shiny substance.  The fences glow with the lights of the streets, and come close to reflecting your visages.

The fences glow with the lights of the streets, and come close to reflecting your visages.

The fences glow with the lights of the streets, and come close to reflecting your visages.

nodes.s: You are at a small intersection.
nodes.l: ...a small intersection.  This is the area that the inhabitants of the town usuallly refer to as "shops way".  The two areas that extend from here are not boundaried by the picket fence, indicating that this is the end, proper, of Woodward Street.  No names have been attached to the two areas that lead from here, however.  Since these shops seem to be fairly recent additions to the town, no names have been given to their extensions.  You may travel north or west to one of the shops, or eastward along Woodward Street.

nodes.s: You follow Woodward Street.
nodes.l: ...a small thin street.  While the dirt of this street has been smoothed and boundaried with small bushes and trees, it is nothing compared to the majestry of the rest of Spalango Township.  You see a small wooden building west of here.  A sign indicates that is the home of the local fletcher.

nodes.s: You stand outside Mark's Fletching Shop.
nodes.l: ...a small wooden building.  A small sign hangs from above the door.  It depicts a small man kneeling while drawing a bow.  The home of the fletcher may be entered west.

nodes.s: You have entered Mark's Fletching Shop.
nodes.l: ...the main room of the building.  The main room of this building has been converted into a shop for arrows, and bows of different types.  A tall human whittles at a piece of wood that will eventually become a bow.  He discontinues his actions and looks up expectingly at you as you enter.

nodes.s: You walk down Boxers Alley
nodes.l: ...a small handcrafted signpost.  The signpost indicates that this street is named Boxers Alley, at least by those that put up the sign.  Small and smooth, this street is not capped in the same white clay that the rest of the city has been.  A large stone building far to the north from here.

nodes.s: You stand before the Hall of Yulis.
nodes.l: ...a large stone building.  A large plaque above the double doors reveals this to be The Hall of Yulis, but no indication of just what the hall is for is given.  The entrance to the Hall of Yulis is north, while Boxers Alley is south of here.

nodes.s: You have entered the Hall of Yulis.
nodes.l: ...the great hall.  You are in awe at the size of this great room.  The cieling towers over you, and in the center of the room, a huge giant gives out fighting instructions to those that are around him.  He matches up trainees as sparring partners, and gives them pointers as they practice unarmed combat.  Yulis gazes over his students at you as you enter; you can sense a great wisdom in his eyes.

nodes.s: You walk down Dirt Road.
nodes.l: ...an uncovered street.  The halflings have left this one road of their town free of the white clay that is so prolific elsewhere to remind them of their past.  Dirt Road, however, is still very well kept.  Trees and bushes bearing flowers line this small path which leads you northeast or southwest.

nodes.s: Dirt Road and Wizards Lane intersect here.
nodes.l: ...a small intersection.  Southwest of you lies a paved street.  A small signpost indicates that Wizards Lane runs northeast and southwest here.  Dirt Road lies to the northeast and extends from there.

nodes.s: You wend your way down Wizards Lane.
nodes.l: ...a great paved street.  This street is capped with a smooth white clay surface that seems to reflect light.  Great silver glyphs have been inscribed down the center of this road.  They give off a bright blue light even during the day.  The glyphs, obviously magic, give this street an awe-inspiring sense to it.  Wizards Lane continues to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You wend your way down Wizards Lane.
nodes.l: ...a great paved street.  This street is capped with a smooth white clay surface that seems to reflect light.  Great silver glyphs have been inscribed down the center of this road. nodes.s: You stand before a large tower.
nodes.l: ...that you stand before a large tower.  The tower that stands before attempts to reach into the sky, though it falls far short of its goal.  Almost perfectly circular, you can't help but notice that there are no windows in this tower.  Above the entrance which is southwest of you is a huge sign that literally floats.  In great glowing letters, the sign announces this to be Shea Tower.

nodes.s: You have entered The Tower of Shea.
nodes.l: ...the vastness of the Tower of Shae.  This tower is named after the great mage that built this tower and still resides within it.  Great staircases lead upward to other levels, and while you didn't see any windows from the outside, portals are clearly visible now that you are within the building.  To the south is a door with guards to either side.  Above the door are glyphs inscibed in the air announcing that this room is for other those of the mage caste only.

nodes.s: You are deep in the halls of Shea Tower.
nodes.l: ...a large laboratory.  You have walked deep into the halls of Shea Tower, and can feel the great power held within this workshop.  Tomes far older than you line these walls, and many students of the craft pour meticulously through them.  Behind a clear barrier, other practitoners attempt some of the spells that they have just learned.  The rest of Shea Tower is north of you.

nodes.s: You have entered the antechamber.
nodes.l: ...the antechamber of the temple.  Many priests sit here in hopes that their prayers will lead them to the guidence that they need to discover the weaknesses of the evils around them, and their cause.  You can smell the heavy incense that burns continuously in this room, and are filled with inspired wisdom.  It is here that Myias shares some of her greatest secrets.

nodes.s: You are walking on Glitter Street.
nodes.l: ...a glitterglow street.  The most recent addition to Spalango Township, this street is made of the same glitterglow that is found in other, larger, cities.  The halflings give glitterglow a new life, though, with the shine that only they can seem to bring from it.  Glitter Street is appropiately named, and runs northeast from here.

nodes.l: ...a glitterglow street.  The most recent addition to Spalango Township, this street is made of the same glitterglow that is found in other, larger, cities. nodes.s: You are at an intersection.
nodes.l: ...a great intersection.  The glitterglow that makes up the street here is exteremly polished and bright here.  The glowing substance of the ground makes the very air seem to be filled with little sparkling motes of light.  A signpost has been erected in the center of this intersection, and the pointers have been coated with the same glitterglow of the ground.  Great letters inscribed in the wood indicate that Chambers Street runs northwest and southeast from here.  The great School of Thought is northwest, while the School of Introspection is southeast.  Shana's School of Etiquette lies to the northeast.

nodes.s: You have entered Shana's School of Etiquette.
nodes.l: ...a great classroom.  In this room, a small shapely elf gives instructions of etiquette and beuty here.  There are other rooms further into the school, with various teachers giving lessons on the different aspects of interaction with others.  You carefully perpare your payments for whatever lessons you feel would best suit you.  You may leave Shana's School of Etiquette by returning southwest.

nodes.s: You walk along Chambers Street.
nodes.l: ...that you are walking along a great, cleaned, glittering street.  This street almost overwhelms your senses as you walk along it with its glittering, glowing properties.  Small motes of light dance before you, and you find your concentration wane as you continue along this path.  Chambers Street continues to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You stand outside The School of Introspection.
nodes.l: ...a great monestary.  What is commonly called the School of Introspection is a large monestary where a person comes to look deep within their own hearts for insight.  The entrance to the school is covered with a thick curtain.  There is no door, as all are welcome to enter its sanctuary.

nodes.s: You have entered the School of Introspection.
nodes.l: ...a large meditation area.  Many people sit in various forms of relaxation as they meditate and pray.  There are no instructors here, as here the belief is that the best teacher is the guide within.  The curtain covered exit is northeast of you.

nodes.s: You stand outside the School of Thought.
nodes.l: ...a large academy.  This large building holds books of knowledge and gives courses on study and the realm.  Only those willing to pay a great tuition are permitted to learn of the secrets within, however.

nodes.s: You have entered the School of Thought.
nodes.l: ...a great acadamic hall.  Lecture halls surround you, many of them of use.  A great library is accessible here, as well, for those that are able to use them.  Research of all manners are in progress within these halls.  You may exit this academians haven by going southwest.

nodes.s: You creep into the sheriff's office.
nodes.l: This large room is rather plain and, save for a small desk towards the back, is entirely empty.  A large closed iron door leads off to the west and is labeled "Authorized personnel only".  A deputy sits idly behind the desk flippping through random piles of paperwork all the while keeping a watchful eye over your actions.  A sign on the wall indicates that one may pay off criminal fines at this location.

nodes.s: You have climbed the large oak tree.
nodes.l: ...a glorious view from above.  You are given a majestic view of the area around.  You can see the tall spire of the Wizards Mount in Imperial City even from here, though the foilage below prevents you from getting a clear view of any other details of the land.  The branches beneath you seem to twist about themselves, supporting even your weight with ease.  While many branches hang about you, a single branch calls to your attention.  It is slightly discolored, and seems to be smoother than the rest.  Its foilage appears to be greater than the branches about it, almost as if it were unnatrually grown.

nodes.s: You have entered the Spalango Gem Shop
nodes.l: ...many gems on display.  This small hovel is cramped and dark.  The only light comes from a single glowstone that has been attached to the cieling.  Many glass-type shelves hold several gems of different types upon them.  A single gnome sits in a chair in the corner ready to perform any trades that you so desire.

nodes.s: You are in the catacombs.
nodes.l: These catacombs are ancient, yet well kept and clean  The darkness that was about you is ever present here, giving you a sense of foreboding and expectation.  Exits lead to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are at the bottom of a circular staircase.
nodes.l: You are at the bottom of a strange circular staircase.  The staircase appears to be made entirely of bone.  The shadows that dance upon this staircase make it seem alive.  The only other exit from this room is to the north.

nodes.s: You are in the catacombs.
nodes.l: Your light source is dim, but gives off enough light for you to see.  Every few feet you notice that there is a plaque on the wall with some strange inscription. Although unable to read the ancient language, you surmise that these plaques are akin to headstones.  An eerie feeling comes ofver you as you realize just how many of the heroes of old are buried within these walls.  The tombs continue to the north; the room to the south has a bone staircase that leads upwards.

Although unable to read the ancient language, you surmise that these plaques are akin to headstones.  An eerie feeling comes ofver you as you realize just how many of the heroes of old are buried within these walls.  The tombs continue to the west, east, and south.

nodes.s: You have entered the labyrinth.
nodes.l: ...a path into the ziggaraut.  You have descended deep into the ziggaraut that is atop Mount Fear.  The walls to either side of you are cut stone.  To either side you can see the images of minotaurs at various tasks cut in bas relief in the walls.  You may continue into this underground mystery by walking north.  You may leave this place of fear by returning upwards.

nodes.s: You have entered a labyrinth.
nodes.l: ...a long passageway.  This passageway has the same minotaurs in bas relief as the entrance to this place does.  The lights you bear make the shadows seem to dance and the carvings come alive.  North or south are your choices from here.

nodes.s: You have entered a labyrinth.
nodes.l: ...a long passageway.  This passageway has the same minotaurs in bas relief as the entrance to this place does.  The lights you bear make the shadows seem to dance and the carvings come alive.  North or south are your choices from here.

nodes.s: You have entered a labyrinth.
nodes.l: ...a confusing labyrinth.  The walls here have strange sigils carved upon them while the rest of the area is bare.  You notice that the sigils are in a repeating pattern and have been designed to give you a small sense of vertigo.  You find it difficult to maintain your bearings as you walk down this corridor.

nodes.s: You are in a hall of statues.
nodes.l: ...a great hall with statues.  This corridor is apparently some type of memorial to the many heroes that have passed through the Labyrinth of Fear, though who would keep such a memorial within the labyrinth remains a mystery.  Great statues of heroes in various poses of combat and defense line either side of this wall.

nodes.s: You are in a large stone room.
nodes.l: ...a large statue centered in the room.  The walls here, like the walls of the other areas that you have passed, are graven with many undecipherable glyphs.  A huge stone door is centered on the southwest wall.  The wall has a whole in the middle of it that is fairly deep.  Images of medusa heads surround the hole.  The rest of the room is barren.

nodes.s: You are in a huge room.

nodes.s: You have entered a labyrinth.
nodes.l: ...a confusing labyrinth.  The walls here have strange sigils carved upon them while the rest of the area is bare. nodes.s: You are in a gigantic cavern.
nodes.l: ...a large cavern in the labyrinth.  This cavern is much larger than the other caverns that you've encountered while within this layer of the labyrinth.  A thick metal ring is attached to a stone door set in the floor.  With the exception of this feature, the room is barren.

nodes.s: You are in the tombs.
nodes.l: Your light source is dim, but gives off enough light for you to see.  Every few feet you notice that there is a plaque on the wall with some strange inscription. Although unable to read the ancient language, you surmise that these plaques are akin to headstones.  An eerie feeling comes ofver you as you realize just how many of the heroes of old are buried within these walls.  The tombs continue to the west and east.

You notice that the sigils are in a repeating pattern and have been designed to give you a small sense of vertigo.  You find it difficult to maintain your bearings as you walk down this corridor.

nodes.s: You are in a dark twisting labyrinth.
nodes.l: ...a brightly lit room.  The strange sigils that adorn the walls in therest of the labyrinth are present on these walls, thought the monotony of these disorienting runes is broken by a large torch sconce on the wall.  The sconce holds no torch, though, and the cobwebs in the sconcereflect that no torch has been held by this sconce for ages.  Strangly enough, there are no webs hanging from the sconce where the wall and thesconce conenct.  In fact, the wall around the sconce looks strangly smooth.
nodes.quest_text: move sconce ... You manage to move the torch sconce! ... %s pulls heftily on the torch sconce! ... %&

You notice that the sigils are in a repeating pattern and have been designed to give you a small sense of vertigo.  You find it difficult to maintain your bearings as you walk down this corridor.

nodes.s: You are in the Labyrinth of Fear.
nodes.l: ...a large passageway.  The walls of this passageway are cleaned and smoothed; many of the runes that you have encountered elsewhere in the labyrinth are missing, though a few of the more powerful runes remain.  Hanging from the ceiling are large tapestries which depict a large minotaur king holding court.  Several small banners with heraldicdevices hang from either side of the tapestries.  These coats of arms are unknown to even the most knowledgable of you, as these heraldic devices have been striken from the recodes ages before you were born.

nodes.s: You are in the Labyrinth of Fear.
nodes.l: ...a large cavern within the labyrinth.  This cavern is enormous, with your lights only barely able to reach the far wall.  A huge stone table is set in the middle of this room, with a single large stone chair.  Theback of the chair peaks higher than the head of even the largest of giants.

nodes.s: You have entered an overgrown area.
nodes.l: ...the trees here are large and untended.  Wild weeds make passing through this area difficult.  Gnats and other small insects buzz about noisefully, you spend much of your time swatting them away.  You see no true path from your location but feel that you may be able to work your way either west or northeast from here.

nodes.s: You have entered a patroled area.
nodes.l: ...a large campsite.  This campsite has all the normal trimmings that you would expect to see.  A fire is centered in this area, and several tall tents have been erected.  Broken spears, javalins, and other weaponry lay in witness to some of the battles that have occurred here.  A path leads to the northwest and southeast from here.  You can also wend your way southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking along a wooded path.
nodes.l: ...the trees to either side of this path have been tended in such a way as to give a clear passage.  The dirt path has been stripped of weeds and debree.  Water has been constantly applied to the path, giving it an almost clay-like feel.  This path continues to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You have entered a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  This clearing is one of the many drinking spots of Satyr Woods.  A small fresh-water pond lies near a cropping of short grass.  Severalfallen logs have been cut to make seats.  A small firepit is also present, butit is unlit at this time.  A single well-muscled elf sits cross-leggedbeneath a willow tree.  The only path from this area is to thesouthwest.

nodes.s: You come across a satyr guard post.
nodes.l: ...a small wooden structure.  This small wooden shack is commonly used to house the patrolling satyrs when they are tired.  The shack has been reinforced by a layer of shaped stone.  This layer of stone prevents the door from being forced open by even the strongest of warriors.  The only path from this area is to the southeast.

nodes.s: You have entered a small clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  The arching path that you are travelling widens slightly here, causing a small circular clearing.  The weeds of this area seem to have been pulled, and the grass is maintained short.  Many of the pebbles that are present elsewhere in this area have been cleared from this area, as well.  This path continues to the northeast and southeast.

nodes.s: You have entered a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...a large clearing.  Trees bend away from this clearing as if they had been growing in a formation to make this clearing since the seeding.  Several small logs on the ground may serve as benches.  The grass here is green, fresh, and maintained.  Mushrooms grow in a small circle in the center of this clearing.  Large weeds have been permitted to grow outside this clearing, giving the clearing a very isolated look.  Flowers have been planted among the weeds to the east forming a site that will remain with you for quite some time.  Paths lead from this clearing to the northwest and to the southwest.

nodes.s: This path is covered in weeds.
nodes.l: ...a weed covered path.  This path appears to have been forgotten, as it is apparent that it is untended.  Wild flowers grow among the weeds here.  While it is difficult to see through the woods and trees of this area, you notice a small hut that appears to be abandoned to the east.  You know that you can force your way west again.

nodes.s: You have entered a hut hidden in the woods.
nodes.l: ...a small elven workshop.  A small elf quietly looks up from his alchemetical experiment as you enter this hut.  All around this small workshop you can see various creatures and races.  Remarkably, there are no satyrs here.  Though you begin to wonder how it is that he has managed to remain undiscovered for so long, you think it wiser not to question his presence.  The only exit from his workshop is to the west.

nodes.s: You find yourself amidst many trees.
nodes.l: ...a rough pass through the trees.  Unlike the worked and carefully tended paths that you have been walking, this path appears to be more natural.  The trees pose a natural obstacle course as the branches intertwine in each other.  You feel confident that you can negotiate your way either northeast or southeast.

nodes.s: You have discovered a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...a large natural clearing.  This natural clearing is devoid of the weeds, insects, and flowers that are found elsewhere in these woods.  No fallen logs liehere.  Standing in the center of this circle is a large statue of agreat satyr.  This satyr holds before him a huge carbonite gong whichsways in the wind.  A sense of danger overcomes you as you enter thisgreat circle.

nodes.s: You are on a deserted forest path.
nodes.l: ...a deserted forest path.  The intertwining branches here have many weeds and wildflowers growing amidst them.  The overgrowth of tall grass make it difficult to keep an eye on the path that you are on, and many rocks and pebbles hidden on the ground make your footing difficult to maintain.  Dispite the difficulty, you can travel either to the east or to the west.

Dispite the difficulty, you can travel either to the west, to the northeast, or to the southeast.

nodes.s: You stand before a large oak tree.
nodes.l: ...a huge clearing.  This clearing may have some religious significance, or maybe it is kept for its ascetic beuty.  What ever the case may be, you cannot help but stand in awe at the absolute beuty of this area.  The grass has been cut to a uniform length, and there isn't a hint of weeds anywhere in sight.  A huge oak tree stands majestically in the center of this huge clearing, its branches reaching upward like some tall gentle, giant being stretching after an afternoon nap.  A sense of calm overcomes you as you stand in silent contemplation here.  A path leads from this glade to the southeast.
nodes.quest_text: climb tree ... You carefully climb the tree. ... %s scurries up the tree! ... 

nodes.s: You are on a twisting forest path.
nodes.l: ...a twisting, winding path.  This path has been blazed around trees, rather than have them cut down.  While difficult to traverse, you are able to continue west or southeast.

nodes.s: You are on a twisting forest path.
nodes.l: ...a twisting, winding path.  This path has been blazed around trees, rather than have them cut down.  While difficult to traverse, you are able to continue west or southeast.

nodes.s: You stand before a huge cliff face.
nodes.l: ...a huge granite rockface.  This rockface looks to be the side of a large hill or small mountain.  Its actual composition is unimportant, though; it serves the single purpose of blocking your passage.  You can't help but to focus on the small dark granite keyhole that has been placed into this rock face, however.  Placed four feet from the ground, it sticks out like coal in a ballroom.  The only path from this place leads to the west.

nodes.s: You have entered a small workshop.
nodes.l: ...a gnomish workshop.  This small cavern is riddled with beakers, crystal rods, felts and scrolls.  A small gnome glaces fertively at you as you enter his domain.  As you gaze around this place, he gazes at you.  You may exit his workshop through the door to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are on a forest path.
nodes.l: ...a quaint forest path.  Well tended grass and clipped weeds surround you.  The sounds of birds flittering high in the trees mingle with the sound of the caper of many small animals.  The melody of rustling winds seeks to hide itself in the background of the more active notes of nature.  This well formed path continues to the east and northwest.

nodes.s: You are walking on a deserted path.
nodes.l: ...a circle of large standing stones.  Boulders reaching the height of eight or nine feet have been placed in a rough circle here.  A small fire continuously burns in the center of this rough circle.  A slab, probably an alter of some type, stands supported by two smaller stones.  This granite slab has several items on it.  Bones, swatches of fur, and a large iron bowl are the prominent items on the alter.  Two huge stakes stand to either side of this slab; the head of the latest victims of some crusade stand tall upon the tops of these spikes.  There are several paths form this satyr sacred ground; they are east, west, and southeast.

nodes.s: You are walking on a deserted path.
nodes.l: ...a rarely used path.  Thick spider webs hang from the trees here.  Moss and weeds have become prolific here, making travel difficult as you slip with every step.  Brambles clutch at you as you carefully pick your way along this path.  While travel is laborous, you may continue to the west or northeast.

nodes.s: You are walking on a deserted path.

nodes.s: You stand before a large stone wall.
nodes.l: ...a huge granite rockface.  This rockface looks to be the side of a large hill or small mountain.  Its actual composition is unimportant, though; it serves the single purpose of blocking your passage.  You can't help but to focus on the small dark sandstone keyhole that has been placed into this rock face, however.  Placed four feet from the ground, it sticks out like coal in a ballroom.  The only path from this place leads to the southwest.

nodes.s: You have entered the secret shop.
nodes.l: ...a small curio.  This shop has many items upon its shelves.  Books, stones, gems, and clothing are but a few of the items here.  Many of these items have cobwebs attached to them and layers of dust upon them.  Some of the items look newly created or acquired, though; and many of these catch your eye.  A large flesh golem stands ready to greet and service you.  A large sign hangs around his neck - "Buy what you want, be back soon.  Archmage Ateren."

nodes.s: You have entered Satyr Woods
nodes.l: ...trees... and more trees.  Satyr Woods is nothing less than a small forest. This area has been claimed by the satyrs long ago, and even Imperius recognizes the boundaries that the satyrs have set forth.  You duck around the low branches and tred carefully through the brambles that reach up from the ground.  Thick sinewy vines with large thorns wrap themselves around some of the trees.  While the satyrs may have little difficulty negotiating these paths, they are slightly more treacherous to you.  Paths can be seen wending to the east and northwest.

nodes.s: You walk along a narrow path.
nodes.l: ...a narrow path.  A small path has been cut through the weeds, vines, and brambles that are so prolific to this area.  Small prints in the ground show that this path is travelled, and not created by some fluke.  Most of these prints are goat-like in nature; evidence of the satyr population in this area.  This path widens towards the northwest and continues to the east.

nodes.s: You have entered a large clearing
nodes.l: ...a large grassy clearing.  Firmly matted grass and numerous patches of worn down vegetation clearly mark this area as well-travelled.  In the middle of the wide open area is a large pit.  Situated high above the pit is a long roasting pike still warm to the touch.  A narrow, well groomed foot path leads off to the northeast and to the southwest is an even narrower path entrenched in a sea of weeds and mulch.

nodes.s: You are walking on a weed-covered path.
nodes.l: ...a weed infested path.  This very narrow path is covered in a layer of brambles, thorny vines, and mulch.  This path shows the evidence of one having been very well travelled but has apparently fallen into disuse.  Huge xut bugs crawl along the moss covered trunks, their spider-like eyes waving about on their long antennae.  A clearing is seen to the northeast, while this long-forgotten path continues to the southwest.

nodes.s: You are walking on a weed-covered path.
nodes.l: ...a weed infested path.  This very narrow path is covered in a layer of brambles, thorny vines, and mulch.  This path shows the evidence of one having been very well travelled but has apparently fallen into disuse.  Huge xut bugs crawl along the moss covered trunks, their spider-like eyes waving about on their long antennae.  This long-forgotten path continues to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You have stumbled upon a large hut.
nodes.l: ...a large abandoned hut.  This hut was once some grand living quarters, but has since fallen into disuse.  Vines surround this wooden structure, and the windows have been boarded up to prevent further disrepair.  A single path leads from this hut to the northeast.

nodes.s: Satyr Woods closes about you here.
nodes.l: ...a thin path.  This small path is surrounded by close-knit trees and intertwined foilage.  Brambles bite at your legs as you attempt to wend your way through this difficult path.  This small path continues northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: Satyr Woods closes about you here.
nodes.l: ...a thin path.  This small path is surrounded by close-knit trees and intertwined foilage.  Brambles bite at your legs as you attempt to wend your way through this difficult path.  This small path continues east, northeast, and southwest.

nodes.s: You stand in an encampment in the woods.
nodes.l: ...a large campsite.  This campsite has all the normal trimmings that you would expect to see.  A fire is centered in this area, and several tall tents have been erected.  Broken spears, javalins, and other weaponry lay in witness to some of the battles that have occurred here.  A path leads to the northwest and southeast from here.  You can also wend your way northwest or southwest.

nodes.s: This path in Satyr Woods ends here.
nodes.l: ...a dead end.  Like so many paths that were created by adventurers long ago, this path ends abruptly.  Usually caused by adventureres when they attempt to force their way about the forest when there is no actual path.  This path stretches in one direction which is southeast.

nodes.s: A winding path looms before you.
nodes.l: ...a long winding path.  This path slopes downward into a valley.  The valley has tall trees growing to either side of it.  You gaze at the majestic view; being able to see the valley from above the height of the trees gives you a sense of power and control.  The small path wends downward into the valley to an area that is hidden deep within the foilage.  The path leads weastward.

nodes.s: You stand before a large gem tower.
nodes.l: ...a large gem tower.  This emerald green tower looms above you.  The spire reaches almost to the height of the tallest tree.  Magicks cause this tower to seem invisible until you are almost upon it.  Your lights glisten and gleam.  Though the tower appears to be made entirely of emerald, the thickness of it prevents you from peering within.  A winding path leads eastward.

nodes.s: You have entered the large gem tower.
nodes.l: ...a huge crystal rotunda.  This rounded room has several people of various races within it.  Near the center of this room is a legendary storm giant who casually, quietly and patiently drones on about the methods of forming lightning into a lance.  Light scintillates off of the crystal which makes up the walls, floor and ceiling of this room.  An aura of power and respect is evident here.  The only exit from this great room appears to be to the east.

nodes.s: You have entered a large clearing.
nodes.l: ...a small clearing.  While it was impossible to view the entrance to this area from the west, you have a clear view of all those that would pass by this clearing.  The matted ground and deep prints show that this area is often used as a guard post and ambush spot.  There are exits to the east and west.

nodes.s: You are walking on a path in the woods.
nodes.l: ...a dark wooded path.  This path in the woods appears to have been created naturaly and without much intevention.  Trees have been permitted to arch this way and that, moss and lichen grow on rocks, weeds hang down from low branches, and pebbles assault your feet with every step.  This path continues to the west and northeast.
