nodes.s: You have entered the gemstone pyramid.
nodes.l: ...a gem laden room.  This room is at the interior base of the large gemstone pyramid.  Several beams of light shine through many of the gems creating a lattice of pulsing colors.  The gems seem to pulsate with a life of their own.  These pulsating lights are accompanied by the distant sounds of drumming thunder.  The lights and sound, coupled with the haze created by the diffused light, give you the impression of being centered in a storm cloud.  A spectral figure appears to be moving to and fro while watching you curiously.  There is an exit from this room to the west.

nodes.s: You stand before a gemstone pyramid.
nodes.l: ...a gemstone pyramid.  This path comes to an abrupt end, and to the west you see a tremendous pyramid that appears to be made of millions of gemstones.  These gemstones have been fit together so that there are no gaps between them.  They are adhered to a clear surface with a substance that is also clear; the gems are impossible to move, budge, or remove.  A single aperture in the pyramid faces you from the west.  You may return to satyr woods by travelling northeast.

nodes.s: You are deep within the satyr's territory.
nodes.l: ...a forest path.  The trees here appear taller than in any other area of this area.  The weeds that are so prolific elsewhere seem to be absent here.  The ground, while natural, has had all manners of obstacles removed.  Bushes have been trimmed to either side of you, indicating that this is, indeed, a well travelled road.  This darkened path continues to the northeast and southwest.

nodes.s: You have entered a large clearing.

Situated high above the pit is a long roasting pike still warm to the touch.  Several paths wind from this area; they lead to the east and southwest.

nodes.s: You are in a large room.
nodes.l: This cavern is huge.  Although, like much of the catacombs, it is clean, it is obviously of ancient construction.  Many faces have been carved into the wall, and the shadows make it seem like these stone carvings move as if alive, sneering at you and your attempts to enter this place.  There are exits to the southeast, southwest, and to the south.

nodes.s: You are in a brightly lit corridor.
nodes.l: This long, brightly lit corridor is berift of the cuniform design that many of the walls of the catacombs possess.  This passage leads to the north and south.

nodes.s: You are in a brass room.
nodes.l: Constructed entirely of brass, this room seems odd and out of place.  A small pedastal stands centered in this room.  Atop the pedastal is a strange metallic orb whose colors seem to shift endlessley.  The only exit from this room is to the north.

nodes.s: You are in a large tomb.
nodes.l: This large room is dark and dank; the air here smells stale.  A large coffin is centered in the room.  The top of the coffin is open and reveals stairs leading downward into darkness.

nodes.s: You are at the bottom of a circular staircase.
nodes.l: You are at the bottom of the staircase.  The room here is triangular and bare.  You notice that there is another staircase leading down.  The top stair is just below floor level, but there is a shimmering force covering it.  There are three other exits from this room.  They are northwest, northeast, and south.  All the passages lead into darkness.

nodes.s: You have entered a mausoleum.
nodes.l: This huge underground cavern doubles as a huge mausoleum.  A large obilisk with strange protective symbols stands high above an obsidian coffin.  The room is made of basalt, and the air here is dank.  A sense of great power and forbodance overcomes you as look around.

nodes.s: You are in the room of portals.
nodes.l: Great swirling mists surround you as you find yourself oustide of time and space.  Beneath you, a travellers glyph covers a trapdoor that leads downward.  The glyph shows the symbol of Spalango.  Westward is an arch through which you can see the spendor of the Temple of Myrias in Imperial City.

nodes.s: You are in a huge cavern.
nodes.l: ...a huge cavern.  You have entered one of the many ice lizard dens that have been created by the creatures that dwell here.  Torches line the walls, but more for heat that for sight.  Several huge piles of furs and skins are lying about.  The floor is surprisingly clean, however, of the bones and trash that are found in the other dens of the ice lizards.  The only exit is to the south.

nodes.s: You are in a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a winding cave.  You are in a cave that is part of a winding corridor of caves.  Several sharp stalagmites push up from the floor; the frost on the top makes them look like miniature mountains.  Steam escapes from your mouth as you breath and the cold air sends shivers through your body.  There are exits to the northwest and northeast.

nodes.s: You are in the Ice Dale caverns.
nodes.l: ...an iced-over cavern.  You are in the Ice Dale caverns.  The mist formed by your breath seems to crystallize almost as soon as it leaves your mouth; your nose aches from the dry, bitter cold.  Your clothing does nothing to protect you from this cold as it makes your limbs numb.  The exits from this cavern are to the northeast and south.

nodes.s: You are in a huge cavern.
nodes.l: ...a huge cavern.  This huge cavern of the Ice Dales has a sheet of ice and frost that is very thick.  There are few tracks in this cavern; it is traveled much.  Many of the stalactites have fallen off the ceiling from the weight of the ice that had formed on them.  Many more of the stalactites threaten to fall.  There are several exits from this frigid cavern: northeast, northwest, southwest, and east.

nodes.s: You are in an icy conservatory.
nodes.l: ...a huge cavern.  This huge cavern looks to be made of ice.  Your light is reflected and magnified a thousand times.  There are many types of flowers here and vines of ice crystals crawl upon the walls.  Some of these flowers seem to bend in your direction as you examine them; in this place, even the flowers are alive.  Through the misty fog that comes from the icy walls, beyond a bedof flowers, you can see the mighty Alter of Assumption.  The magics ofthis place allow you to assume the powers and abilities of your chosenclass (but only if you are ready).  The only exit from this room is tothe west.

nodes.s: You are at the Ice Dale Tower.
nodes.l: ...a great Ice Tower.  You stand outside the great Ice Dale Tower.  The tower is centered in a cavern of immense size, and its higher levels spire into the ceiling.  The tower appears to be made completely of a blue opaque ice.  The drawbridge to the south is also made of the same material.  It is down and ready to allow you entrance into this mysterious place.
nodes.quest_text: enter ... Your bridgestaff grows and allows you passage. ... %s uses his bridgestaff to create a bridge! ... /,

nodes.s: You are in a frigid cave.
nodes.l: ...an extremely cold cave.  The coldness of this cave reaches to your very bones.  No amount of clothing or heat seems to be enough to stave off the chill that this cave brings to you.  This cave may be exited to the west and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in the Ice Dale Tower.
nodes.l: ...a corridor.  You are in the corridors of the Ice Dale Tower.  The floors, walls, and ceiling of the corridor are made of a pale blue crystal which is ice-like in appearance and feel.  The air here is bitter and a fog rises from the floor.  Your light is reflected off the many facets of this place; it is almost blinding to keep your eyes open.  This corridor continues to the north and south.
nodes.quest_text: place rose in hand of spectre ... The Ice Wizard takes the rose.. you may pass. ... %s hands the statue the crystal rose. ... .&

nodes.s: You are in the waiting room.
nodes.l: ...a waiting room.  You are in the waiting room of the Ice Dale Tower.  The north leads out of this tower, while the south leads deeper into this mysterious place.  The south egress, however, is blocked by a large spectre of some wizard long since died.  The specter holds a small crystalline rose in one hand while the other motions towards the southern exit.  Although insubstantial, you can feel mystical power being emulated from him.

nodes.s: You are in a strange tower.
nodes.l: ...a strange tower.  This tower is larger than the rest you have entered within this place.  The east wall is covered by a huge sheet of ice.  There are other exits to the northeast and southeast as well.

nodes.s: You are in a large ice corridor.
nodes.l: ...a huge corridor.  This huge corridor is brightly lit by glowing sigils carved into the ice that the corridor is comprised of.  There is a huge chasm that must be traversed if you wish to continue to the east.  The sheet of ice to the west looks almost transparent.

nodes.s: You are in a large corridor.
nodes.l: ...a huge corridor.  This huge corridor is brightly lit by glowing sigils carved into the ice that the corridor is comprised of.  There is a huge chasm that must be traversed if you wish to continue to the west.  There is a room to the east.

nodes.s: You are in a large room.
nodes.l: ...a large room.  This large room looks to be carved from a single piece of ice.  Shelves have been carved out of the walls and books line them.  A large crystal ball stands on a pedestal in the center of the room.  Tools and implements of magic line the many tables that are in this room.  A sense of power comes from the many sigils that are carved in this room.

nodes.s: You are in a glowing passageway.
nodes.l: ...a large passageway.  This large passageway glows with an eerie purple light.  Your brow itches with power as your rune of power resonates with the power of this place.  There are sigils on the walls and floor; there is an eerie sense of foreboding from this place.  You may continue to the east and west.

nodes.s: You are in a large crystal cave.
nodes.l: ...a large crystal cave.  This large crystal cave glows with the same purple light that the passageway has been glowing with.  The corridors to the northwest and southeast seethe with power, more that the passageway to the east does.

nodes.s: You are in a power-ridden corridor.
nodes.l: ...a great corridor.  This great corridor has intensely glowing runes about it which give off a reddish-purple light that can hardly be contained.  This power counters the cold that the rest of the Tower has within it; you can sense that even without any light source you could still easily see.  This corridor continues to the northwest and southeast.

nodes.s: You are in a dark corridor.
nodes.l: ...a dark corridor.  This dark corridor is covered in many, many sigils that you cannot decipher.  You vaguely remember seeing these symbols on many of the weapons that the dreaded drow have been carrying.  You may continue to the east or west from here.

nodes.s: You are in a dark corridor.
nodes.l: ...a dark corridor.  This dark corridor is covered in many, many sigils that you cannot decipher.  You vaguely remember seeing these symbols on many of the weapons that the dreaded drow have been carrying.  You may continue to the east or west from here.  The passage to the east is barred by a large statue of a large black spider with a human female head.

nodes.s: You are in a large cave.
nodes.l: ...a large cave.  You are in a large cave that has a huge pit in the center of it.  The pit has many bluish, metallic stones about it, each of which has a different sigil engraved upon it.  The only other exit from this cave is to the west.

nodes.s: You are in a corridor.
nodes.l: nan

nodes.s: You are on an icy path.
nodes.l: ...an icy pathway.  Although the cold air is not unbearable, the ground has become frozen, causing the pathway under your feet to harden and react in a slippery fashion.  On both sides of the pathway light foliage exists, but also you can see that the bushes and grass have frozen over.  To the west lies the western gate to Imperial City; to the northeast, the path continues.

nodes.s: You are on an icy path.
nodes.l: ...an icy pathway.  The road here runs from the northeast to the southwest in what appears to have once been a main passageway to Imperial City.  Now, much of the path is frozen and harsh for travel.  To the east you can see that another pathway, perhaps older, is barely discernable.  It branches off from the main road and winds away from view.

nodes.s: You are on a rough, icy path.
nodes.l: ...a frozen trail.  Frozen leaves, grass, and stone cover much of this trail that heads to the west, northwest, and southeast.  The trees and bushes, although many are barren of leaves, close in on the path and make travel slow for even the most sure-footed.

nodes.s: You are on a rough, icy path.
nodes.l: ...a broken and frozen trail.  The pathway here is too distorted and old to make any sense of.  The environment seems to close in and cut off any attempt to travel except northwest, from whence you came.

nodes.s: You are on an icy path.
nodes.l: ...an icy roadway.  Although the cold air is not unbearable, the ground has become frozen, causing the pathway under your feet to harden and react in a slippery fashion.  On both sides of the pathway light foliage exists, but also you can see that the bushes and grass have frozen over.  This path curves around a bend and continues both east and southwest.  Branching off from the road, you notice a barely discernable trail to the southeast.

nodes.s: You are on an icy path.
nodes.l: ...an icy roadway.  Although the cold air is not unbearable, the ground has become frozen, causing the pathway under your feet to harden and react in a slippery fashion.  On both sides of the pathway light foliage exists, but also you can see that the bushes and grass have frozen over.  The road continues, running both west and northeast.

nodes.s: You are on an icy path.
nodes.l: ...an icy roadway.  Although the cold air is not unbearable, the ground has become frozen, causing the pathway under your feet to harden and react in a slippery fashion.  On both sides of the pathway light foliage exists, but also you can see that the bushes and grass have frozen over. nodes.s: You are on a trail covered with snow.
nodes.l: ...a frozen trail.  Frozen leaves, grass, and stone cover much of this trail that heads to northwest and southwest.  The trees and bushes, although many are barren of leaves, close in on the path and make travel slow for even the most sure-footed.

nodes.s: You are at the edge of a snow-filled canyon.
nodes.l: ...the edge of a cliff overlooking a snow-filled canyon.  Sounds of water rushing through the canyon below can be heard from where you stand.  Looking into the narrow chasm, you observe that much of the water is frozen while some of it continues to run.  This canyon wall here descends into the gorge at only a slight incline.

nodes.s: You are in a snow-filled canyon.
nodes.l: ...within a gorge of water and ice.  Standing on the most reasonably stable ice here, you notice the many tracks about this land.  It is obvious that the waters here are the main source of liquid as well as meat for the creatures that dwell in the tundra.  The canyon walls are not too dramatic, and finding an exit should not be difficult.

On the top of the post is a sphere of opaque white color.  A dim yellowish light emanates from the sphere.  The Hallway of Meditation is east of here.

nodes.s: You are in the Halls of Meditation.
nodes.l: ...that you are in a mystical refuge for meditation.  Gnomes that desired to practice certain disciplines of magic created the Halls of Meditation in a time long ago.  The rooms here are covered with tapestries, carpets, and works of art.  Incense lingers in the air, meant to coerce deep thought and philosophy.

nodes.s: You are in Nasuel's Nasals.
nodes.l: ...that you are in a store.  You are welcomed as you enter the building called "Nausuel's Nasals" with a sense of warmth.  All around you see strange looking items made of cloth.  It is only until you approach closer, that you realize that these pieces of "wear" are actually for covering the nose.  You remember how concerned gnomes are of their noses and understand the importance of this place.

nodes.s: You are in the Hall of Treegan Claim.
nodes.l: ...a hallway dedicated to the Treegan Gnomes. Much like the Tunnels of Tor, this building contains lore and art that can only be attributed to the gnomes of Quentin.

nodes.s: You are at the Eastern Gate of Quentin.
nodes.l: ...a gate of wood and stone.  Here stands a normal sized gate with writings from the Gnome script upon it.  This portal is the entryway into the city of Quentin, home of the Ice Gnomes.  Quentin has long been shrouded in the seclusion of the arctic tundra.  The air here is fresh and cool, though, the smell of the city does rise to meet your nostrils.  A guard tower stands to the north of here.

nodes.s: You are in the Guard Tower.
nodes.l: ...you are within the guard tower.  You are standing in one of the three guard towers constructed for the city of Quentin.  The purpose of the towers is stand watch before the gates of Quentin and to provide access to the shieldwalls that stand high above the city.  Within this stone-worked creation you notice a wooden ladder designed to allow movement between the shieldwall and the main city.

nodes.s: You are in Pala's Music Shop.
nodes.l: ...a shop full of musical instruments.  At first glance, the items hanging about appear to be some weird form of machination.  After more scrutinized perusal, you acknowledge that these are musical pieces of equipment created and played solely by the gnomes.

nodes.s: You are on Corin's Approach.
nodes.l: ...you are on a holy street in the city of Quentin.  The consistency of its design tells you that there is intent more than meets the eye here.  This street seems to carry a specific purpose related to religion; you wonder if you are violating some gnomic law as you stand here.  On both sides of this travel way, you see markers covered in the Gnome script, spaced a few feet apart.  To one side, there is a post that carries the street name in Gnome script and in the Imperial tongue.  On the top of the post is a sphere of opaque white color.  A dim yellowish light emanates from the sphere.

nodes.s: You are in a Temple of Myrias.
nodes.l: ...a temple dedicated to a gnomic god.  There is an uncanny smell in the temple, like a mixture of incense and another, more discriminate herb lingering in the air.  The floor of the temple is made of basalt; you have no idea where the material could have come from.  Various idols, all representative of a figure that is gnome-like in appearance are placed throughout this place of worship.

nodes.l: ...a crypt built from a time long ago.  You have entered a sacred area of the gnome religion called the Crypt of Ascendants.  It is usually forbidden for any, but higher-ranking priests to enter the chambers here.  It is said that within this room, the voices of priests long dead still carry.

nodes.s: You areon Celan Bridge.
nodes.l: ...a bridge of stone and wood.  This construction has been made to span over the river that runs through Quentin.  Notoriously, it also separates the Higher District from the Lower and Middle ones.  The bridge itself seems slightly fragile even though it looks sturdy enough.

nodes.s: You are southeast of The Pinnicle.
nodes.l: ...a spire that ascends very high.  In this small square, a flagstaff made of some metal has been set into the stonework of the road.  Residing in the very middle of the area, it towers possibly fifteen meters in height.  Known as the Pinnacle, this icon represents the loyalty of the Ice Gnomes to the city of Quentin.  High upon the flagstaff, a banner flutters in the wind.

nodes.s: You are at Quentin's northwest gate.
nodes.l: ...a gate of wood and stone.  Here stands a normal sized gate with writings from the Gnome script upon it.  This portal is the entryway into the city of Quentin, home of the Ice Gnomes.  Quentin has long been shrouded in the seclusion of the arctic tundra.  The air here is fresh and cool, though, the smell of the city does rise to meet your nostrils.  A guard tower is directly east of here.

nodes.l: ...you are within the guard tower.  You are standing in one of the three guard towers constructed for the city of Quentin.  The purpose of the towers is stand watch before the gates of Quentin and to provide access to the shieldwalls that stand high above the city.  Within this stone-worked creation you notice a wooden ladder designed to allow movement between the shieldwall and the main city.

nodes.s: You are at the garbage dump.
nodes.l: ...garbage.  One of the most unpleasant sights in the city of Quentin, the "Dump" carries a stench almost all the way up to the High District.  Trash and filth lay scattered over every corner of this large hole at the edge of Stench Street.  Glancing inside the dump, you notice shoddy-clad gnomes walking about and organizing the mess to some extent; heavy cloth covers their mouths and noses.  With city guards circled around the dump, you realize that those gnomes are criminals and paying the penalty for breaking the law.

Perhaps it has a purpose for defense; you cannot tell.  To the side, there is a post that carries the street name in Gnome script and in the Imperial tongue.  On the top of the post is a sphere of opaque white color.  A dim yellowish light emanates from the sphere.

nodes.s: You are in Liliar's Music Shop.
nodes.l: ...a shop full of musical instruments.  At first glance, the items hanging about appear to be some weird form of machination.  After more scrutinized perusal, you acknowledge that these are musical pieces of equipment created and played solely by the gnomes.

nodes.s: YOu are at an intersection.
nodes.l: ...an intersection of roads.   An intersection has been put here to provide access and quicker route to another part of Quentin.  After passing through here only a few minutes, you realize that a specific architecture has been conceptualized, providing quicker means to certain parts of the city.  A post of sculpted stone has been driven into the street and displays both street names for guidance and direction.  Garfauli's Fine Foods is directly east from here.

nodes.s: You are in an alleyway.
nodes.l: ...a slim alleyway.  As opposed to much of Quentin, this area is not very kept and contains some discarded trash.  The ground is worked, but with rough stone to provide just enough structure for easy maintenance.  The light levels here are low due to the closeness of the buildings around you.

A small wayside shack stands west of here.

nodes.s: You are in a small shack.
nodes.l: ...a healer's quarters.  You have entered a small, disheveled, home only to realize you have found a healer among the citizens of lower class here in Quentin.  The room carries the scent of herbs; you see a cooking pot off to the side of the room with the lid still over it.

nodes.s: You are in Garfauli's Casino House.
nodes.l: ...a gambling establishment.  Attributed to Garfauli, a gnome well known among those of the lower quarters, this house has been converted into a place of gambling.  Boards of odds decorate the walls, listing chances of arena fighting, a well-liked form of gambling.  Throughout the room, various tables of chance have been placed, some foreign to you and some not so unknown.

nodes.s: You are in Garfauli's Leather House.
nodes.l: ...an establishment of leatherworking.  Attributed to Garfauli, a gnome well known among those of the lower quarters, this house has been converted into a place or leather repair and sale.  Many gnome workers work on hides and strips of leather, fashioning them into pliable forms and equipment.

nodes.s: You are in Garfauli's Fine Foods.
nodes.l: ...an establishment of stored food.  Attributed to Garfauli, a gnome well known among those of the lower quarters, this house has been converted into a place for the storing and selling of prepared food.  You do notice a slightly stale smell in the air.

nodes.s: You are in the guardtower.
nodes.l: ...you are within the guard tower.  You are standing in one of the three guard towers constructed for the city of Quentin.  The purpose of the towers is stand watch before the gates of Quentin and to provide access to the shieldwalls that stand high above the city.  Within this stone-worked creation you notice a wooden ladder designed to allow movement between the shieldwall and the main city.

nodes.s: You are at the northeast tower.
nodes.l: ...a stone reinforced guard wall.  You are above the city of Quentin on a wall designed for patrol and defense.  Known as the shieldwall by the citizens, it consists of three barriers connected together like a triangle.  The architecture here seems sound and ingenious; you realize it is well constructed and effective against invasion should the time ever arise.  There is also a ladder here leading to the ground below.

nodes.s: You are in the Captains office.
nodes.l: ...the office of the Guardwatch.  This is a stone-constructed room, basic and very clean, made for the gnomes that stand watch and patrol throughout Quentin.  Most citizens of the city stand watch from time to time.  On the northern wall, you see a tapestry of arms depicting the gnome regiment.

nodes.s: The Captain of the Watch rest station.
nodes.l: ...the main quarters of the Captain of the Watch.  While much of these quarters are lightly furnished, here there is a difference.  Slightly more color and artwork decorate the room, while a large, white oak desk sits in the middle of the room.  These quarters are where the watch-captain dispenses his orders and assigns a watch rotation.

nodes.s: Type LOOK in this room.
nodes.l: ...you can see the details of this room.  You should type LOOK in every room here until you complete the passages of learning.  An old man leans next to the north wall while directing travel through here.  You are informed that the west passage is the only true passage out.  He also points to an old parchment tacked to the wall.  You should LOOK at it.  Three other corridors are here: the north, east, and south.

nodes.s: The Linguistic Council.
nodes.l: ...you are being taught to speak.  Three women are repeatedly reciting syllables over and over here; the room echoes of words being spoken proper and formal.  At every available moment, you are being told to speak (type: Hello, I can speak now.).  While you are learning, each woman tries to get you to LOOK at her.  To the west, you can see a room filled with stacks of papers and books.

nodes.s: The Library for HELP (type HELP).
nodes.l: ...walls covered with parchments and writings.  In this room books are stacked everywhere; the walls are lined with writings and information on a vast number of topics.  HELP <name of subject>, or just HELP by itself can teach you many things related to the land of New Corinthia.  You can use the HELP command anywhere.  The Council of Linguistics is to the east; the Hallway of Discarded Items is northwest of here.

nodes.s: A room full of discarded trash.
nodes.l: ...a littered hallway.  There are useless items, worn and old, lying scattered about the floor here.  Over by the west wall, a sign is posted, saying, "Please, GET the TRASH.  Do not DISCARD your TRASH here!"  You notice a lazy guard standing at the northern end of the hall; he is motioning for you to LOOK at him.  To the southeast is the HELP library; to the north is a Dressing Room.

nodes.s: A room full of boots and knives.
nodes.l: ...a dressing room.  Boots and knives of various sizes are organized to the side of the east wall.  If you would like to put some boots on, type GET BOOTS, then WEAR BOOTS.  If you decide to take the boots off, type REMOVE BOOTS, then DISCARD BOOTS.  You cannot WEAR a KNIFE, but you can GET a KNIFE and keep it in your inventory.  A wardroom sign is posted by the wall.

nodes.s: A room of bartering merchants.
nodes.l: ...merchants exchanging their wares.  This room has been set up as a Trader's Pit; the current commodity being exchanged is animal hide.  Type LIST to see what is being sold right now.  If you wish to buy one of the items on the list, type BUY <name of item>.  If you wish to sell an item, type SELL <name of item>.  There is also a trading exchange sheet on the floor.  You should LOOK at the sheet for help.

nodes.s: An area for practice fighting.
nodes.l: ...a wooden practice dummy.  Here you will learn the various commands important to survival.  ATTACK <name of creature> will begin combat.  The command STOP will cause any attacking to cease.  There is also a war scripture posted by the wall that you should LOOK at.

nodes.s: A dais covered with symbols.
nodes.l: ...a dais of enlightenment.  This structure rises, leading up to an altar.  Scrawled on the dais is information pertaining to advancement.  In New Corinthia, you can learn new skills, raise your attributes, and promote to the next level.  The command HINT will tell you if you are in a place where this form of advancement is possible.  You should LOOK at the dais before you leave this room.

nodes.s: An altar dedicated to the gods.
nodes.l: ...an altar devoted to advancement.  The altar here represents various places you will go when you advance yourself in New Corinthia.  You should LOOK at the altar to learn the powerful knowledge it can reveal to you.  Once you are done here, you have completed the rites of passage and are ready to venture into the world.  Below you is the Dais of Enlightenment; to the east is the exit from the passages of learning.
nodes.quest_text: exit ... Good luck on your future journeys! ... Don't forget to wish %s good luck! ... ##

nodes.s: An ancient training room.
nodes.l: ...an ancient training room.  This room was long ago used by those that had  undergone the Ritual of Ascension; the power of such training still permeates this place.  The spectres of many of the trainers fade in and out of view; their ability to train those that are prepared have not been diminshed by their passing.  A large donation chest sits against the far wall upon the floor.  It is perpetually empty.

nodes.s: You are in a torch lit passage.
nodes.l: ...a passage lit brightly by wooden torches.   The walls of the passageway, constructed of a brownish stone, are cool and damp to the touch.  Cold air drifts lazily through the passage carrying the faint scent of hopps and other grains.  A sturdy wooden staircase ascends upwards into Coat of Arms Tavern.  To the north, the passageway continues.

nodes.s: You are in a torch lit passage.
nodes.l: ...a passage lit brightly by wooden torches.  The walls of the passageway, constructed of a brownish stone, are cool and damp to the touch.  Cold air drifts lazily through the passage carrying the faint scent of hopps and other grains.  To the north, the passageway continues and in the distance to the south, you notice a wooden staircase leading upwards.

nodes.s: You are in a torch lit passage.
nodes.l: ...a passage lit brightly by wooden torches.  The walls of the passageway, constructed of a brownish stone, are cool and damp to the touch.  Cold air drifts lazily through the passasge carrying the faint scent of hopps and other grains.  The passageway continues to the north and to the south.

nodes.s: You are in a torch lit passage.
nodes.l: ...a passage lit brightly by wooden torches.  The walls of the passageway, constructed of a brownish stone, are cool and damp to the touch.  Cold air drifts lazily through the passage carrying the faint scent of hopps and other grains.  The passageway continues to the south and to the northwest you notice some heaped trash.

nodes.s: You are in a foul smelling room.
nodes.l: ...a large trash heap.  The room is full of all manner of foul smelling trash.  Your nostrals stiffen just slightly as the smell creeps up your nasal passages.  One corner of the room is a bit cleaner than the rest.  The passageway continues to the southeast and to the north you notice a long hallway lined with racks of wine.

nodes.s: You are in a torch lit passage.
nodes.l: ...a clean, well lit passageway.  The walls of the passageway, constructed of a brownish stone, are cool and damp to the touch.  Cold air drifts lazily through the passage carrying a strong scent of beer and wine.  This section of the passageway is the main storage area for the Coat of Arms's wine supply.  To the south, the smell of rotting something-or-the-other drifts heavily.  To the east and to the west you notice small panties lined with wine racks and to the north the wine-hall passageway continues.

nodes.s: You are in a small pantry.
nodes.l: ...a small pantry adorned with wine racks.  Built into this pantry are several large wooden wine racks.  The racks are filled to capacity with wines of varying ages, colors and flavors.  Upon inspection, you notice that most of the bottles are quite dusty and you surmise that the tavern above probably doesn't sell much wine.  To the west is the main passageway.

nodes.s: You are in a tight passage.
nodes.l:
...a tight passage.  This section of the main passageway is tighter in diameter than the previous parts.  The scent of honey ale wafts slowly through the air.  This passageway connects the wine storage area with the ale 
brewing area.  To the south, you notice the main storage area for the wine cellar and to the northeast you may enter the Tavern's main brewing area.

nodes.s: You are in a brewing area.
nodes.l: ...a large area equipped for the brewing of ales.  This room is well lit and though quite enormous, there is barely enough room to move about due to the plethora of ale-brewing vats.  A heavy scent of beer wafts through the air and the floor is sticky.  To the north and to the west you can see more large vats and to the southeast a thin passage leads to the wine storage areas.

nodes.s: You are in a brewing area.

A heavy scent of beer wafts through the air and the floor is sticky.  A small diagram, outlining the brewing process, is tacked to the wall here though it has since become dogeared and faded.  To the north and to the east you can see more large vats.

Small, immobile lanterns hang from the beams above casting ominous shadows upon the walls.  To the west you spy what appears to be an operations center of some sort and to the north the tunnel continues.

nodes.l: ...a small kobold lair.  Wrought with dirt, filth this lair is the proverbial pig sty.  Scraps of meat and bones lie rotting on the floor and the dust and dirt you kick up nearly chokes you.  To the west is the tunnel proper.

Behind and above the desk is a pencil drawn portrait of Clyde the barkeep holding the head of goblin in the air.  The scent of honey ale and perfumes stagnates here.  A jammed open door leads east.

Small piles of rubble and dirt line the walls and rickety beams support the ceiling.  One solitary lantern hangs from a low slung beam.  To the south the tunnel continues.

nodes.s: You are in large passageway.
nodes.l: ...a large rusty door.  You stand in a recently excavated rock and dirt tunnel.  Small piles of rubble and dirt line the walls and rickety beams support the ceiling.  A large array of lanters lite this room well.  On the western end of the passageway is a large rusty metal door.  To the east, the passage continues.

nodes.s: You are in a room.
nodes.l: ...a rather large hole in the ground.  This room, like the rest of the passageway has been carved from rock and dirt.  Small piles of rubble and dirt line the walls and rickety beams support the ceiling.  A large hole is dug out from the ground allowing passage downward. Peering below you notice that you are directly above the Imperial City sewer system.  The not so gentle stink of raw sewage glides ever so slowly up into your nostrals.

nodes.s: You are in the sewers.
nodes.l: ...a rather large hole in the ceiling.  You are ankle deep in the Imperial City sewer system.  The walls, carpetted with filth, scum and insects, are a red and green tint.   Raw sewage drifts by your feet and small rodents scurry about the sides of the wall.  Light casts down from a large hole in the ceiling illuminating the room.  The sewer drifts to the southeast.

nodes.s: You are at the floodgates.
nodes.l: ...a large flood gate.  The flood gate holds back the current of the sewer at this point.  Sewage of all types flows through your legs and out through a small opening in the flood gate.  Though pretty much STUCK, the flood gate looks as though it is capable of opening and closing to a certain degree.  Looking carefully about, you decide that the control to the gate is elsewhere.  You may continue to the northwest or to the south.

nodes.s: You are in a large room.
nodes.l: ...the kobold hideout.  Significantly nicer smelling than the rest of the sewer, this living area is converted from an old storage area for the Imperial Sewer.  Droppings, trash and paraphenali litter the floor.  Shackle rings on the wall set a gentle forboding about the room.  To the south the plot thickens and to the north are the floodgates.

nodes.s: You are in a large room.
nodes.l: ...the kobold hideout.  You stand in a reasonably clean passageway.  The droppings, trash and sewage that you have gotten so used to is swept neatly in the corner and the air is almost breathable.  To the east and the west you notice small living quarters, to the north you may continue on back to the sewer system.  To the south you hear some arguing.

To the north you notice a hallway and some living quarters and to the east the redstone corridor continues.

nodes.l: ...a small well lit room.  This room is a haven from the current and stench of the sewer proper.  It is empty save for a small lever on the west wall marked FLOOD GATES.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven Square.
nodes.l: ...Pendlehaven Square.  Well kept, this grand open area marks the social center of Pendlehaven.  Denizens of Pendlehaven stroll about leisurely, stopping often to what with, admire, and greet one another.  A large stage has been erected in the center of the square and a sign hangs brazenly from it reading "The Crier will be here soon."  Standing next to the stage is a small wooden bulletin board with several small yellowed parchments tacked to it.  Roads lead north, south, east and west from here.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven Armor Shop.
nodes.l: ...a small, well lit armor shop.  Though mostly rudimentary, the Pendlehaven armor shop stocks a reasonable supply of armors and other protective gear.  Animal pelts and worked leather garments hang upon the walls of the shop and a small pie shield rack, though empty, leans against the far wall.  In the back of the shop, a seamstress works the pelts into wearable articles of protection.  Towards the front of the store is a small wooden counter with a wooden stool tucked beneath.  A small coin scale, fashioned from brass, sits on top of the counter.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven Weapon Shop.
nodes.l: a well lit weapons shop.  In the far corner of the room a fire roars inside a stone hearth and in the distance the vivid clanging of iron can be heard.  Knives, daggers, darts and other implements of war can be viewed and purchased here.  Several large bins stocked with edged weapons sit in the center of the store; bundled close to the entranceway are many varieties of staves.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven Arena.
nodes.l: ...a simple arena.  A complex summoning circle is drawn upon the ground here in red chalk.  On a raised platform sits a small dais.  Behind the dias a small, unassuming cloaked figure stands impatiently.  At your direction, the figure, known only as the arena master, will RING the GONG and summon an opponent for you.  A small sign hangs from the dias insuring all participants that this arena is free to all.  Occassionally a small wisp of smoke rises from the summoning circle.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven Hospice.
nodes.l: ...a small healing chamber.  A feeling of comfort envelopes you as you step through the door.  Lay healers and other curates garbed in white and purple gowns mill about tending to the wounded.  Each healer carries with them several small beakers, viles of holy water, and life sphere regeants.  A large alter dedicated to the Sphere of Life stands unpreteniously in the middle of the area.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven Guild.
nodes.l: ...a large training room.  In each area of the room, combatants dressed in protective gear spar under the direction of a guild trainer.  The not very tolerant guild trainer shouts instructions and offers constructive feedback to the combatants.  High above, a large balcony encircles the room.  The Pendlehaven Guildmaster paces along the balcony shouting occasionally to the people below.  The Guildmaster's loud and booming voice drowns out all conversation and each time he speaks all stop and listen.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven Bank.
nodes.l: ...a large bankroom.  There is a partition that keeps this part of the room seperate from the teller's area.  Next to the teller's aresa is another window where Ooteeny glady appraiss items in the hopes that he can convince others to sell their wares to him.  The area behind Ooteeny is a mess, piles of items strewn about the floor.  Only he (and his brothers) know for sure what he does with these items.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven General Store.
nodes.l: ...a room filled with goods and sundries.  The Pendlhaven General Stores has many of the basic items a beginning adventurer may need.  Large baskets of fruit sit near a metal scale and a variety of adventuring gear is strewn about hte store.  The store has many signs and lables about it to assist the customer in finding things.  The store is not particualrly well tended.

nodes.s: Pendlehaven Tavern.
nodes.l: ...a large tavern.  This tavern has a forboding feel to it.  A large layer of smoke hangs around the cieling of the area dimming the torchlight that is used to give this room what small lighting it has.  The musky smell of spilt ale and sweat assaults your nose as you breath.  Patrons sit at several tables talking in hushed tones as they glance about ferverishly.  In the corner, a small game of bones is being played by several men crouched low.  Servers, both male and female, glide about in what little dress they are permitted.  The sounds of pots and pans clanging against ladles and other metallic instruments can be heard coming from the kitchen.  From the drinking station the barkeep eyes you warily.

nodes.s: Underground Passage.
nodes.l: ...a long underground passage.  Clear and well kept, this smooth-stoned underground passage connects Pendlehaven and Imperial City.  Large statues of heroes line the passageway; each has a light spell cast upon the shield.  This light makes the statues seem to have a life of their own.  Pendlehaven lies to the east, Imperius to the west.
